Name: Data Engineer
Description: Data Engineer (AWS)Permanent - Brisbane - Hybrid WFH Emanate Technology is proud to be working with an Australian-born technology company that’s focused on architecting, building & operating cloud-native applications, data streams, platforms and services. The company provides solutions that are centred around AWS and best-of-breed technology. From a stand-still start in 2014, they've grown to over 500 people in just eight years across Sydney, Melbourne, Adelaide, Perth, Brisbane, Singapore and now Denver. With a diversified offering in professional services, managed services and products, they are poised for significant growth in 2022. They are the Australian AWS Consulting Partner of the Year, for the 3rd time, and recently became a Snowflake and Talend Partner. This company believes in bringing craftsmanship back to technology because as technology artisans, they passionately care about the quality outcomes they leave behind. They already have some of the best techs in Australia and due to client demand, they’re now on the hunt for experienced Data Engineers to come on board. As their Data Engineer you will help deliver scalable, automated, repeatable ‘big data’ and analytic patterns within the AWS stack. Their ideal Data Engineer understands both data pipeline development, operations and management as well as delivery of automated data solutions that are ready for production operations.From a development or operations background (or an existing DataOps Team)Understanding what getting something “done done” looks like (documentation, testing, operational requirements, continuous improvement of process)Experience with big data tools: Hadoop, Spark, Kafka, Kinesis etc.Knowledge of relational SQL and NoSQL databases, including Snowflake, PostgreSQL, Cassandra, etc.Extensive experience with data pipelines and workflow management tools: Azkaban, Luigi, NiFi, Airflow, etc.Experience with AWS cloud data services: EMR, RDS, Redshift, Kinesis, GluePrevious exposure to stream-processing systems: Storm, Spark-Streaming, etc.Experience with object-oriented/object function scripting languages: SQL, Python, PySpark, Scala, etc The Culture No cool cliques, just motivated passionate humans generating ideas and devising solutions in a creative, collaborative workspace. They're building a team and looking for people who can think outside the square and deliver what others might consider impossible.They truly embrace the notion of family and enjoy working together to achieve outstanding success.  What they offerCompetitive salary packageWorking in a flexible, outcome-driven environment. Outside of client obligations, you can work from the office or home as needed. Also, leave the suit and tie behind and put on a T-shirt instead.Weekly internal tech talks; all streamed and recorded so those who can’t make it to the office can still participate. For those who do make it, there’s pizza, beer, wine and soft drinks on tapRegular social events, meetups and guest speakers organised and facilitated by our teamA supportive family culture - If you need help, just askCelebration of the wins – big or small, because we know how hard you work. If this opportunity sounds like a good fit for you, submit your application using the "Apply" link above! Or for a confidential chat, please contact Jimmy Downey on 0481 153 606 or jimmy@emanatetechnology.com.au.

Name: IT Systems Administrator
Description: Element Engineering Australia is fast becoming one of the worlds leading product development houses. We help clients from all around the globe utilize and incorporate cutting edge technology in their designs and user experiences. With projects spanning Consumer Electronic Products, Mining Equipment, Big Data and IoT, there's no shortage of interesting challenges at Element Engineering. We are seeking an IT Systems Administrator to join our team, keep us up and running, and continually improving our systems such that we can grow and continue to provide premium service to our clients.Our Teams and SystemsOur Mechanical Engineering team works on everything from design and analysis of mining equipment, to mechatronic design of autonomous vehicles through to the mechanical design of consumer electronic products. They primarily use CAD on powerful Windows workstations and simulation on our in-house simulation server. Our Electronics Engineering team works on electronic design mainly for IoT devices across ruggedized industrial applications through to electronic products for consumers. They utilize similar CAD systems on Windows workstations.Our Software Engineering teams work across a range of developments from app development, through to back-end software and even some big data analytics. The team is split using Apple Mac laptops and workstations primarily for front-end development as well as Linux workstations for backend and server application development.All teams utilize MS Teams for collaboration, cloud and in-house Microsoft servers for file storage depending on the program requirements, cloud and in-house license server applications depending on the program, and all have the ability to work remotely when they like via cloud or VPN. Other off the shelf systems as well as some of our own bespoke systems are implemented to help the team get work done as efficiently as possible.  The RoleKeeping a diverse team up and running is a challenging IT Systems Administration role. Our IT Admin will be helping maintain systems, improving them and rolling out new systems as we need. We are seeking an IT Administrator who:is driven to be part of our growing business and teamis passionate about technologyunderstands the importance of documentation of all IT Systemsis a keen problem solveractively keeps up to date with new technologies as well as appreciating best practices and industry standard systemsYou will be undertaking the following:Management and continual deployment of engineering workstations (Primarily Windows, with some Mac and Linux machines)Management of virtual Windows Servers for Domain Controllers, Active Directory, Group Policy, DHCP, File Servers (DFSR) and DNSManagement of data backup applications and offsite backup systemsManagement of networking and security across Software Firewalls, Ubiquiti Unifi and Windows systemsManagement of software licensing servers across paid engineering software used in-houseManagement of a 3CX VOIP systemDocumentation of all systemsMaintenance of physical host Linux machines as development and production VM host serversMaintenance of Linux based web server VM's for in-house proxy systems and development environmentsThis is a challenging and diverse role, however, you will be provided with all training required to undertake the role as well as the freedom to research and explore as needed to get the job done.Pre-requisites you should bringWe'd like our IT Systems Administrator to possess the following:At least Diploma in Information Technology Systems Administration, or equivalent certificatesExperience working with Windows OS and management of Domain Controllers, Active Directory, Group Policy and associated servicesExperience with maintenance of networking systemsSome experience or at least a basic proficiency with Linux using bash/command lineWhat's in it for youThis position gives you the opportunity to grow with our business and be a key part of our business expansion.You will work directly with the Team Leaders and Management Team as well as having access to all Engineering Teams to keep them up and develop bespoke tools for your workflow as needed. With an exceptional culture, flexible working arrangements, charismatic and diverse team with many social events, amazing clients from all around the world, and the development of our own product suite as part of a newly formed additional company, being part of the Element Engineering team is more than just a job. How do you apply?Please apply here through SEEK and send through your Cover Letter and Resume. Have something ready to show us that shows relevant experience maintaining IT systems. Please note, only applicants with Australian Working Rights will be considered. Only Shortlisted candidates will be contacted. Applications only accepted directly through SEEK. Applications will not be accepted through recruitment agencies. Thank you for considering Element Engineering as the next team you may grow with.

Name: Senior API Integration Engineer
Description: AC3 is an Australian and New Zealand IT Managed Services company, working across Cloud, Infra and DevOps, Cyber Security, Apps and Data and ServiceNow. This role sits in the Apps and Data Division.    FY22/23 will see AC3’s Apps and Data Practice go through exponential growth with a new Head of Apps and Data spearheading the practice, a strong existing customer base and sizeable pipeline of work.    The Senior API Integration Engineer will work across a broad tech stack and work with some of the biggest names in the private sector as well as State and Federal Government agencies.    Fully flexible working environment, we have offices in Sydney, Melbourne, or Auckland. We're also open to remote working in A/NZ.    Culture    Voted 4th Best Place to work in 2021. Culture is a top priority at AC3. We approach business with family values, which means people here have real relationships that go beyond work. We believe it’s important that everyone is heard and treated with respect, whether you have the next big idea or simply a question. We keep it simple and live by our fours ways of being:    Own It: If I say I’m going to do it, I do it. And I give it my all. Better It: I take the current status quo and make it better. Brave It: I listen, say what needs to be said, and do the right thing. Especially when it’s tough. Enjoy It: I take my work seriously, but don’t take myself too seriously.    What will I be doing?  Guide the design and development of secure REST API & Data Integration projects Utilise expert level DevOps knowledge in the ‘Build & Design’ of deployment pipelines for project artefacts Design and implement secure serverless API & Data Integration projects on the cloud (preferably AWS and Azure) with potential to migrate to GCP Work collaboratively with the Head of Apps and Data and help to build solution proposals and convert initial program design concepts into working prototypes Implement cloud infrastructure, systems and application solutions and services with focus on CI/CD and automation tasks to treat Infrastructure as Code Provide expertise and recommendations to improve existing designs     Skills required to be successful (this is an extensive list, so if you have 60% or more of these, we would love to speak to you.)  Expert level knowledge in secure REST API & Data Integration projects with specific experience in the following technology frameworks: Java (e.g., Spring boot, Spring MVC), Python, NodeJS (e.g., Express, Mean.io), Ruby, Big Data/Analytics, Microservice Architecture, Machine Learning, OAuth2, OAS 2.0+, exposure to modern JS frameworks (e.g., React, Angular) plus other open-source frameworks Expert level DevOps knowledge in the build and design of deployment pipelines with experience in the following technologies: Source Version Control (e.g., Git, Subversion, TFS, Bitbucket etc.), containerization technologies (e.g., Docker) and their associated orchestration engines (Kubernetes/Openshift/Rancher/Swarm, Jenkins CI/CD, Octopus etc. Advanced knowledge designing and implementing secure serverless API & Data Integration projects on the cloud using some of the popular services for AWS (e.g., S3, DynamoDB, RDS, Lambda, Cognito, Data Pipeline, API Gateway etc.) and Azure (e.g., Blob, CosmosDB, SQL databases, Functions, Active Directory, Data Factory, API Management) Excellent knowledge of automated testing frameworks and tools for API & Data Integration projects (e.g., Mockito, Selenium, Apache JMeter, Flood.IO, BlazeMeter, SILKPerformer, Apigee, JMeter, JBehave, Postman etc.)    If this sounds like your sort of opportunity, then please apply and we can have a confidential conversation.    We look forward to hearing from you.

Name: Senior Analyst Data Engineer
Description:
Opportunity for a Developer to join the Test Data Management team
Showcase your exceptional experience in Big Data and Data Engineering
At NAB, we are committed to flexible working 

A career that gives you more
Your career at NAB is about more than money, it's about serving our customers well and helping our communities prosper.
We have an opportunity for a Senior Analyst Engineer to join the Test Data Management (TDM) team. This team leads the TDM design as well as oversees the build, implementation and transition of TDM changes to TDM Operations.
About the role 
As a Senior Analyst Engineer, you will be responsible for supporting various service offerings related to the TDM Asset, primarily focussed on building, maintaining and supporting Big Data delivery automation pipelines utilising & promoting best DevOps practices. This role is both strategic and operational to ensure that technical solutions enable operational excellence, are secure, reliable, scalable, cost optimized and maintainable. 
What you’ll be doing 
Your role will include but not limited to: 

Creation and maintenance of delivery pipeline tooling. Including build/deploy/CI/infrastructure scripts, monitoring, logging 
Setting up automated environment provisioning that will setup secure cloud and on premise  
Supporting the infrastructure and application layer, both in Production and non-Production environments 
Supporting the build team (Dev and Test) to be self-sustained through training and troubleshooting 
Continually learning and researching best practices and tooling for Big Data delivery 

What you’ll bring 

Demonstrated experience in application development
Proven background in deploying and managing Big Data solutions 
Experience in designed and implemented CI/CD pipelines 
Strong working knowledge of test automation principles 
Demonstrated experience establishing environments in the cloud preferably AWS, and/or Azure
Working knowledge of Cloud (AWS) environments 
Strong hand-on experience on Hadoop & Docker
Relevant tertiary qualification in related discipline

What we can offer 
From education and volunteer leave to learning benefits and banking discounts, we offer access to a wide range of employee benefits. You can learn more about these at http://www.nab.com.au/about-us/careers/working-at-nab/benefits 
We embrace diversity of thought, style and working arrangement to ensure our workforce is representative of the community that we service. 
Have a chat to us about how our support of workplace flexibility can work for you. 
NAB, invested in you
At NAB, we believe success comes from our people. We're committed to supporting your talent and skills through your career, as you help us build a culture that affects change for our customers - and for the community too.
To be eligible to apply, you must have Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency status.
Please note candidate screening and interviews may be conducted prior to the closing date of the job advert.

Name: Senior Data Analyst
Description:
Data Analyst (Contract)The CompanyJoin a Big 4 Bank with all the benefits of working with a Bank.The roleThe purpose of the role is to provide detailed analysis and investigative methods to identify suspicious activity. You will be a key member of the Fraud Prevention and Detection team and will be able to proactively problem solve and identify solutions to detect and prevent fraud. You will support the delivery of the strategic and operational plans across all aspects of the portfolio including:
Analysis and modelling of data;Solution development and design;Research and benchmarking;Insight and Intelligence;Data management and quality; andProcess and service governance.
Your day to day will include:
Optimise detection system performance proactively through development of rules and models to effectively target fraudulent activity;Collecting, analyzing and modelling data to develop and enhance detection scenario’s;Manage day-to-day operational concerns relating to performance, capability, service quality and customer experience;Interact with colleagues and stakeholders to ensure alignment, and leverage these relationships to improve overall capability; andProvide powerful visual and written insights through the use of data analysis to support decision making.
Your skills:
Around 1 - 2 years experience working as a Data Analyst working with large data sets & big dataGood experience using SQL Exposure to database and application programming (SQL Server, Teradata, Oracle, SAS, etc).Experience with any major programming language will be highly regarded (Python, R, SAS)Exposure to a big data environments
Other requirements:
Must be Australian / NZ Citizen or PRTertiary qualification requirement
Salary: Ideally $400 - $500 a day incl super (may be higher for the right candidate)Contract Length: 12 month contract with the view to extend / make permanent thereafterLocation: Melbourne CBD Location (we offer WFH flexibility)Does this role suit you?If you’re interested in this role, submit your resume using ‘apply now’ (no need for a cover letter!). or for a confidential discussion call Johnson Do on 0410 454 167 or email johnsond@halcyonknights.com.au#SCR-johnson-do

Name: Senior Analyst Data Engineer
Description:
About the role:
As a Senior Analyst Data Engineer for the Platform Operation team, you will be responsible for providing critical thinking and a high degree of technical innovation and attention to detail while being recognized as a trusted advisor to the team and stakeholders. The characteristics include being versatile, displaying leadership qualities and enthusiasm to take on new problems across the operations team, ensuring the Platform runs smoothly.
What you will be doing…
In this role you will have varying degrees of analysis, development, documentation, testing and support responsibilities and providing critical support to Production Services. You will be: 

Supporting enterprise applications
Applying pro-actively & perform hands-on design and implementation of best practice CI/CD
Taking ownership and accountability for production service, including incident & problem investigation, root cause determination and resolution
Production Support – the role requires the successful applicant to be on support for NRP and NDC – (business hours)
Developing and contributing to software verification plans and quality assurance procedures
Documenting and maintaining software functionality
Troubleshooting, debugging, and upgrading existing systems, including participating in DR test
Complying with industry standards and regulatory requirements
Coaching & mentoring of other Service Team members

What you’ll bring:

Proven experience in application development and operation support roles
Software Delivery technical skills such as CI/CD, Automated Deployments, Automated Testing, Build Servers, Software/Source Code Configuration Management
Knowledge of core AWS data services such as: S3, RDS, Redshift, DynamoDB, EMR,
Nice to have experience in supporting the following applications in an enterprise environment: PowerBI, Thoughtspot, Amazon Redshift, Powercenter
Platform automation tools experience like DB Management, AWS, Jenkins, or GITHUB
Knowledge of SQL and ETLs
Desired knowledge or experience with NAB Data Hub (NDH)
Proven ability to use relevant data analytics approaches and tools to problem-solve and trouble-shoot.
Experience in Incident and Problem Management

What we can offer 
From education and volunteer leave to learning benefits and banking discounts, we offer access to a wide range of employee benefits. You can learn more about these at http://www.nab.com.au/about-us/careers/working-at-nab/benefits 
We embrace diversity of thought, style and working arrangement to ensure our workforce is representative of the community that we service. 
Have a chat to us about how our support of workplace flexibility can work for you. 
NAB, invested in you
At NAB, we believe success comes from our people. We're committed to supporting your talent and skills through your career, as you help us build a culture that affects change for our customers - and for the community too.
To be eligible to apply, you must have Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency status.

Name: Graduate Data Coder
Description:
IRI is powered by people
We’re a fast paced, tech driven and people focused business. Innovation and entrepreneurism are part of our core DNA. We like to create, and we like to make things happen. Our team is diverse and is made up of Insight and Industry Consulting Analysts, Data Scientists, Product Managers, Solution Architects and Software Engineers. 
As an organisation we’re leading the charge as the specialist provider of data-driven, insight and consulting solutions for FMCG retailers and manufacturers. 
We power over 500+ leading Australian businesses with a number of services and solutions including;
        Client consulting services for the retail, grocery, liquor, tobacco and pharmaceutical sectors        Performance data processing and solutions for the FMCG sector        Consumer shopper, loyalty and analytics programs        Software development and cloud-based reporting platforms 
So, why IRI?
We’re progressive, inclusive and people focused. We seek to create a down to earth culture which balances work and home life and enables our team to be the best that it can be. Our people are important to us and we offer a number of fantastic benefits including;
       Flexible working with the hours you work and where you work them       Employee training and continuous development programs       Women in leadership accelerated development opportunities       5 weeks annual leave and holiday buy back scheme       Birthday leave        Summer half days        IRI Me Days       Paid parental leave       Free onsite gym and swimming pool
Key responsibilities:
You will support the Data Works team loading and maintaining high quality data for our clients on time and in full. Also, you will manage expectations of internal stakeholders and build good quality working relationships with our client insights team who will extract data from the categories you manage.
       Load and maintain database        Assign meta data such as brand and product details        Oversee the data validation process       Ensure data is provided to stakeholders accurately and on time        Research product categories to acquire general knowledge for the categories you manage       Investigate any errors in coding or data and provide resolution
We’re looking for:
       Tertiary qualification in business, mathematics, data analytics or similar       Strong attention to detail        High level of accuracy        Excellent communication skills, both verbal and written        Intermediate MS Excel skills       Database management experience (desirable)       SQL experience (desirable)       Python experience (desirable)
Interested? 
We would LOVE to hear from you. Please apply online with your CV. 
Please note, we can only consider Australian/NZ citizens or permanent residents.

Name: Level 2 Technical Support Engineer
Description: Join a global fully remote team of technical support professionals, servicing a growing customer base and enhancing their digital operations with two very impressive AI products. We’re after a talented Level 2 Technical Support Engineer to help in the performance and health of the applications from the data tier right up to the presentation layer through constant collaboration with the infrastructure and development teams! What your exciting day-to-day will look like:   Using query execution plans to spot areas of poor performance and identify fixes to SQL, indexes or other elements  Diagnose and fix issues in IIS for our VM-based solutions and Azure Application Services & Azure Functions Create, update, delete and own data transformation related parts of the solution, including SSIS packages (as we continue to move to PaaS and build exciting new features)  Participation across the SDLC for new products and application upgrades with the Infrastructure and Development teams Input into the future direction around the data and analytics tiers as we investigate and implement new AI, ML and Big Data technologies. Working closely with your fellow L1&L3 Support Engineers to provide technical support solutions  What you’ll bring to the team:   Considerable knowledge of MS SQL Server, T-SQL, SSRS, SSIS and IIS Knowledge of T-SQL Experience supporting Web-Based Applications An analytical mind - able to digest data and devise execution plans  What’s next? Apply today via the link below or reach out directly to fiona@realtimeaustralia.com for more information - we can’t wait to meet you!

Name: DevOps Engineer
Description: About Us: Established in 1991, DWS is a professional Technology Consultancy and part of HCL Technologies. With offices across Australia, we have over 800 employees in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane and Canberra; providing services to a broad range of blue-chip corporate clients, as well as Federal, State and Local Government agencies. We provide a wide range of services including; IT consulting, managed application services, project management, customer driven innovation, digital transformation, data and business analytics, strategic advisory and productivity, and robotic process automation. About the role: DWS is looking for experienced DevOps Engineers who can work with platforms teams on building out their CI/CD capability and moving their current infrastructure to GitLab. You would also be supporting, building and maintaining their platform team’s AWS infrastructure.. The right people for these roles will be passionate and really love their DevOps work! Skills and Experience:  Expert with CI/CD: BuildKite & Ansible Experience with Golang, Python, Node.js or Java Experience with TDD and Paired Programming Experience with AWS ECS, Kubernetes, Lambda & AWS Batch Jobs, Step Functions and Spark Knowledge of Kinesis, Kafka, SQS, SNS and Firehose Knowledge of DynamoDB, RDS, S3 and Athena Apigee (API Gateway), AWS Cognito and Okta (Identity Management) This is a Hybrid position (it will consist of home and office based work)  Working at DWS offers you:  Ongoing professional and career development Paid learning and certifications (chosen entirely by you), with completion bonuses An active social club that host regular, subsidised events Corporate discounts on a range of services and products, including health insurance, gym memberships, JB HiFi, Apple products and much more  All applicants must hold Australian Citizenship, Permanent Residency (PR), or other permanent work rights – DWS are unable to sponsor or support visas. Ready for a new challenge? Click APPLY now! www.dws.com.au

Name: CRM Program Director (Sydney or Melbourne)
Description: About Gravitas Gravitas is an entrepreneurial Customer Relationship Management (CRM), loyalty and big data agency and is a market leader in customer engagement and retention. Its core purpose is to accelerate customer value management, engagement and performance. Gravitas’ key focus is to work with data and analytics to derive customer insights that inform targeted and differentiated CRM and loyalty strategies.About The Opportunity The primary purpose of the CRM Program and Account Director role is to have exceptional understanding of our clients and their customer’s needs. The role involves ensuring the successful execution of customer management and loyalty strategies. This includes taking responsibility for all aspects of strategy and execution and managing the relationship and communications with the client and stakeholders. About YouYou have an exceptional understanding of customers and their needs – they are at the centre of your world. This role requires you to draw on your skills as a CRM and account lead. You are technology- and data-minded and understand how the market is developing.  And – needless to say – you’re a team player who finds it easy to work together with people from many different disciplines and who is prepared to look at things from various perspectives. Your work is always interesting because it involves a lot of experimentation and various clients - and you’re not afraid to fail now and again – in fact, that just makes you even more creative!Mandatory Criteria We are looking for a superstar with the following skills and experience:7+ years’ experience in CRM / Account Management Experience developing data-driven marketing & customer-engagement strategies Proven cross-industry experience in Marketing with an understanding of key business drivers in Retail Commercially astute with strong financial acumen Confident communicator with outstanding written and oral skills A dynamic personality with an ability to effectively engage and influence a variety of stakeholders at all levels You will also have a Tertiary/Post Graduate qualification, ideally in Marketing/Commerce/ Business/Finance or Communications.This really is a fantastic opportunity to work with a leading-edge data driven agency with high profile clients. As a bonus, we’ll throw in a talented and experienced team who are also a lot of fun to work with. If you meet the selection criteria above apply now by forwarding your resume and cover letter. Please contact Sonia Tammaro at sonia@innov8te.com.au if you have questions or apply now.

Name: Senior Engineer - Scala, Spark, Big Data
Description: Do Work that Matters As an experienced data engineer with proven expertise in software development and a passion for providing data-driven solutions, you're ahead of trends and work at the forefront of Big Data technologies.  Which is why we're the perfect fit for you. Here, you'll be part of a team of engineers going above and beyond to improve the standard of digital banking. Using the latest tech to solve our customers' most complex data-centric problems.  Across our end-to-end cycle, it will be your job to support the design and construction of large-scale automated machine learning and data mining practices. Drawing from your ability to integrate diverse sets of data from multiple sources you will design, develop and build industry-leading group data products.  Your experience means you're able to execute state-of-the-art coding practices, driving high quality outcomes to solve core business objectives and minimise risks. Communicating to technical and non-technical stakeholders across the business comes naturally to you.  As someone who's both eager to learn and share knowledge, you're at home in a culture where quality, excellence and openness are championed. Here you'll experience flexibility, great rewards and the opportunity to drive your own career growth.  See yourself in the Team?  To us, data is everything. It's what powers our cutting-edge features and it's the reason we can provide seamless experiences for millions of customers from app to branch.  We're responsible for CommBank's key analytics capabilities and work to create world-leading capabilities for analytics, information management and decisioning. We work across the Group Data Warehouse, Hadoop Big Data Platform, Pega Decisioning, SAS, R, Tableau, Oracle BI, Ab Initio and Data Stage.  We value innovation and encourage our employees to constantly think outside the box and break boundaries to solve complex problems. Our diverse teams are dedicated to learning, sharing knowledge and continuous improvement.  We're always interested in hearing from people who: Have experience working with enterprise-level software applications providing Big Data solutions on Cloudera Hadoop platform. Possess strong skills and background within software engineering, preferably with backend coding in Java, Scala and Python Hold a strong exposure to Ab Initio ETL product suite Demonstrated experience in writing Spark APIs, Hive and Impala queries, along with strong expertise working with Apache Kafka and Apache Cassandra. What skills you will need to be successful? Strong skills in software data engineering and functional programming in Scala, along with backend coding expertise in Java and Python are mandatory. Demonstrated experience in design and development of big data applications on a Hadoop platform, using Spark and ETL based tech stack is highly essential. Commendable skills in building group data products from scratch, by integrating large sets of data from hundreds of internal and external sources would be highly critical. A true passion to learn new skills, along with being diligent to solve data problems with a proactive, risk-mindset. A natural ability to educate, communicate and positively influence large stakeholder groups, and to continuously collaborate with multiple engineering teams is highly essential! What's in it for you? Flexible working programs to promote your mental well-being and work life balance! A brilliant team culture that promotes collaboration and innovation at its core! Fantastic opportunities for career growth If this sounds like you, apply now!  The health and safety of our people, customers and communities is our number one priority. This means that we require all of our employees to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. Please speak to us if you have any questions about this based on your individual circumstances. Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career here is for you. Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive and flexible workplace. One where we're driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.Here, you'll thrive. You'll be supported when faced with challenges, and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We really love working here, and we think you will too.We're determined to make a real difference for Australia's first peoples. We encourage all interested applicants to apply. If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick [link removed] to submit a valid application. We're keen to support you with the next step in your career.

Name: Principal Data Architect
Description: The Company  A big brand with a reputation for leading the way with Big Data is looking for a Principle Architect who is passionate about building cutting edge BI solutions in an Agile environment.  This company is investing significantly into their Big Data capability, with a huge project environment & a push to provide a world-class data processing capability.  With big budgets & long scope, this role will see you working on some of the most exciting projects in the local market.  Hit the Apply for this job button now to get more information!    About the Role  You will be responsible for developing and maintaining information architecture - Implement Data Management, Data Governance and Process Governance frameworks across the organization and to educate the Senior Leadership teams around the benefits.  You will plan with vision and foresight to provide high quality data, to identify and define common information requirements, to design conceptual structures and plans to meet the current and long-term data requirements at an enterprise level.    Technical Skills Needed: Degree qualified in Business management, IT, Computer Systems, software or computer engineering fields or equivalent.10+ years commercial experience with relational & dimensional data modelling, process modelling of large scale data warehousesData-modelling and Information modelling, classification expertise, excellent Enterprise conceptual modelling skillsStrong experience in Reference & Master Data Management, Data Quality, Data GovernanceStrong technical knowledge and experience in RDBMS (Teradata), Big Data (Cloudera), ETL (Informatica Power Centre/BDM), Metadata management and BI analytics toolsData Quality tools - Informatica or equivalentData Security tools - Dynamic Data masking on various technology platforms eg Teradata, Cloudera etcData Modelling using tools like ERWinHadoop / Big Data knowledge and experienceKnowledge of Cloud Platform like GCP, Azure What's in it for you:  You'll be joining a large Agile team with a manager that believes in continual development. This team has excellent staff retention rates and the manager looks for people that want to grow with the company for years to come.  They have a reputation for being a great place to work with excellent career growth opportunities and internal promotions. With an awesome site, they have a gym, onsite restaurants, bars and cafes. They also provide a flexible hybrid work from home arrangements.  This is a company that genuinely promotes flexibility and work/life balance, really valuing their employees.  Hit the Apply for this job button now or contact Adam on 0478026276 to get more information!

Name: Pre-Sales Consultant (APAC, AML, Financial Services, Fraud, Big Data)
Description: Pre-Sales Consultant (APAC, AML, Financial Services, Fraud, Big Data)   My client, a leading multinational firm with a strong presence across the financial services and insurance space, is urgently seeking pre-sales consultants with a remit across APAC to specify and perform demos for maximum customer impact. The successful pre-sales consultant will provide subject matter expertise and demos in pre-sales meetings, respond to RFP’s and RFI’s, and provide business consultancy on high risk pilots, including complex new propositions. You will possess broad and detailed customer domain knowledge, functional and/or technical understanding of the products’ capabilities, as well as my clients’ competitors, and be expected to interact with customer and delivery teams throughout complex project lifecycles to ensure solutions lead to high customer satisfaction.   Key Attributes  APAC regional financial crime (fraud and/or compliance domain) experience. Proven senior stakeholder management capabilities. Demonstrable analytics experience, including the use of open source tools. Public speaking and thought leadership background. Experience of working across multiple time zones and being part of a distributed broader regional team   Desirable Attributes  Experience working in financial crime detection in banking / financial services Experience in AML (anti-money laundering) and Fraud solutions including technical configuration. Strong preference for cross domain operational experience. Graph Based Network Analytics experience is advantageous. Understanding of Big Data technologies.  Joining a dynamic and Agile organisation with a strong presence within the financial services and insurance sector, you will play a pivotal role in driving a number of initiatives simultaneously. You will be nurtured and supported to take your career to the next step in this growing and high-performing team. My client provides a very strong remuneration package and promotes a highly collaborative culture.   Also, great salary, bonus, flexible working. Please forward your CV or contact details for more information and/ or a confidential discussion.   Location: Sydney Salary: Highly Competitive  Start: Immediate

Name: Senior Developer Programmer
Description: About us Billigence Pty Ltd is a specialist in the delivery of market-leading Business Intelligence and CRM solutions. Headquartered in Sydney, Australia and with offices in Prague, London, Frankfurt and Singapore our passion is data and our focus is the delivery of end-to-end solutions via a talented team of skilled professionals. We are partners with leading edge software platforms including Tableau, Alteryx, Collibra, Snowflake and Salesforce. What we are looking for:Senior Developer Programmer to join our team. Essential skills/experience required:  Strong experience as a big data engineer / Developer Programmer working with Hadoop Solid experience working with Spark, Hive etc Programming experience with either Scala, Java or python Excellent written & verbal communication skills    You will be responsible for:  Responsible for the development of Data Analysis tools, analytics reporting and real-time analysis systems. We are passionate about employee development and progression and would love to hear from individuals that share our values and ambitions.If this sounds like something you are interested in, please apply with your most up-to-date CV and we will be in touch!

Name: Consultant/Senior Consultant
Description:
IRI is powered by people
We’re a fast paced, tech driven and people focused business. Innovation and entrepreneurism are part of our core DNA. We like to create, and we like to make things happen. Our team is diverse and is made up of Insight and Industry Consulting Analysts, Data Scientists, Product Managers, Solution Architects and Software Engineers. 
As an organisation we’re leading the charge as the specialist provider of data-driven, insight and consulting solutions for FMCG retailers and manufacturers. We power over 500+ leading Australian and New Zealand businesses with a number of services and solutions, including;
          Client consulting services for the grocery, pharmacy, liquor, tobacco and petrol & convenience sectors          Performance data processing and solutions for the FMCG sector          Consumer shopper, loyalty and analytics programs          Software development and cloud-based reporting platforms 
So, why IRI?
We’re progressive, inclusive and people focused. We seek to create a down to earth culture which balances work and home life and enables our team to be the best that it can be. Our people are important to us and we offer a number of fantastic benefits, including; 
         Flexible working both on and off-site         Employee training and continuous development programs         Women in leadership accelerated development opportunities         Up to 5 weeks annual leave and holiday buy back scheme         Paid maternity and paternity leave          Birthday leave          Summer half days          IRI Me Days          Free onsite gym and swimming pool
Key responsibilities:
 Effectively partnering with well-known FMCG manufacturers, you will:
         Define business problems through consultations with clients and provide solutions to their business needs          Solve briefs with actionable recommendations through incorporating analysis from different data sources          Provide and present insights through storytelling          Lead client relationships and proactively develop these relationships to deliver against account plan objectives          Be the responsible for client contract, financials (including invoicing), renewal and growth revenue target          Lead business development activities for targeted accounts 
We're looking for:
         2-5 years’ experience in data analysis/insights or category management, at a market research agency or FMCG manufacturer/retailer          Previous experience working with scan, shopper or customer data          Strong account management and client servicing skills          A creative and curious nature, with the ability to effectively problem solve          Ability to influence and engage senior stakeholders         A confident persona, with the capability to effectively manage client expectations          Strong commercial acumen with the ability to identify business development opportunities 
Interested? We would LOVE to hear from you. Please apply online by submitting your CV. 
Even if you don’t meet all of the above criteria, we encourage you to submit your application.

Name: Data Scientist - Early Career
Description: Nothing stands out on a CV like experience at a high profile, successful business.     Seize your chance to join one of the biggest and best data science teams in Australia as an Early Career Data Scientist!    This top data science team builds commercial analytics and machine learning solutions that have a big impact this company’s performance.    Here’s some of the work the new starters completed last year:  They gained a solid understanding and de-bugging of the code base for one or more production machine learning models and data pipelines built with Python, SQL, Apache Spark and deployed on Google Cloud Platform. They assisted a senior data scientist to scale a model using kubernetes or kubeflow – making it easier to move into production and scale millions of customers records. They developed APIs to help other analytics or technology teams in the business consume and use your data science products  What we’re looking for:   You need skills (1 to 5 years) in data science and are already a strong practitioner with: Python, SQL and tree-based algorithms such as Random Forest, GBMs, XGBOOST At least a bachelor’s degree, Masters or PhD in a related numerical discipline – such as; Computer Science, Software Engineering, Statistics, Actuarial Studies, or a similar field (perhaps Aeronautical Engineering) which combines strong numerical, data and technical skills You will definitely need full, unrestricted Australian work rights – ie a bridging visa or something longer term. Sponsorship is not available. You can be based anywhere in Australia, but long-term, Sydney is the head office. To relocate there would be at your expense. Heavy preference will be given to good commercial experience with data science using real customer data for big companies or start-ups  Interest in these roles will be immense. Set yourself apart by writing a cover letter that demonstrates your experience with customer data or large data sets, and apply ASAP!

Name: Data Engineer
Description: Data Engineer (AWS)Permanent - Brisbane - Hybrid WFH Emanate Technology is proud to be working with an Australian-born technology company that’s focused on architecting, building & operating cloud-native applications, data streams, platforms and services. The company provides solutions that are centred around AWS and best-of-breed technology. From a stand-still start in 2014, they've grown to over 500 people in just eight years across Sydney, Melbourne, Adelaide, Perth, Brisbane, Singapore and now Denver. With a diversified offering in professional services, managed services and products, they are poised for significant growth in 2022. They are the Australian AWS Consulting Partner of the Year, for the 3rd time, and recently became a Snowflake and Talend Partner. This company believes in bringing craftsmanship back to technology because as technology artisans, they passionately care about the quality outcomes they leave behind. They already have some of the best techs in Australia and due to client demand, they’re now on the hunt for experienced Data Engineers to come on board. As their Data Engineer you will help deliver scalable, automated, repeatable ‘big data’ and analytic patterns within the AWS stack. Their ideal Data Engineer understands both data pipeline development, operations and management as well as delivery of automated data solutions that are ready for production operations.From a development or operations background (or an existing DataOps Team)Understanding what getting something “done done” looks like (documentation, testing, operational requirements, continuous improvement of process)Experience with big data tools: Hadoop, Spark, Kafka, Kinesis etc.Knowledge of relational SQL and NoSQL databases, including Snowflake, PostgreSQL, Cassandra, etc.Extensive experience with data pipelines and workflow management tools: Azkaban, Luigi, NiFi, Airflow, etc.Experience with AWS cloud data services: EMR, RDS, Redshift, Kinesis, GluePrevious exposure to stream-processing systems: Storm, Spark-Streaming, etc.Experience with object-oriented/object function scripting languages: SQL, Python, PySpark, Scala, etc The Culture No cool cliques, just motivated passionate humans generating ideas and devising solutions in a creative, collaborative workspace. They're building a team and looking for people who can think outside the square and deliver what others might consider impossible.They truly embrace the notion of family and enjoy working together to achieve outstanding success.  What they offerCompetitive salary packageWorking in a flexible, outcome-driven environment. Outside of client obligations, you can work from the office or home as needed. Also, leave the suit and tie behind and put on a T-shirt instead.Weekly internal tech talks; all streamed and recorded so those who can’t make it to the office can still participate. For those who do make it, there’s pizza, beer, wine and soft drinks on tapRegular social events, meetups and guest speakers organised and facilitated by our teamA supportive family culture - If you need help, just askCelebration of the wins – big or small, because we know how hard you work. If this opportunity sounds like a good fit for you, submit your application using the "Apply" link above! Or for a confidential chat, please contact Jimmy Downey on 0481 153 606 or jimmy@emanatetechnology.com.au.

Name: IT Systems Administrator
Description: Element Engineering Australia is fast becoming one of the worlds leading product development houses. We help clients from all around the globe utilize and incorporate cutting edge technology in their designs and user experiences. With projects spanning Consumer Electronic Products, Mining Equipment, Big Data and IoT, there's no shortage of interesting challenges at Element Engineering. We are seeking an IT Systems Administrator to join our team, keep us up and running, and continually improving our systems such that we can grow and continue to provide premium service to our clients.Our Teams and SystemsOur Mechanical Engineering team works on everything from design and analysis of mining equipment, to mechatronic design of autonomous vehicles through to the mechanical design of consumer electronic products. They primarily use CAD on powerful Windows workstations and simulation on our in-house simulation server. Our Electronics Engineering team works on electronic design mainly for IoT devices across ruggedized industrial applications through to electronic products for consumers. They utilize similar CAD systems on Windows workstations.Our Software Engineering teams work across a range of developments from app development, through to back-end software and even some big data analytics. The team is split using Apple Mac laptops and workstations primarily for front-end development as well as Linux workstations for backend and server application development.All teams utilize MS Teams for collaboration, cloud and in-house Microsoft servers for file storage depending on the program requirements, cloud and in-house license server applications depending on the program, and all have the ability to work remotely when they like via cloud or VPN. Other off the shelf systems as well as some of our own bespoke systems are implemented to help the team get work done as efficiently as possible.  The RoleKeeping a diverse team up and running is a challenging IT Systems Administration role. Our IT Admin will be helping maintain systems, improving them and rolling out new systems as we need. We are seeking an IT Administrator who:is driven to be part of our growing business and teamis passionate about technologyunderstands the importance of documentation of all IT Systemsis a keen problem solveractively keeps up to date with new technologies as well as appreciating best practices and industry standard systemsYou will be undertaking the following:Management and continual deployment of engineering workstations (Primarily Windows, with some Mac and Linux machines)Management of virtual Windows Servers for Domain Controllers, Active Directory, Group Policy, DHCP, File Servers (DFSR) and DNSManagement of data backup applications and offsite backup systemsManagement of networking and security across Software Firewalls, Ubiquiti Unifi and Windows systemsManagement of software licensing servers across paid engineering software used in-houseManagement of a 3CX VOIP systemDocumentation of all systemsMaintenance of physical host Linux machines as development and production VM host serversMaintenance of Linux based web server VM's for in-house proxy systems and development environmentsThis is a challenging and diverse role, however, you will be provided with all training required to undertake the role as well as the freedom to research and explore as needed to get the job done.Pre-requisites you should bringWe'd like our IT Systems Administrator to possess the following:At least Diploma in Information Technology Systems Administration, or equivalent certificatesExperience working with Windows OS and management of Domain Controllers, Active Directory, Group Policy and associated servicesExperience with maintenance of networking systemsSome experience or at least a basic proficiency with Linux using bash/command lineWhat's in it for youThis position gives you the opportunity to grow with our business and be a key part of our business expansion.You will work directly with the Team Leaders and Management Team as well as having access to all Engineering Teams to keep them up and develop bespoke tools for your workflow as needed. With an exceptional culture, flexible working arrangements, charismatic and diverse team with many social events, amazing clients from all around the world, and the development of our own product suite as part of a newly formed additional company, being part of the Element Engineering team is more than just a job. How do you apply?Please apply here through SEEK and send through your Cover Letter and Resume. Have something ready to show us that shows relevant experience maintaining IT systems. Please note, only applicants with Australian Working Rights will be considered. Only Shortlisted candidates will be contacted. Applications only accepted directly through SEEK. Applications will not be accepted through recruitment agencies. Thank you for considering Element Engineering as the next team you may grow with.

Name: Senior API Integration Engineer
Description: AC3 is an Australian and New Zealand IT Managed Services company, working across Cloud, Infra and DevOps, Cyber Security, Apps and Data and ServiceNow. This role sits in the Apps and Data Division.    FY22/23 will see AC3’s Apps and Data Practice go through exponential growth with a new Head of Apps and Data spearheading the practice, a strong existing customer base and sizeable pipeline of work.    The Senior API Integration Engineer will work across a broad tech stack and work with some of the biggest names in the private sector as well as State and Federal Government agencies.    Fully flexible working environment, we have offices in Sydney, Melbourne, or Auckland. We're also open to remote working in A/NZ.    Culture    Voted 4th Best Place to work in 2021. Culture is a top priority at AC3. We approach business with family values, which means people here have real relationships that go beyond work. We believe it’s important that everyone is heard and treated with respect, whether you have the next big idea or simply a question. We keep it simple and live by our fours ways of being:    Own It: If I say I’m going to do it, I do it. And I give it my all. Better It: I take the current status quo and make it better. Brave It: I listen, say what needs to be said, and do the right thing. Especially when it’s tough. Enjoy It: I take my work seriously, but don’t take myself too seriously.    What will I be doing?  Guide the design and development of secure REST API & Data Integration projects Utilise expert level DevOps knowledge in the ‘Build & Design’ of deployment pipelines for project artefacts Design and implement secure serverless API & Data Integration projects on the cloud (preferably AWS and Azure) with potential to migrate to GCP Work collaboratively with the Head of Apps and Data and help to build solution proposals and convert initial program design concepts into working prototypes Implement cloud infrastructure, systems and application solutions and services with focus on CI/CD and automation tasks to treat Infrastructure as Code Provide expertise and recommendations to improve existing designs     Skills required to be successful (this is an extensive list, so if you have 60% or more of these, we would love to speak to you.)  Expert level knowledge in secure REST API & Data Integration projects with specific experience in the following technology frameworks: Java (e.g., Spring boot, Spring MVC), Python, NodeJS (e.g., Express, Mean.io), Ruby, Big Data/Analytics, Microservice Architecture, Machine Learning, OAuth2, OAS 2.0+, exposure to modern JS frameworks (e.g., React, Angular) plus other open-source frameworks Expert level DevOps knowledge in the build and design of deployment pipelines with experience in the following technologies: Source Version Control (e.g., Git, Subversion, TFS, Bitbucket etc.), containerization technologies (e.g., Docker) and their associated orchestration engines (Kubernetes/Openshift/Rancher/Swarm, Jenkins CI/CD, Octopus etc. Advanced knowledge designing and implementing secure serverless API & Data Integration projects on the cloud using some of the popular services for AWS (e.g., S3, DynamoDB, RDS, Lambda, Cognito, Data Pipeline, API Gateway etc.) and Azure (e.g., Blob, CosmosDB, SQL databases, Functions, Active Directory, Data Factory, API Management) Excellent knowledge of automated testing frameworks and tools for API & Data Integration projects (e.g., Mockito, Selenium, Apache JMeter, Flood.IO, BlazeMeter, SILKPerformer, Apigee, JMeter, JBehave, Postman etc.)    If this sounds like your sort of opportunity, then please apply and we can have a confidential conversation.    We look forward to hearing from you.

Name: Senior Analyst Data Engineer
Description:
Opportunity for a Developer to join the Test Data Management team
Showcase your exceptional experience in Big Data and Data Engineering
At NAB, we are committed to flexible working 

A career that gives you more
Your career at NAB is about more than money, it's about serving our customers well and helping our communities prosper.
We have an opportunity for a Senior Analyst Engineer to join the Test Data Management (TDM) team. This team leads the TDM design as well as oversees the build, implementation and transition of TDM changes to TDM Operations.
About the role 
As a Senior Analyst Engineer, you will be responsible for supporting various service offerings related to the TDM Asset, primarily focussed on building, maintaining and supporting Big Data delivery automation pipelines utilising & promoting best DevOps practices. This role is both strategic and operational to ensure that technical solutions enable operational excellence, are secure, reliable, scalable, cost optimized and maintainable. 
What you’ll be doing 
Your role will include but not limited to: 

Creation and maintenance of delivery pipeline tooling. Including build/deploy/CI/infrastructure scripts, monitoring, logging 
Setting up automated environment provisioning that will setup secure cloud and on premise  
Supporting the infrastructure and application layer, both in Production and non-Production environments 
Supporting the build team (Dev and Test) to be self-sustained through training and troubleshooting 
Continually learning and researching best practices and tooling for Big Data delivery 

What you’ll bring 

Demonstrated experience in application development
Proven background in deploying and managing Big Data solutions 
Experience in designed and implemented CI/CD pipelines 
Strong working knowledge of test automation principles 
Demonstrated experience establishing environments in the cloud preferably AWS, and/or Azure
Working knowledge of Cloud (AWS) environments 
Strong hand-on experience on Hadoop & Docker
Relevant tertiary qualification in related discipline

What we can offer 
From education and volunteer leave to learning benefits and banking discounts, we offer access to a wide range of employee benefits. You can learn more about these at http://www.nab.com.au/about-us/careers/working-at-nab/benefits 
We embrace diversity of thought, style and working arrangement to ensure our workforce is representative of the community that we service. 
Have a chat to us about how our support of workplace flexibility can work for you. 
NAB, invested in you
At NAB, we believe success comes from our people. We're committed to supporting your talent and skills through your career, as you help us build a culture that affects change for our customers - and for the community too.
To be eligible to apply, you must have Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency status.
Please note candidate screening and interviews may be conducted prior to the closing date of the job advert.

Name: Senior Data Analyst
Description:
Data Analyst (Contract)The CompanyJoin a Big 4 Bank with all the benefits of working with a Bank.The roleThe purpose of the role is to provide detailed analysis and investigative methods to identify suspicious activity. You will be a key member of the Fraud Prevention and Detection team and will be able to proactively problem solve and identify solutions to detect and prevent fraud. You will support the delivery of the strategic and operational plans across all aspects of the portfolio including:
Analysis and modelling of data;Solution development and design;Research and benchmarking;Insight and Intelligence;Data management and quality; andProcess and service governance.
Your day to day will include:
Optimise detection system performance proactively through development of rules and models to effectively target fraudulent activity;Collecting, analyzing and modelling data to develop and enhance detection scenario’s;Manage day-to-day operational concerns relating to performance, capability, service quality and customer experience;Interact with colleagues and stakeholders to ensure alignment, and leverage these relationships to improve overall capability; andProvide powerful visual and written insights through the use of data analysis to support decision making.
Your skills:
Around 1 - 2 years experience working as a Data Analyst working with large data sets & big dataGood experience using SQL Exposure to database and application programming (SQL Server, Teradata, Oracle, SAS, etc).Experience with any major programming language will be highly regarded (Python, R, SAS)Exposure to a big data environments
Other requirements:
Must be Australian / NZ Citizen or PRTertiary qualification requirement
Salary: Ideally $400 - $500 a day incl super (may be higher for the right candidate)Contract Length: 12 month contract with the view to extend / make permanent thereafterLocation: Melbourne CBD Location (we offer WFH flexibility)Does this role suit you?If you’re interested in this role, submit your resume using ‘apply now’ (no need for a cover letter!). or for a confidential discussion call Johnson Do on 0410 454 167 or email johnsond@halcyonknights.com.au#SCR-johnson-do

Name: Senior Analyst Data Engineer
Description:
About the role:
As a Senior Analyst Data Engineer for the Platform Operation team, you will be responsible for providing critical thinking and a high degree of technical innovation and attention to detail while being recognized as a trusted advisor to the team and stakeholders. The characteristics include being versatile, displaying leadership qualities and enthusiasm to take on new problems across the operations team, ensuring the Platform runs smoothly.
What you will be doing…
In this role you will have varying degrees of analysis, development, documentation, testing and support responsibilities and providing critical support to Production Services. You will be: 

Supporting enterprise applications
Applying pro-actively & perform hands-on design and implementation of best practice CI/CD
Taking ownership and accountability for production service, including incident & problem investigation, root cause determination and resolution
Production Support – the role requires the successful applicant to be on support for NRP and NDC – (business hours)
Developing and contributing to software verification plans and quality assurance procedures
Documenting and maintaining software functionality
Troubleshooting, debugging, and upgrading existing systems, including participating in DR test
Complying with industry standards and regulatory requirements
Coaching & mentoring of other Service Team members

What you’ll bring:

Proven experience in application development and operation support roles
Software Delivery technical skills such as CI/CD, Automated Deployments, Automated Testing, Build Servers, Software/Source Code Configuration Management
Knowledge of core AWS data services such as: S3, RDS, Redshift, DynamoDB, EMR,
Nice to have experience in supporting the following applications in an enterprise environment: PowerBI, Thoughtspot, Amazon Redshift, Powercenter
Platform automation tools experience like DB Management, AWS, Jenkins, or GITHUB
Knowledge of SQL and ETLs
Desired knowledge or experience with NAB Data Hub (NDH)
Proven ability to use relevant data analytics approaches and tools to problem-solve and trouble-shoot.
Experience in Incident and Problem Management

What we can offer 
From education and volunteer leave to learning benefits and banking discounts, we offer access to a wide range of employee benefits. You can learn more about these at http://www.nab.com.au/about-us/careers/working-at-nab/benefits 
We embrace diversity of thought, style and working arrangement to ensure our workforce is representative of the community that we service. 
Have a chat to us about how our support of workplace flexibility can work for you. 
NAB, invested in you
At NAB, we believe success comes from our people. We're committed to supporting your talent and skills through your career, as you help us build a culture that affects change for our customers - and for the community too.

Name: Graduate Data Coder
Description:
IRI is powered by people
We’re a fast paced, tech driven and people focused business. Innovation and entrepreneurism are part of our core DNA. We like to create, and we like to make things happen. Our team is diverse and is made up of Insight and Industry Consulting Analysts, Data Scientists, Product Managers, Solution Architects and Software Engineers. 
As an organisation we’re leading the charge as the specialist provider of data-driven, insight and consulting solutions for FMCG retailers and manufacturers. 
We power over 500+ leading Australian businesses with a number of services and solutions including;
        Client consulting services for the retail, grocery, liquor, tobacco and pharmaceutical sectors        Performance data processing and solutions for the FMCG sector        Consumer shopper, loyalty and analytics programs        Software development and cloud-based reporting platforms 
So, why IRI?
We’re progressive, inclusive and people focused. We seek to create a down to earth culture which balances work and home life and enables our team to be the best that it can be. Our people are important to us and we offer a number of fantastic benefits including;
       Flexible working with the hours you work and where you work them       Employee training and continuous development programs       Women in leadership accelerated development opportunities       5 weeks annual leave and holiday buy back scheme       Birthday leave        Summer half days        IRI Me Days       Paid parental leave       Free onsite gym and swimming pool
Key responsibilities:
You will support the Data Works team loading and maintaining high quality data for our clients on time and in full. Also, you will manage expectations of internal stakeholders and build good quality working relationships with our client insights team who will extract data from the categories you manage.
       Load and maintain database        Assign meta data such as brand and product details        Oversee the data validation process       Ensure data is provided to stakeholders accurately and on time        Research product categories to acquire general knowledge for the categories you manage       Investigate any errors in coding or data and provide resolution
We’re looking for:
       Tertiary qualification in business, mathematics, data analytics or similar       Strong attention to detail        High level of accuracy        Excellent communication skills, both verbal and written        Intermediate MS Excel skills       Database management experience (desirable)       SQL experience (desirable)       Python experience (desirable)
Interested? 
We would LOVE to hear from you. Please apply online with your CV. 
Please note, we can only consider Australian/NZ citizens or permanent residents.

Name: Level 2 Technical Support Engineer
Description: Join a global fully remote team of technical support professionals, servicing a growing customer base and enhancing their digital operations with two very impressive AI products. We’re after a talented Level 2 Technical Support Engineer to help in the performance and health of the applications from the data tier right up to the presentation layer through constant collaboration with the infrastructure and development teams! What your exciting day-to-day will look like:   Using query execution plans to spot areas of poor performance and identify fixes to SQL, indexes or other elements  Diagnose and fix issues in IIS for our VM-based solutions and Azure Application Services & Azure Functions Create, update, delete and own data transformation related parts of the solution, including SSIS packages (as we continue to move to PaaS and build exciting new features)  Participation across the SDLC for new products and application upgrades with the Infrastructure and Development teams Input into the future direction around the data and analytics tiers as we investigate and implement new AI, ML and Big Data technologies. Working closely with your fellow L1&L3 Support Engineers to provide technical support solutions  What you’ll bring to the team:   Considerable knowledge of MS SQL Server, T-SQL, SSRS, SSIS and IIS Knowledge of T-SQL Experience supporting Web-Based Applications An analytical mind - able to digest data and devise execution plans  What’s next? Apply today via the link below or reach out directly to fiona@realtimeaustralia.com for more information - we can’t wait to meet you!

Name: DevOps Engineer
Description: About Us: Established in 1991, DWS is a professional Technology Consultancy and part of HCL Technologies. With offices across Australia, we have over 800 employees in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane and Canberra; providing services to a broad range of blue-chip corporate clients, as well as Federal, State and Local Government agencies. We provide a wide range of services including; IT consulting, managed application services, project management, customer driven innovation, digital transformation, data and business analytics, strategic advisory and productivity, and robotic process automation. About the role: DWS is looking for experienced DevOps Engineers who can work with platforms teams on building out their CI/CD capability and moving their current infrastructure to GitLab. You would also be supporting, building and maintaining their platform team’s AWS infrastructure.. The right people for these roles will be passionate and really love their DevOps work! Skills and Experience:  Expert with CI/CD: BuildKite & Ansible Experience with Golang, Python, Node.js or Java Experience with TDD and Paired Programming Experience with AWS ECS, Kubernetes, Lambda & AWS Batch Jobs, Step Functions and Spark Knowledge of Kinesis, Kafka, SQS, SNS and Firehose Knowledge of DynamoDB, RDS, S3 and Athena Apigee (API Gateway), AWS Cognito and Okta (Identity Management) This is a Hybrid position (it will consist of home and office based work)  Working at DWS offers you:  Ongoing professional and career development Paid learning and certifications (chosen entirely by you), with completion bonuses An active social club that host regular, subsidised events Corporate discounts on a range of services and products, including health insurance, gym memberships, JB HiFi, Apple products and much more  All applicants must hold Australian Citizenship, Permanent Residency (PR), or other permanent work rights – DWS are unable to sponsor or support visas. Ready for a new challenge? Click APPLY now! www.dws.com.au

Name: QA Manager (Big Data)
Description: Looking to take the next step into a QA Lead opportunity? Look no further!  Your new company Your new organisation is a world-leading analytical data virtualisation solution company, and we passionate about being at the forefront of the analytics technology field. Enjoy the benefits of a Start-up culture - fast paced and dynamic, innovative, results driven, with a down to earth team who is supportive and collaborative.  Your new roleWe are looking for a QA lead who really wants to build ground-breaking S/W in the Big Data space. This QA Lead is responsible for leading quality review of the Networked Data Platform(NDB) and includes creating test plans and strategy, test cases in partnership with developers, customer success team and Dev Lead.
