Name: CRM Program Director (Sydney or Melbourne)
Description: About Gravitas Gravitas is an entrepreneurial Customer Relationship Management (CRM), loyalty and big data agency and is a market leader in customer engagement and retention. Its core purpose is to accelerate customer value management, engagement and performance. Gravitas’ key focus is to work with data and analytics to derive customer insights that inform targeted and differentiated CRM and loyalty strategies.About The Opportunity The primary purpose of the CRM Program and Account Director role is to have exceptional understanding of our clients and their customer’s needs. The role involves ensuring the successful execution of customer management and loyalty strategies. This includes taking responsibility for all aspects of strategy and execution and managing the relationship and communications with the client and stakeholders. About YouYou have an exceptional understanding of customers and their needs – they are at the centre of your world. This role requires you to draw on your skills as a CRM and account lead. You are technology- and data-minded and understand how the market is developing.  And – needless to say – you’re a team player who finds it easy to work together with people from many different disciplines and who is prepared to look at things from various perspectives. Your work is always interesting because it involves a lot of experimentation and various clients - and you’re not afraid to fail now and again – in fact, that just makes you even more creative!Mandatory Criteria We are looking for a superstar with the following skills and experience:7+ years’ experience in CRM / Account Management Experience developing data-driven marketing & customer-engagement strategies Proven cross-industry experience in Marketing with an understanding of key business drivers in Retail Commercially astute with strong financial acumen Confident communicator with outstanding written and oral skills A dynamic personality with an ability to effectively engage and influence a variety of stakeholders at all levels You will also have a Tertiary/Post Graduate qualification, ideally in Marketing/Commerce/ Business/Finance or Communications.This really is a fantastic opportunity to work with a leading-edge data driven agency with high profile clients. As a bonus, we’ll throw in a talented and experienced team who are also a lot of fun to work with. If you meet the selection criteria above apply now by forwarding your resume and cover letter. Please contact Sonia Tammaro at sonia@innov8te.com.au if you have questions or apply now.

Name: Senior Engineer - Scala, Spark, Big Data
Description: Do Work that Matters As an experienced data engineer with proven expertise in software development and a passion for providing data-driven solutions, you're ahead of trends and work at the forefront of Big Data technologies.  Which is why we're the perfect fit for you. Here, you'll be part of a team of engineers going above and beyond to improve the standard of digital banking. Using the latest tech to solve our customers' most complex data-centric problems.  Across our end-to-end cycle, it will be your job to support the design and construction of large-scale automated machine learning and data mining practices. Drawing from your ability to integrate diverse sets of data from multiple sources you will design, develop and build industry-leading group data products.  Your experience means you're able to execute state-of-the-art coding practices, driving high quality outcomes to solve core business objectives and minimise risks. Communicating to technical and non-technical stakeholders across the business comes naturally to you.  As someone who's both eager to learn and share knowledge, you're at home in a culture where quality, excellence and openness are championed. Here you'll experience flexibility, great rewards and the opportunity to drive your own career growth.  See yourself in the Team?  To us, data is everything. It's what powers our cutting-edge features and it's the reason we can provide seamless experiences for millions of customers from app to branch.  We're responsible for CommBank's key analytics capabilities and work to create world-leading capabilities for analytics, information management and decisioning. We work across the Group Data Warehouse, Hadoop Big Data Platform, Pega Decisioning, SAS, R, Tableau, Oracle BI, Ab Initio and Data Stage.  We value innovation and encourage our employees to constantly think outside the box and break boundaries to solve complex problems. Our diverse teams are dedicated to learning, sharing knowledge and continuous improvement.  We're always interested in hearing from people who: Have experience working with enterprise-level software applications providing Big Data solutions on Cloudera Hadoop platform. Possess strong skills and background within software engineering, preferably with backend coding in Java, Scala and Python Hold a strong exposure to Ab Initio ETL product suite Demonstrated experience in writing Spark APIs, Hive and Impala queries, along with strong expertise working with Apache Kafka and Apache Cassandra. What skills you will need to be successful? Strong skills in software data engineering and functional programming in Scala, along with backend coding expertise in Java and Python are mandatory. Demonstrated experience in design and development of big data applications on a Hadoop platform, using Spark and ETL based tech stack is highly essential. Commendable skills in building group data products from scratch, by integrating large sets of data from hundreds of internal and external sources would be highly critical. A true passion to learn new skills, along with being diligent to solve data problems with a proactive, risk-mindset. A natural ability to educate, communicate and positively influence large stakeholder groups, and to continuously collaborate with multiple engineering teams is highly essential! What's in it for you? Flexible working programs to promote your mental well-being and work life balance! A brilliant team culture that promotes collaboration and innovation at its core! Fantastic opportunities for career growth If this sounds like you, apply now!  The health and safety of our people, customers and communities is our number one priority. This means that we require all of our employees to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. Please speak to us if you have any questions about this based on your individual circumstances. Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career here is for you. Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive and flexible workplace. One where we're driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.Here, you'll thrive. You'll be supported when faced with challenges, and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We really love working here, and we think you will too.We're determined to make a real difference for Australia's first peoples. We encourage all interested applicants to apply. If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick [link removed] to submit a valid application. We're keen to support you with the next step in your career.

Name: Principal Data Architect
Description: The Company  A big brand with a reputation for leading the way with Big Data is looking for a Principle Architect who is passionate about building cutting edge BI solutions in an Agile environment.  This company is investing significantly into their Big Data capability, with a huge project environment & a push to provide a world-class data processing capability.  With big budgets & long scope, this role will see you working on some of the most exciting projects in the local market.  Hit the Apply for this job button now to get more information!    About the Role  You will be responsible for developing and maintaining information architecture - Implement Data Management, Data Governance and Process Governance frameworks across the organization and to educate the Senior Leadership teams around the benefits.  You will plan with vision and foresight to provide high quality data, to identify and define common information requirements, to design conceptual structures and plans to meet the current and long-term data requirements at an enterprise level.    Technical Skills Needed: Degree qualified in Business management, IT, Computer Systems, software or computer engineering fields or equivalent.10+ years commercial experience with relational & dimensional data modelling, process modelling of large scale data warehousesData-modelling and Information modelling, classification expertise, excellent Enterprise conceptual modelling skillsStrong experience in Reference & Master Data Management, Data Quality, Data GovernanceStrong technical knowledge and experience in RDBMS (Teradata), Big Data (Cloudera), ETL (Informatica Power Centre/BDM), Metadata management and BI analytics toolsData Quality tools - Informatica or equivalentData Security tools - Dynamic Data masking on various technology platforms eg Teradata, Cloudera etcData Modelling using tools like ERWinHadoop / Big Data knowledge and experienceKnowledge of Cloud Platform like GCP, Azure What's in it for you:  You'll be joining a large Agile team with a manager that believes in continual development. This team has excellent staff retention rates and the manager looks for people that want to grow with the company for years to come.  They have a reputation for being a great place to work with excellent career growth opportunities and internal promotions. With an awesome site, they have a gym, onsite restaurants, bars and cafes. They also provide a flexible hybrid work from home arrangements.  This is a company that genuinely promotes flexibility and work/life balance, really valuing their employees.  Hit the Apply for this job button now or contact Adam on 0478026276 to get more information!

Name: Pre-Sales Consultant (APAC, AML, Financial Services, Fraud, Big Data)
Description: Pre-Sales Consultant (APAC, AML, Financial Services, Fraud, Big Data)   My client, a leading multinational firm with a strong presence across the financial services and insurance space, is urgently seeking pre-sales consultants with a remit across APAC to specify and perform demos for maximum customer impact. The successful pre-sales consultant will provide subject matter expertise and demos in pre-sales meetings, respond to RFP’s and RFI’s, and provide business consultancy on high risk pilots, including complex new propositions. You will possess broad and detailed customer domain knowledge, functional and/or technical understanding of the products’ capabilities, as well as my clients’ competitors, and be expected to interact with customer and delivery teams throughout complex project lifecycles to ensure solutions lead to high customer satisfaction.   Key Attributes  APAC regional financial crime (fraud and/or compliance domain) experience. Proven senior stakeholder management capabilities. Demonstrable analytics experience, including the use of open source tools. Public speaking and thought leadership background. Experience of working across multiple time zones and being part of a distributed broader regional team   Desirable Attributes  Experience working in financial crime detection in banking / financial services Experience in AML (anti-money laundering) and Fraud solutions including technical configuration. Strong preference for cross domain operational experience. Graph Based Network Analytics experience is advantageous. Understanding of Big Data technologies.  Joining a dynamic and Agile organisation with a strong presence within the financial services and insurance sector, you will play a pivotal role in driving a number of initiatives simultaneously. You will be nurtured and supported to take your career to the next step in this growing and high-performing team. My client provides a very strong remuneration package and promotes a highly collaborative culture.   Also, great salary, bonus, flexible working. Please forward your CV or contact details for more information and/ or a confidential discussion.   Location: Sydney Salary: Highly Competitive  Start: Immediate

Name: Senior Developer Programmer
Description: About us Billigence Pty Ltd is a specialist in the delivery of market-leading Business Intelligence and CRM solutions. Headquartered in Sydney, Australia and with offices in Prague, London, Frankfurt and Singapore our passion is data and our focus is the delivery of end-to-end solutions via a talented team of skilled professionals. We are partners with leading edge software platforms including Tableau, Alteryx, Collibra, Snowflake and Salesforce. What we are looking for:Senior Developer Programmer to join our team. Essential skills/experience required:  Strong experience as a big data engineer / Developer Programmer working with Hadoop Solid experience working with Spark, Hive etc Programming experience with either Scala, Java or python Excellent written & verbal communication skills    You will be responsible for:  Responsible for the development of Data Analysis tools, analytics reporting and real-time analysis systems. Work closely with the team to develop well architected & tested code that support the business requirements. Recommend technologies to use to take advantage of development capabilities for new and existing projects. Promote and ensure that developed code is well tested and stable. Name: Consultant/Senior Consultant
Description:
IRI is powered by people
We’re a fast paced, tech driven and people focused business. Innovation and entrepreneurism are part of our core DNA. We like to create, and we like to make things happen. Our team is diverse and is made up of Insight and Industry Consulting Analysts, Data Scientists, Product Managers, Solution Architects and Software Engineers. 
As an organisation we’re leading the charge as the specialist provider of data-driven, insight and consulting solutions for FMCG retailers and manufacturers. We power over 500+ leading Australian and New Zealand businesses with a number of services and solutions, including;
          Client consulting services for the grocery, pharmacy, liquor, tobacco and petrol & convenience sectors          Performance data processing and solutions for the FMCG sector          Consumer shopper, loyalty and analytics programs          Software development and cloud-based reporting platforms 
So, why IRI?
We’re progressive, inclusive and people focused. We seek to create a down to earth culture which balances work and home life and enables our team to be the best that it can be. Our people are important to us and we offer a number of fantastic benefits, including; 
         Flexible working both on and off-site         Employee training and continuous development programs         Women in leadership accelerated development opportunities         Up to 5 weeks annual leave and holiday buy back scheme         Paid maternity and paternity leave          Birthday leave          Summer half days          IRI Me Days          Free onsite gym and swimming pool
Key responsibilities:
 Effectively partnering with well-known FMCG manufacturers, you will:
         Define business problems through consultations with clients and provide solutions to their business needs          Solve briefs with actionable recommendations through incorporating analysis from different data sources          Provide and present insights through storytelling          Lead client relationships and proactively develop these relationships to deliver against account plan objectives          Be the responsible for client contract, financials (including invoicing), renewal and growth revenue target          Lead business development activities for targeted accounts 
We're looking for:
         2-5 years’ experience in data analysis/insights or category management, at a market research agency or FMCG manufacturer/retailer          Previous experience working with scan, shopper or customer data          Strong account management and client servicing skills          A creative and curious nature, with the ability to effectively problem solve          Ability to influence and engage senior stakeholders         A confident persona, with the capability to effectively manage client expectations          Strong commercial acumen with the ability to identify business development opportunities 
Interested? We would LOVE to hear from you. Please apply online by submitting your CV. 
Even if you don’t meet all of the above criteria, we encourage you to submit your application.

Description: Nothing stands out on a CV like experience at a high profile, successful business.     Seize your chance to join one of the biggest and best data science teams in Australia as an Early Career Data Scientist!    This top data science team builds commercial analytics and machine learning solutions that have a big impact this company’s performance.    Here’s some of the work the new starters completed last year:  They gained a solid understanding and de-bugging of the code base for one or more production machine learning models and data pipelines built with Python, SQL, Apache Spark and deployed on Google Cloud Platform. They assisted a senior data scientist to scale a model using kubernetes or kubeflow – making it easier to move into production and scale millions of customers records. Sponsorship is not available. You can be based anywhere in Australia, but long-term, Sydney is the head office. To relocate there would be at your expense. Heavy preference will be given to good commercial experience with data science using real customer data for big companies or start-ups  Interest in these roles will be immense. Set yourself apart by writing a cover letter that demonstrates your experience with customer data or large data sets, and apply ASAP!

ongoing professional development and free technical certification 
highly competitive remuneration and bonuses. 

If the above sounds like the right opportunity to further your career, apply via the link below or get in touch with chirag.bhojani@macquarie.com [link removed] for more information. 
About the Corporate Operations Group
The Corporate Operations Group brings together specialist support services in Digital Transformation & Data, Technology, Operations, Human Resources, Business Services, Business Improvement & Strategy, and the Macquarie Group Foundation. We deliver service excellence to ensure Macquarie is open for business, deliver on transformational change, invest in our people and have deep relationships with our customers.
Our commitment to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion 
The diversity of our people is one of our greatest strengths. Name: Senior Consultant Engineer
Description:
Opportunity for a Senior Consultant Engineer
Be part of an innovative and collaborative team culture
At NAB, we are committed to working flexibly

About the role
As a Senior Consultant Engineer, you will be part of the Foundational Platform Engineering team in Enterprise Data and Analytics that are building NABs strategic data lakehouse, and will be responsible for the design, development and deployment of capability aligned with the business roadmap and driving efficiencies that enhance availability, performance and stability of strategic data services.
What you’ll be doing
As an experienced Senior Consultant Engineer and an expert in the use of specific technologies and the software development discipline, you will be the ‘go to’ person to help plan, design, deliver and support features that deliver customer value and mature our service capabilities.  You will have broad experience in analysis, design, development, documentation, testing and support responsibilities and be a thought leader in driving best practices in the team.
What you’ll bring

Extensive demonstrated experience across DevOps, Cloud and Data Engineering
Experience designing and supporting API enabled cloud applications
Prior experience with CDC tools (HVR experience highly regarded) and Databricks
Technical skills in software delivery such as CI/CD, Automated Deployments, Automated Testing, Build Servers, Software / Source Code Configuration Management.
Solid experience in large scale data transformation, design and solution delivery experience of high-quality data processing pipelines and solutions in a professional services environment.
Experience in data lake or warehouse integrity and reconciliation; tracking and reconciling data movement and transformation.
Expertise in designing and building maintainable and scalable end to end big data solutions in HDFS, Kafka, Apache Spark, Hive, EMR, Airflow and Python or other similar tools.
Extensive knowledge of core AWS data services such as: S3, RDS, Redshift, Glue, Athena, DynamoDB, EMR, Kinesis, Kinesis Firehouse.
Ability to provide technical mentoring and guidance to less experienced members of the development team
Execute and drive hands-on design, to maximise and implement best practice CI/CD across the team.
Work with delivery teams to achieve success through the adoption of CI/CD and DevOps practices, processes and tooling.

What we can offer
From education and volunteer leave to learning benefits and banking discounts, we offer access to a wide range of employee benefits. You can learn more about these at http://www.nab.com.au/about-us/careers/working-at-nab/benefits 
We embrace diversity of thought, style and working arrangement to ensure our workforce is representative of the community that we service. 
Have a chat to us about how our support of workplace flexibility can work for you. 
NAB, invested in you
At NAB, we believe success comes from our people. We're committed to supporting your talent and skills through your career, as you help us build a culture that affects change for our customers - and for the community too.
To be eligible to apply, you must have Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency status.

Name: Data Scientist
Description: About the Role As a key member of the Data Science Chapter, you will help lead, ideate, develop, build, deploy and drive adoption of data science within the organisation. You will be joining a team with a fantastic culture, where an innovative and entrepreneurial mindset is openly celebrated and supported. Working with stakeholders across Optus Consumer, in both Agile and non-Agile environments, you will take a central role in supporting the Associate Director of Data Science to establish a data driven culture with a focus on driving the adoption of data science, ensuring that the analytical assets produced are robust, scalable and add value. You will work with senior leaders across the organisation, to lead & drive the adoption of data science as well as create an understanding of how data science can best be utilised in a marketing context. More specifically, as a Data Scientist, you will:  Deliver tangible analytical assets, utilising appropriate advanced analytical techniques and productionise these into the modelling pipeline (which includes, but not limited to, propensity modelling, machine learning, mathematical optimisation) Possess the ability to work with large amounts of information and see the ‘bigger picture', conduct data discovery, apply basic, complex and/or data science techniques for automation using a hypothesis driven approach Support the development and execution of the Data Science roadmap across Optus Consumer Collaborate with users and stakeholders to develop, test and document new ways to help provide data driven outcomes to the business Support the ongoing implementation of cutting-edge machine learning solutions and best practice Data Science within the Chapter and across the Optus Analytics Communities to help community members build robust analytical solutions  About YouYou will have strong communication skills and agile thinking mindset to settle into a new environment quickly and achieve results quickly. You enjoy being hands-on and are excited to apply your data science knowledge to uncovering insights hidden in vast amounts of data, wrangling & engineering that information and developing meaningful analytical assets that add value to the organisation. You thrive on being empowered with the autonomy to perform your role, whilst leveraging the support of the Chapter and collaborating with peers and stakeholders. You are proactive, flexible, adaptable to change, enjoy dynamic environments and thrive on the challenge of driving adoption. Our values Customer Focus, Challenger Spirit, Teamwork, Integrity and Personal excellence will resonate with you deeply and you will enjoy being part of iconic Australian company that prides itself on innovation and putting the customer at the centre of everything. Other skills and experience include:  Tertiary qualifications in a STEM or business discipline Experience in building large scale, end-to-end machine learning systems using a combination of big data tools and programming languages like R, Spark/Scala, Java and Python (PySpark preferred) and workflow management and code repositories such as Github/Bitbucket, JIRA Sharepoint & Confluence Sound communication and influencing skills with stakeholders from a range of backgrounds with varying levels of technical competency Inquisitive nature - a desire to go beneath the surface of a problem, find the questions at its heart, and distil them into a very clear set of hypotheses that can be tested Optus is a place where we let you do you.  We offer all kinds of benefits, such as: Work collaboratively in an open, Agile environment with flexible working hours and location; Discounts with over 400 companies Australia wide (Technology, Retail, Home, Fashion and more!); Mobile & Broadband staff discounts; Participate in a unique campus environment where you can interact, learn, develop new relationships and have new experiences. Onsite facilities at Macquarie Park such as a Gym, GP, Mini-mart and cafes; Training, Mentoring and further learning opportunities and subsidised staff bus service between campus and Epping and campus and campus and Wynyard !

Name: IT Systems Administrator

Mac and Linux machines)Management of virtual Windows Servers for Domain Controllers, Active Directory, Group Policy, DHCP, File Servers (DFSR) and DNSManagement of data backup applications and offsite backup systemsManagement of networking and security across Software Firewalls, Ubiquiti Unifi and Windows systemsManagement of software licensing servers across paid engineering software used in-houseManagement of a 3CX VOIP systemDocumentation of all systemsMaintenance of physical host Linux machines as development and production VM host serversMaintenance of Linux based web server VM's for in-house proxy systems and development environmentsThis is a challenging and diverse role, however, you will be provided with all training required to undertake the role as well as the freedom to research and explore as needed to get the job done.Pre-requisites you should bringWe'd like our IT Systems Administrator to possess the following:At least Diploma in Information Technology Systems Administration, or equivalent certificatesExperience working with Windows OS and management of Domain Controllers, Active Directory, Group Policy and associated servicesExperience with Name: Principal Machine Learning Engineering
Description:
Opportunity for Principal Machine Learning Engineer 
Deep technical and leadership experience is essential
Be recognised as an expert, empowered to deliver and succeed

About the Role:
As a Principal Machine Learning Engineer, you will be part of an awesome team that plays a crucial role in transforming the data and analytics landscape as well as changing how we use our data to help our customers and business. You will work closely with scrum masters, asset designers and data consulting teams to determine platform requirements and priorities.
You will manage a team in an agile environment, involving stand-ups, retros, planning, showcases whilst providing technical guidance and coaching to the members of the team. You will build tools and libraries to enable efficient data transport, profiling and transformation.
What you'll be doing  
Your key accountabilities will include but not be limited to:

Building tools and libraries to enable efficient data transport, profiling, and transformation
Ensure NABs engineering and security standards are adhered to
Resolve technical barriers and roadblocks impacting delivery teams
Track delivery outcomes against key performance indicators and provide reporting to manager of analytics & reporting
Work with analysts and data scientists on bespoke problems requiring engineering support
Define the technical direction for a cloud based advanced analytics platform 
Promote AWS and cloud best practices to maximize compute performance while minimizing infrastructure costs
Design and develop an automated data pipeline including integrity
Manage and run an enterprise level DevOps team
Work with different data types e.g. streaming, real-time, file based, RDMS, unstructured data, etc. 
Work on software and data engineering for bespoke projects

What you'll bring  
To succeed in this role, you will bring extensive leadership experience as either a manager or technical lead coupled with unwavering drive and motivation to succeed in fast paced, at times ambiguous and complex environment and have:

Demonstrated experience managing analytical or data focused projects / teams.
Experience of reporting and analytics, and/or experience working with analysts and data scientists. 
Demonstrated experience using productivity and collaboration tools such as JIRA and confluence in a software delivery environment
Experience with Data ingestion technologies and capturing meta-data and data lineage
Understanding of how to build modern data pipelines
Familiarity with data orchestration frameworks such as Airflow
Knowledge of big data processing tools such as Spark and Scala
Familiarity with AWS services and/or other Cloud vendors
Experience with shell scripting
Exposure to DevOps and Agile
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, both oral and written 
Relevant tertiary qualification in a related discipline

Name: Graduate Professionals - National Opportunities
Description: Why join ARRB: Where else will you make a meaningful impact on the lives of 25 million Australians per day and do your bit towards making the country sustainable?    ARRB is a supportive, culturally diverse and vibrant organisation which daily provides exciting opportunities for our teams to do great things, to tackle the big transport and infrastructure questions, and to see these solutions being practically applied.     If our values of Collaboration, Transformation, Integrity and Energy & Passion strike a chord with you, then join us and make your mark! This role offers passionate, proactive, talented and energetic professionals the opportunity to make a significant contribution to the sustainability of Australia’s future mobility system!    ARRB is committed to train young professionals who wants to establish their careers within the transportation infrastructure arena to become the next generation thinkers, thought-leaders and game-changers.  The aim of our experts is to provide mentorship, support and some challenges to help you thrive in your career to stand tall in years to come and be the expert within your chosen field.    About the role and you: We are looking for applicants who can demonstrate their interest/field of study in the below areas within the transportation industry including roads, rail, ports and airports.     We have graduate opportunities for applicants interested in the below fields:    Data Analytics (big data analysis, programming skills / data dashboards / interactive maps / GIS / spatial analysis) Mobility Futures (Artificial Intelligence, next generation transport systems, future fuels, Intelligent Transport Systems) Environmental Management - sustainability, transport and environmental economics, Materials Engineering – traditional road, bridge and rail building materials as well as recycled materials Infrastructure Design – methods and materials for safer, resilient and value-for money infrastructure, smart infrastructure Asset Management – infrastructure condition assessments, investment programming for better mobility outcomes, data technologies for infrastructure assessment Network and Traffic Management – modelling and prediction of capacity and demand, micro-mobility, active travel   Successful applicants will work on a wide range of research, advisory and data-related projects designed to deliver quality and best practice outcomes for our clients with guidance from our experts.       The successful candidates will have the following skills:  Recent Engineering/Science graduates who received their qualifications within the last 5 years Ability to confidently interact within a team made up of a diverse group of people located across Australia Confident communication skills (both verbal and written) Motivated to work and learn with excellent time management skills Excellent attention to detail and ability to solve problems creatively and practically Keen interest in research, creating new knowledge and practical solutions    What we offer:  At ARRB, we are proud of our thriving workforce.  We continue to attract the leading minds within the transportation infrastructure and related research arena.  We truly celebrate our culturally and gender diverse work environment.    We provide an exciting, dynamic and collaborative workplace with challenging roles, where your skills, knowledge and experience will be recognised and respected, including:  Opportunities to work with nationally recognised experts, who offer brilliant mentorship and support Opportunities to contribute to high-profile and interesting projects which make a difference to the community Healthy work-life balance, with flexible arrangements Access to 6 weeks of paid parental leave, extra 2 days of paid holiday leave in December Strong support for career development and further study, including an explicit step-by-step guide for progressing in the organisation and a range of professional development options A well-established social club, with regular socialising events, competitions, quiz events and tournaments We embrace diversity - highlighting a multidisciplinary workforce from all over the world within all of our offices across Australia Contemporary and modern work campuses  To be considered:  Applicants must be Australian Citizens / Permanent Resident of Australia who currently reside in Australia.  Applicants on visas cannot be considered for these vacancies. Name: Software Engineer
Description: Servian, is an award-winning, regional and global tech consultancy with a rich heritage in Data, DevOps, Digital and Cloud. We embrace innovation, change, and the positive impact it has on us and our clients. All roles at Servian involve personal and technical development pathways which aim to facilitate your career growth. We aim to build an employee experience where you will grow more with us, not be drowned out by the loudest voice, and hence we strive to set you up for a career that will have a greater impact.Our consultants are natural problem solvers - they are curious, ambitious and experts in their fields.  You will have the opportunity to collaborate and learn from them. You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, working with our clients to understand their needs and to help shape the engagements that allow Servian to provide services that will meet those needs. If you have a passion for learning new technologies, want to be tech agnostic, and work with like-minded technologists, Servian is the place to grow your career and have fun in the process!Our focus:Cloud Technology - Cloud Services (AWS, Azure, GCP), Snowflake, HashiCorpData & Analytics - BI/DWH, Big Data Analytics, Data Engineering and Advanced AnalyticsDigital - Full stack Development, UI/UX Design, Mobile DevelopmentCustomer Engagement - Marketing Campaigns, Campaign Analysis, Customer InsightsArtificial Intelligence - Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Deep LearningCyber Security - DevSecOps, Penetration Testing, Multi-Cloud Security, Security Posture AnalysisWhat are we looking for?Developed skills with a range of programming languages and libraries (Typescript, NodeJS, etc.)Experience working in cloud environments (AWS, Azure, GCP)Consultative mindset with strong stakeholder management and communication skillsExpertise in the design, development and delivery of data or automation solutionsExperience in CI/CD, TDD and secure coding practicesExperience integrating web-based applications with backend API servicesKnowledge of common data structures and algorithmic solutionsPassion for teaching, coaching or mentoring team membersLove working in an Agile environmentWhy join Servian?Work on a wide range of interesting projects, using a variety of emerging technologies. This is a chance to work alongside a collaborative and passionate like-minded team in an environment that fosters proactive career development through structured learning and development, and multiple avenues for growth.Alongside the above, we also provide employees with life and salary insurance, progressive parental leave policy, and a sociable workplace that truly values its diversity. To make it a fun place you want to be involved in, we have a range of consultant-led initiatives to get everyone excited, which include social and tech clubs (gaming, IoT, chatbots, wellbeing, etc.), meetups, and cloud vendor hackathons.If you’re looking for the opportunity to step up into a leadership position and are excited by the thought of getting your hands dirty with the latest tech-stacks/methodologies, then look no further... APPLY NOW!

Name: Lead Solution Architect – Integrated Risk Management – GRC domain
Description:
Join our Risk Technology team as an Experienced/Senior Technology Leader in the Compliance and Operational Risk Management domain, and be responsible for delivering an enterprise-wide technology and data led transformation to create an integrated risk detection capability for both internal and external threats.
Join our team as the Lead Solution Architect to support a wide-scale transformation of our enterprise risk management capability.
In this role, you will be you will be responsible for the vision and strategy of integrated risk management for the enterprise through automation and uplift of OpenPages or similar GRC tooling and other risk management capabilities, powering the enterprise to enhance its control assessment, monitoring and detection offering across key risk events.
You will be part of a globally distributed team, with high visibility throughout the organisation and will involve in technology sourcing strategy requiring interaction with the senior management levels. You will have a broad and deep understanding of technology strategy and architecture and delivery roadmap.
Your ability to lead, communicate effectively, influence senior management and contribute to cross-functional teams across the business will be vital in this role. Other key attributes that will aid in your success include:• applied experience in building technology and data fabric for the enterprise• excellent stakeholder engagement skills, including experience working with C-level management and other business leaders on complex programs• working knowledge of technology capabilities for operational risk monitoring, and understanding or applied experience in machine learning based risk management• applied experience with enterprise data strategies and tools, including big data, cloud technology, enterprise data models, analytics, BI• application of machine learning to solve business challenges or create new opportunities• evangelisation of data analytics and data democratisation• ability to realise synergies and delivery efficiency through digitailsation across enterprise solutions• experience with vendor sourcing and market assessment of next-best product• excellent written and verbal communication skills with both technical and non-technical stakeholder• experience in Financial Services will be highly regarded.
We need you to:• demonstrated experience as a Lead or Enterprise Solution Architect• develop and deliver on the strategic risk management solutions and its future roadmap • develop a governance and control framework to assure the integrity, completeness and accuracy of data collected or created by the Strategic Data Platform and Tools• provide input on the formulation of the Enterprise Technology team priorities in leadership forums• experience in iterative development
If this role sounds like the right opportunity to further your career, please apply via the link or reach out to chirag.bhojani@macquarie.com for more information.
The Corporate Operations Group brings together specialist support services in Digital Transformation & Data, Technology, Market Operations, Human Resources, Business Services, Business Improvement & Strategy, Brand & Marketing and the Macquarie Group Foundation.
Find out more about Macquarie careers at www.macquarie.com/careers [link removed]
Macquarie understands the importance of diversity and inclusion - our long history of success has come from being different. At Macquarie we value the innovation and creativity that diversity of thought brings. The one thing we all have in common is our focus on high performance. If you're capable, motivated and can deliver, we want you on our team.
We recognise that flexibility comes in a variety of forms. Talk to us about what flexibility you need.

Name: Data Modeller
Description: Our Client is a large Financial Services organisation based in Sydney, seeking the services of a seasoned Data Modeller to increase capability across a range of data projects within the enterprise risk management group. These projects are required to satisfy APRA regulations.   You will be skilled in designing data models for extensibility, scalability, simplicity, consistency, and integrity, reducing data redundancy and improving data integration.   This level of task will require a consultant with solid experience in data modelling & analysis, data migration strategy and data alignment across multiple applications, data governance, heterogeneous data identification, data masking/transformation and data mining activities.   The role will focus on:    Defining key strategies and technologies needed to build and manage a modern data architecture Defining standard labels and notations to use across the organisation, in line with data governance and advisory group taxonomies Develop and maintain relational, hierarchical and dimensional data models (conceptual, logical, physical and canonical) and definitions that align with business rules, processes and analytics requirements.    We don't require the finished article with ALL skills/ standards to apply; We would like to see a T-shape skillset which covers some of the following:    Demonstrable experience working on complex end-to-end enterprise data-focused initiatives Strong experience in Data Architecture & Design Experience working in Financial Services is preferred Experience working with standard data models like FpML, FIXML Strong stakeholder management skills Hands-on expertise in big data technologies. Experience in Cloudera a plus Strong hands-on experience doing data analysis using different data formats - XML, JSON & CSV… etc Experience with structured & unstructured data; including e-communications, voice etc Strong Experience in AWS Data Storage & Services  Experience in presentations layer analytics platforms like Power BI, Tableau, Alteryx Strong understanding of database concepts such as referential integrity and data alignment, table partitions, data import-export mechanisms, data transfer and transformation mechanisms, data encryption/decryption & cleansing/harmonisation Solid understanding of table structures, schema, users and grants Knowle in designing optimised solutions to process TBs of data. Knowledge of query optimisation techniques Knowledge of Python, R, Scala or JAVA is a plus (code reviews)    Please apply now if you have an appetite for a role of this magnitude. You can express your interest using any of the below channels:   Click: apply now Mobile: 0400 220 167  Email: tim@excelsisdeo.com.au Alternatively, please book a 15-minute consultation: https://calendly.com/timothyexcelsisdeo/office-hours

Name: Automation Engineering Lead
Description: The OpportunityWe are looking for an Automation Engineering Lead to join our growing project Banksia team at Seqirus for the construction of our state-of-the-art Influenza cell-culture (FCC) manufacturing facility in Tullamarine (Victoria, Australia). Expected to be completed in 2026, this facility will be the only cell-based influenza vaccine manufacturing facility in the Southern Hemisphere and will also produce unique products important to Australia's public health needs such as snake and spider antivenoms. The RoleBased at our Tullamarine facility, and internally referred to as the Execution Systems Lead, this Full-time Permanent role owns the Execution Systems strategy and master plan for a recipe driven, fully integrated, and validated manufacturing facility across the Tullamarine site.You will provide strong leadership to ensure adherence globally as well as having technical and supervisory experience implementing manufacturing execution and process automation systems, including but not limited to, process control systems (PCS), manufacturing execution systems (MES), manufacturing data systems (historians, analytics), and PLCs. Reporting to the Regional Head of Executions Systems, you will:Collaborate in the development and implementation of Execution System strategies and roadmap to design and implement the ES scope aligned with the global and standardised approach across the CSL networkAccountable for System ownership and compliance of MES, PCS, PLC, Enterprise system interfaces, Data Historian, Building Management and Environmental Monitoring SystemsOversight & review of contractors/integrators work during design, construction, commissioning, and validationManages the Execution Systems project scoping and site level OPEX & CAPEX budgets in collaboration with the Project Delivery group as applicableFoster a culture of innovation and big data by directly overseeing the execution of proof of concepts, pilots, and projects based on leading edge technologyAdhere to the Global Standards & Governance for Execution Systems to enable consistent implementation & operability across CSL sites and drive continuous improvement opportunitiesImplement and maintain S95/S88 compliant systems for activities associated with batch production, testing and release including master process data, recipe libraries, recipe management, process control and data historianActs as the overall SME/POC for the global value stream owner, responsible for coordination of global alignment initiatives, changes, and process support for the assigned value streamLead site team of engineers responsible for the technical development, implementation and operational support Skills and Experience10+ years' practical leadership experience in pharmaceutical industry including direct management experience in Manufacturing, Engineering or Execution Systems/Automation; 5 years or more working experience in Execution Systems/Automation design and supportSpecific experience in process automation, MES and batch manufacturing industry standards (ISA S88 &S95).Direct experience designing, building, deploying and supporting automation and execution systems in a regulated large-scale process-based manufacturing environment.Experience in running site-based shop floor systems in a globally distributed footprint is highly desirable.Demonstrated ability to influence at all organisational levels through clear, concise and impactful verbal and written communication skills.Ability to build, mentor and grow a high performing and cohesive team.Experience in Process Excellence methodology is desirable, but not requiredBachelor of Science in an Engineering or other Science discipline/Masters preferred, Computer Science, or Management Information Systems. How to applyIf this sounds like you and you are looking to further develop your skills on this Melbourne Greenfield Project, apply now! Please include a Cover Letter and CV in your application. Applications open 23 June 2022 and close on 23 July 2022.

Name: Enterprise Solution Architect – Financial Crime Risk Domain
Description:
Join our Risk Technology team as an Experienced/Senior Technology Leader in the Trading Surveillance and Financial Crime Risk area, and be responsible for delivering an enterprise-wide technology and data led transformation to create an integrated risk detection capability for both internal and external threats. 

In this role, you will be operating as a senior Technology Leader responsible for the vision and strategy of Macquarie’s Surveillance and Automated monitoring platform and advanced data analytics capability, powering the enterprise to enhance its detection offering across key risk events, leveraging deep analytics AI/Machine Learning techniques. 


You will be part of a globally distributed team, with high visibility throughout the organisation and will involve in technology sourcing strategy requiring interaction with the senior management levels. applied experience in building technology and data fabric for the enterprise 


excellent stakeholder engagement skills, including experience working with C-level management and other business leaders on complex programs 


working knowledge of technology capabilities for financial risk monitoring, and understanding or applied experience in machine learning based risk management 


applied experience with enterprise data strategies and tools, including big data, cloud technology, enterprise data models, analytics, BI 


application of machine learning to solve business challenges or create new opportunities 


evangelisation of data analytics and data democratisation 


ability to realise synergies and delivery efficiency through digitailsation across enterprise solutions 


experience with vendor sourcing and market assessment of next-best product

experience in iterative development

Name: Senior Data Engineer
Description: About us  Transport for NSW is the lead agency of the NSW Transport cluster. Our role is to lead the development of a safe, efficient, integrated transport system that keeps people and goods moving, connects communities and shapes the future of our cities, centres and regions. We work with several government agencies to coordinate road, rail, bus and maritime services, always keeping the safety and comfort of our customers at the heart of what we do. About AAI at TfNSW TfNSW's Advanced Analytics and Insights group design sustainable solutions that will effectively address the uncovered opportunities through business analytics and we deliver a solution that is governed by enterprise standards, with the potential to evolve in line with your business needs. AAI leads data, analytics and insights across Transport to deliver impactful solutions through analytics, data and insights. Our branch supports strategic business decision making for a better customer future. Along with the business engagement team, backed by a team of highly specialised architects, analysts, developers and co-ordinators can help you find the right data solution to meet your business requirements. The opportunity  We have a new opportunity for a Senior Data Engineer, temporary full time role upto 31st March 2024 within Advanced Analystics and Insights division. This role has the responsibility for the provision of all maintenance tasks, modifications, improvements, cleansing, and manipulation of data from across the entire Transport Cluster. Your role will include: Provide technical leadership and implement of a variety of data ingestion processes, technologies and systems which underpin our branch and various data teams across the cluster with the primary focus of driving data democratisation for the delivery of insights. Ensure that data governance processes are implemented at each point of the data management lifecycle and are a key consideration of any implementation that is auditable to a shared reference specification. Design and lead the automation of existing business logic and business processes surrounding data services with a focus on optimising delivery and reliability and extracting business value from data using the latest in cloud technologies with a special focus on near-real-time pipelines Maintain strong stakeholder relationships at various levels, both internally and externally by tailoring consultative services and recommendations to drive alignment and capability uplift of data teams across the Transport Cluster. Monitor compliance with cybersecurity recommendations and advisories while taking the lead in implementing and demonstrating best practices in terms of protecting our data as key assets of the organisation. Lead the identification, design, and implementation of internal process improvements: automating manual processes, streamlining data delivery and re-designing infrastructure for greater scalability and elegance. Identify, analyse and communicate potential opportunities for Business Intelligence, Analytics and Data Science teams to extract new business value to drive business decisions. Design and develop data tools and scripts for Analytics, Business Intelligence and Data Science teams to assist in building highly optimised products ready for a scalable production environments. Lead consultation at an enterprise level to determine the most appropriate and engaging solutions to deliver shared outcomes for federated analytics teams across the Transport Cluster.  For more information please view a copy of the role description. About you We are looking for a hands-on Senior Data Engineer with extensive experience in AWS ‘Big Data' suite, data modelling, data mining, segmentation techniques, a guru in SQL database design and has worked with large, complex data sets. You are a creative and adventurous thinker who enjoys experimenting with new techniques and is looking for a career-building opportunity to showcase your engineering skills. You are also a collaborative team member who enjoys brainstorming, has strong communication skills and is disciplined and organised. Scripting knowledge in Python or similar, backend application development, DBA administration including configuration and knowledge or experience in data governance will be highly regarded. Salary and Benefits The salary for this position is TfNSW Grade 9 ($138,670.00 - $155,309.00) per annum plus superannuation and leave loading.   For more information on Employee Benefits at TfNSW please click here.  How to apply To apply for this position, please answer all questions within the online application process and submit a resume.   Applications Close: 11.59 PM Sunday, 3rd July 2022  We are the community we serveWe are committed to being an inclusive, diverse and flexible workplace where differences are valued. We welcome people of all backgrounds, experience and abilities.We enable our people to work in ways that work for them and their teams. Working virtually and from different locations including regional locations, staggering work hours and job sharing are just some of the ways our people can work flexibly.Please contact the Talent Specialist below if you require any adjustments to be made to how you interact with us throughout the recruitment process or would like to discuss flexible work options. For any enquiries, please email Srivatsa Lakshmi Narayana at Srivatsa.Lakshminarayana@transport.nsw.gov.au Apply today to register your interest! Find out more about Transport for NSW at https://www.transport.nsw.gov.au/about-us

You will work alongside a talented team of consultants who all share your passion in building great solutions and learning new skills.What are we looking for?Developed skills with a range of programming languages and librariesMust have - ReactOptional (JavaScript, GraphQL, Java, Angular, Vue, Golang, .NET Core, NodeJS, etc.) Microservices, Docker, Kubernetes, Cloud Services, etc.Extensive experience working in cloud environments (AWS, Azure, GCP)Consultative mindset with strong stakeholder management and communication skillsExpertise in the design, development and delivery of data or automation solutionsExperience in CI/CD, TDD and secure coding practicesExperience integrating web-based applications with backend API servicesKnowledge of common data structures and algorithmic solutionsPassion for teaching, coaching or mentoring team membersLove working in an Agile environmentWho are you?Curious and eager to learn: you are a curious individual who is eager to develop their skills and progress their career at every opportunity in a consulting environment.Team player: you thrive as a part of high performing teams and love sharing your knowledge with your peers and clients. We win together.Proactive: you seize opportunities when you see them. Every day at Servian presents broad opportunities for personal, professional and business growth.Passionate: you are excited by tech. Our team constantly innovate and implement new technologies and methodologies for themselves, our vendors and our clients.Why join Servian?Work on a wide range of interesting projects, using a variety of emerging technologies.A chance to work alongside a collaborative and passionate like-minded team.Consultant-led events including Social clubs, Tech clubs (IoT, Chatbots, etc.), Gaming events, MeetUps, and Cloud vendor Hackathons.Proactive career development through structured learning and development, multiple avenues for growth and an innovative reward and recognition structure.Alongside the above, we also provide employees with life and salary insurance, progressive parental leave policy, and a sociable workplace that truly values its diversity.What’s Next?If this role sounds of interest, or you would like to hear about other exciting opportunities get in touch with the Servian Talent Acquisition Team.

Name: Senior Developer
Description: Hi, we’re Idoba – nice to meet you!So who are we?Idoba is an innovation ecosystem that brings together the deep industry experience and complementary capabilities of a bunch of proudly West Australian companies who have a shared passion to co-create a better future for the mining industry (and beyond!). By uniting these technology and consulting businesses together, we have capabilities that span technology and innovation, business improvement, data science, analytics and data insights, as well as specialist mine planning and mining technical expertise.We’ve united our complementary capabilities across operational expertise, technology offerings, and digital enablement to partner with our clients on solving gnarly problems and liberating value. Our team members are clever, curious and quirky people who work flexibly between our vibrant open-plan Perth CBD office and from home.About you and what you can bringYou’re someone who's curious about solving problems for people, and create solutions that improve the life of the user. You enjoy working in a team to solve problems by being able to quickly define and scope out solutions by working in an agile environment. More formally, you will need a very strong background in web development and database programming as well as:5+ years hands-on professional experience as Senior DeveloperAWS CertifiedExperience with: Big dataDev-opsAzureC#PythonData-ManagementDAMASome awareness of Cyber SecurityAbout the role This is an opportunity to apply your skills along different parts of the product lifecycle, from experimentation to MVP and beyond, depending on where your purpose takes you. As a Developer, you will be responsible for building a wide range of custom-built applications, to help develop interfaces to our engines. This is a challenging and highly technical role working on a variety of complex problems.   We work in a team and collaborative environment, applying the principles of Agile. You will work closely with our Lead Developer for meeting operational goals, as well as offshore teams (solution modelling and solving, client satisfaction and billability)Next steps If you are thinking about a new opportunity, then please apply via the link and I will be in touch. For any questions or a confidential discussion regarding the role please contact me directly on laura.ashe@sandpitinnovation.com

Name: Data Engineering & Platforms Manager | ABC’s Audiences Team
Description:
About the ABC
The ABC is the nation's most trusted and independent source of Australian conversations, culture, and stories. With over 4,000 employees from diverse backgrounds across over 50 locations around Australia and overseas, we are proud to create, curate and deliver high-quality content that informs, educates and entertains Australian communities.
About the Role
Lead ABC's Audiences Platforms and Data Engineering team, to drive significant changes in strategic business decisions, by automating, optimising, innovating and aligning audience data across the ABC to support the achievement of Audiences’ objectives.
Key Accountabilities

Lead, manage and mentor the Audience Data Engineering and Platform team to achieve a shared understanding and commitment to team objectives, and to build and maintain a collaborative and high-performance culture.
Lead the development of data platforms, which underpin Audience Data and Insights capability and act as the key decision maker on data and platform architecture.
Translate business requirements into technical specifications through synthesis of facts, detailed analysis, interpretation and evaluation of relevant data to deliver the appropriate outcomes.
Data the Data visualization (i.e., Power BI) platforms and Data Science capability using ABC’s modern cloud-based data platforms, including AWS and GCP and Agile ETL processes.
Collaborate with key stakeholders and third-party data providers to effectively interrogate, understand, and articulate business requirements to ensure deliverables meet expectations.
Write senior business cases and develop Proof of Concepts to demonstrate potential outcomes at a very high level.
Provide high-level technical leadership and strategic advice on highly complex/specialist projects to ensure achievement of divisional milestones and objectives.
Provide expert advice and drive the creation of a single view of audience across the ABC to support the development of PAX (Personalised Audience Experience) and APAX (Audiences’ solution to a 360-customer view)

About You; 

Demonstrated in-depth knowledge of data warehousing architecture and enterprise data platforms both on-premises and multi-cloud services such as AWS S3 and Redshift, Advanced Python, R, MS SQL Serversand Google Analytics and Big-Query.
Demonstrated significant experience implementing an industry standard for a large organisation, including processes to extract, transform and load data from different types of platforms and Gateways, develop reporting and roll out of BI tools to users (Airflow Workflow Management Platform, Application Programming Interfaces and SDK integrations).
Demonstrated high proficiency in data solutioning and products available in the market and experience working with big data solutions such as Amazon Web Services, Redshift Spectrum, Athena, Google Analytical Suites, Hadoop, Hive and MapReduce.
Significant experience in the leadership and development of teams.
Highly developed planning, organisational and project management skills, with high level attention to detail and ability to work effectively under pressure to meet deadlines.
Highly developed relationship management and communication skills, with experience in negotiating, influencing and liaising with a diverse group of internal and external stakeholders to achieve strategic outcomes.
Highly developed analytical and problem-solving skills with an aptitude for strategic thinking to inspire innovation.

For further information on this position please contact Jamie Nedved, Digital Talent Acquisition Lead via email nedved.jamie@abc.net.au  
We respectfully request that Recruitment Agencies do not submit applications for this position.
In line with our focus on diversity, applications are strongly encouraged from Indigenous Australians, people from a range of cultural and linguistic backgrounds, people with disability and LGBTIQA+ individuals. The ABC also aims to achieve a gender-balanced workforce.
For more information on inclusive employee networks within the ABC please refer to Life Page on ABC LinkedIn. 
For more information on working at the ABC visit abc.net.au/careers

Name: Senior Product Analytics Analyst - Building AI/ML Products
Description: This role sits within Data Products among data scientists and engineers but will also work closely with the marketing squads in charge of personalisation products. You will be exposed to production and POC big data environments, advanced analytics and ML / AI personalisation projects, with training and exposure to many of the latest cutting-edge tools in the data.Key activities  Provide analysis and ongoing commentary on campaign performance driving personalisation Perform ad hoc analysis using SQL and other tools of your choice, and present findings to broad range of audience Build self-service reporting tools as appropriate. Propose opportunities for conducting A/B tests, and lead the implementation of testing plans Proactively share knowledge with other analysts and use Chapter time to keep learning new analytical techniques. Manage stakeholder relationships in marketing and ecommerce.  Skills required:  Is it essential that you have been an Analyst or a Senior Analyst in a solid commercial environment for a few years. Ideally you have some familiarity with Data Science concepts Extensive experience working in a large, complex customer analytics environment, ideally with some exposure to product analytics or marketing data and insights Good to have exposure to Big Query and Google Cloud Platform Advanced SQL for extracting, querying and relational databases are essential (ideally Teradata, but will consider other data warehouses) Strong visualisation skills are essential (Ideally Tableau) Statistical modelling with R or Python are highly regarded Exposure to cloud platforms is highly regarded (google could platform / GCP, AWS or Azure Preferred knowledge of statistical modelling tools and techniques e.g. segmentation, propensity models Tertiary degree in Mathematics, Marketing, Statistics, Computing or related analytical field Strong influencing skills with ability to effectively liaise at all levels of the business

Name: Business Intelligence Developer (Power Platform, Analytics)
Description: Servian, is an award-winning, regional and global tech consultancy with a rich heritage in Data, DevOps, Digital and Cloud. We embrace innovation, change, and the positive impact it has on us and our clients. All roles at Servian involve personal and technical development pathways which aim to facilitate your career growth. We aim to build an employee experience where you will grow more with us, not be drowned out by the loudest voice, and hence we strive to set you up for a career that will have a greater impact. Our consultants are natural problem solvers - they are curious, ambitious and experts in their fields.  You will have the opportunity to collaborate and learn from them. You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, working with our clients to understand their needs and to help shape the engagements that allow Servian to provide services that will meet those needs.  If you have a passion for learning new technologies, want to be tech agnostic, and work with like-minded technologists, Servian is the place to grow your career and have fun in the process! Our focus:  Cloud & Technology - Cloud Services (AWS, Azure, GCP), Snowflake, HashiCorp Data & Analytics - BI/DWH, Big Data Analytics, Data Engineering and Advanced Analytics Digital - Full stack Development, UI/UX Design, Mobile Development Customer Engagement - Marketing Campaigns, Campaign Analysis, Customer Insights Artificial Intelligence - Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Deep Learning Cyber Security - DevSecOps, Penetration Testing, Multi-Cloud Security, Security Posture Analysis Experience required for success:  Minimum 3 years of technical experience in developing and implementing BI solutions Strong working knowledge (or desire to learn) of Microsoft's Power Platform A passion for delivering data-driven solutions that provide high quality, actionable insights that optimise decision making You are able to design data structures that take into account access patterns, simplicity of human understanding, and maintainability of data Strong technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation technique Expertise in either Power BI, Tableau, Looker or similar reporting technologies Experience with Dynamics CRM is highly desirable Outstanding ability to be agile, nimble and deliver on time You are:  Curious and eager to learn: you are a curious individual who is eager to develop their skills and progress their career at every opportunity in a consulting environment Team player: you thrive as a part of high performing teams and love sharing your knowledge with your peers and clients. We win together Proactive: you seize opportunities when you see them. Every day at Servian presents broad opportunities for personal, professional and business growth Passionate: you are excited by tech. Our team constantly innovate and implement new technologies and methodologies for themselves, our vendors and our clients Why join Servian? Work on a wide range of interesting projects, using a variety of emerging technologies. This is a chance to work alongside a collaborative and passionate like-minded team in an environment that fosters proactive career development through structured learning and development, and multiple avenues for growth. Alongside the above, we also provide employees with life and salary insurance, progressive parental leave policy, and a sociable workplace that truly values its diversity. To make it a fun place you want to be involved in, we have a range of consultant-led initiatives to get everyone excited, which include social and tech clubs (gaming, IoT, chatbots, wellbeing, etc.), meetups, and cloud vendor hackathons. If you’re looking for the opportunity to step up into a leadership position and are excited by the thought of getting your hands dirty with the latest tech-stacks/methodologies, then look no further...    APPLY NOW!

Name: Senior Data Modeller
Description: The company is undergoing an exciting transformation process that will see this role actively collaborating in the build of their target state Data Platform. With collaboration of the Information Architect, this role will see you producing and maintaining the Enterprise Data Model guided by industry data standard and following regulatory requirements.You will also be responsible for the design and documentation of conceptual, logical and physical data model solutions for their Data Platform, including relational, dimensional, and data lake structures.The solutions will support enterprise information management, business intelligence, analytics, real-time data sharing and other business requirements. This key responsibilities for this role are as follows: Reporting to the Information Architect the key focus areas will be:Responsible for the development of conceptual, logical, and physical data models, the implementation of RDBMS, operational data store (ODS), data marts, and data lakes on target platform. Desirable Data Vault modelling knowledge.Responsible for the source-to-target mapping and maintaining related documentationEngage business users and SME's to understand data requirements and translate those requirements into design.Create and own the Enterprise Data Model defining key data domains and sub-domains, establishing definitions and maintaining versioning.Review the business process and conceptualize the entities that interoperate within the business process.Oversee and govern the expansion of existing data model and the optimization of data query performance via best practices.Collaborate with the BI and Analytics teams on creating the optimized, reusable semantic model, complete with metadata and lineage information.Implement business and IT data requirements through new data strategies and designs across all data platforms (relational, dimensional, and NoSQL) and data tools (reporting, visualization, analytics, and machine learning).Work with business and application/solution teams to implement data strategies, build data flows, and develop conceptual/logical/physical data modelsDefine and govern data modelling and design standards, tools, best practices, and related development for enterprise data models.Identify the architecture, infrastructure, and interfaces to data sources, tools supporting automated data loads, security concerns, analytic models, and data visualization.Hands-on modelling, design, configuration, performance tuning, and sandbox.Be an active contributor to how Hollard evolves Data Governance practices and influence the adoption of data standardsTo be considered for this role you need the following skills/experience:5+ years of hands-on relational, dimensional, and/or analytic experience (using RDBMS, dimensional, NoSQL data platform technologies, and ETL and data ingestion protocols). Data Vault modelling is a plus.Bachelor's or master's degree in computer/data science technical or related field.Related certifications desirable.Hands on experience modelling for ODS data lakes, data warehouse, data marts, and enterprise big data platforms.Financial services and/or Insurance knowledge is preferredGood knowledge of metadata management, data modelling, and related tools (Erwin or ER Studio or others) required. Skills acquired or inherent abilitiesDesirable knowledge and experience with industry data modelsExcellent written and oral communication and presentation skills. To learn more about this exciting new role please contact Sahar Khalid on 0421 869 643 or to apply please send your resume to email - sahar.khalid@marsrecruitment.com.au
