Name: Graduate Professionals - National Opportunities
Description: Why join ARRB: Where else will you make a meaningful impact on the lives of 25 million Australians per day and do your bit towards making the country sustainable?    ARRB is a supportive, culturally diverse and vibrant organisation which daily provides exciting opportunities for our teams to do great things, to tackle the big transport and infrastructure questions, and to see these solutions being practically applied.     If our values of Collaboration, Transformation, Integrity and Energy & Passion strike a chord with you, then join us and make your mark! This role offers passionate, proactive, talented and energetic professionals the opportunity to make a significant contribution to the sustainability of Australia’s future mobility system!    ARRB is committed to train young professionals who wants to establish their careers within the transportation infrastructure arena to become the next generation thinkers, thought-leaders and game-changers.  The aim of our experts is to provide mentorship, support and some challenges to help you thrive in your career to stand tall in years to come and be the expert within your chosen field.    About the role and you: We are looking for applicants who can demonstrate their interest/field of study in the below areas within the transportation industry including roads, rail, ports and airports.     We have graduate opportunities for applicants interested in the below fields:    Data Analytics (big data analysis, programming skills / data dashboards / interactive maps / GIS / spatial analysis) Mobility Futures (Artificial Intelligence, next generation transport systems, future fuels, Intelligent Transport Systems) Environmental Management - sustainability, transport and environmental economics, Materials Engineering – traditional road, bridge and rail building materials as well as recycled materials Infrastructure Design – methods and materials for safer, resilient and value-for money infrastructure, smart infrastructure Asset Management – infrastructure condition assessments, investment programming for better mobility outcomes, data technologies for infrastructure assessment Network and Traffic Management – modelling and prediction of capacity and demand, micro-mobility, active travel   Successful applicants will work on a wide range of research, advisory and data-related projects designed to deliver quality and best practice outcomes for our clients with guidance from our experts.       The successful candidates will have the following skills:  Recent Engineering/Science graduates who received their qualifications within the last 5 years Ability to confidently interact within a team made up of a diverse group of people located across Australia Confident communication skills (both verbal and written) Motivated to work and learn with excellent time management skills Excellent attention to detail and ability to solve problems creatively and practically Keen interest in research, creating new knowledge and practical solutions    What we offer:  At ARRB, we are proud of our thriving workforce.  We continue to attract the leading minds within the transportation infrastructure and related research arena.  We truly celebrate our culturally and gender diverse work environment.    We provide an exciting, dynamic and collaborative workplace with challenging roles, where your skills, knowledge and experience will be recognised and respected, including:  Opportunities to work with nationally recognised experts, who offer brilliant mentorship and support Opportunities to contribute to high-profile and interesting projects which make a difference to the community Healthy work-life balance, with flexible arrangements Access to 6 weeks of paid parental leave, extra 2 days of paid holiday leave in December Strong support for career development and further study, including an explicit step-by-step guide for progressing in the organisation and a range of professional development options A well-established social club, with regular socialising events, competitions, quiz events and tournaments We embrace diversity - highlighting a multidisciplinary workforce from all over the world within all of our offices across Australia Contemporary and modern work campuses  To be considered:  Applicants must be Australian Citizens / Permanent Resident of Australia who currently reside in Australia.  Applicants on visas cannot be considered for these vacancies. Please ensure you attach your CV, Cover Letter, Academic Transcript and answer the screening questions provided.   Clearly state on your Cover Letter for which state you are applying for. Only applications who provide all relevant information will be reviewed.

Name: Full Stack Engineer- Digital
Description: The opportunityThis is a great opportunity for those who are eager to diversify their technical ability as well as gain exposure to a number of industries. You will be working alongside some of the most brilliant and talented technologists in the industry, who's thinking and experience has driven Servian's growth and success. You’ll also be exposed to the latest and hottest technologies on the market! About youTechnologist: first and foremost, you are an intelligent technologist with excellent problem-solving skills. We currently have multiple projects in a broad range of clients and environments which require Angular, React, Java, and Node.js skills.Consultative: you are engaging and able to communicate with clients on a strategic and development level. You also possess top class problem solving skills, and the ability to communicate effectively across the technical and the business side of organisation.Team player: you like being part of high performing teams and like sharing your knowledge with your peers. About ServianServian is a consultant-led organisation. We invest heavily in our consultants to ensure they have the technical skills and commercial acumen to be successful in their work. Our consultants have a passion for solving complex problems. They are curious, ambitious and experts in their fields. We have developed a first-rate team so you will be supported and learn from the best.Our business is structured across 5 main pillarsData & Analytics - BI/DW, Big Data Analytics, Data Engineering, Data Science and Advanced AnalyticsCustomer Engagement - Marketing Campaigns, Campaign Analysis, Customer InsightsDigital - Full stack Development, UI/UX Design, Mobile DevelopmentArtificial Intelligence - Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Deep LearningCloud & Technology - Cloud Services (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform) General SkillsStrong professional drive and self-motivatedPassion for IT and are keen to develop and expand your skill setsStrong software development experiences across back and front-end technologiesExposure to AWS, Azure or GCP would be highly desirableExpertise in Angular or ReactExpertise in either Node.js or JavaExposure to; CSS, HTML, and JavaScript is essentialNumerical problem-solving capabilityThe ability to work well with people across both the business and technologyKnowledge of Agile and DevOps methods of delivering projects Why work at Servian?Work on a wide range of interesting projects, using a variety of emerging technologies.Cost of learning covered, such as sponsored certifications and full access to Udemy for all Consultants.A chance to work alongside a collaborative and passionate like-minded team.Consultant-led events including Social clubs, Tech clubs (IoT, Chatbots, etc.), Gaming events, MeetUps, and Cloud vendor Hackathons.Proactive career development through structured learning and development, multiple avenues for growth and an innovative reward and recognition structure.Alongside the above, we also provide employees with life and salary insurance, progressive parental leave policy, and a sociable workplace that truly values its diversity. We hire Junior Engineers through to software architects... if you are passionate about technology and have an insatiable appetite for the acquisition of new knowledge, then a career at Servian is what you want!

Name: Senior Developer
Description: Hi, we’re Idoba – nice to meet you!So who are we?Idoba is an innovation ecosystem that brings together the deep industry experience and complementary capabilities of a bunch of proudly West Australian companies who have a shared passion to co-create a better future for the mining industry (and beyond!). By uniting these technology and consulting businesses together, we have capabilities that span technology and innovation, business improvement, data science, analytics and data insights, as well as specialist mine planning and mining technical expertise.We’ve united our complementary capabilities across operational expertise, technology offerings, and digital enablement to partner with our clients on solving gnarly problems and liberating value. Our team members are clever, curious and quirky people who work flexibly between our vibrant open-plan Perth CBD office and from home.About you and what you can bringYou’re someone who's curious about solving problems for people, and create solutions that improve the life of the user. You enjoy working in a team to solve problems by being able to quickly define and scope out solutions by working in an agile environment. More formally, you will need a very strong background in web development and database programming as well as:5+ years hands-on professional experience as Senior DeveloperAWS CertifiedExperience with: Big dataDev-opsAzureC#PythonData-ManagementDAMASome awareness of Cyber SecurityAbout the role This is an opportunity to apply your skills along different parts of the product lifecycle, from experimentation to MVP and beyond, depending on where your purpose takes you. As a Developer, you will be responsible for building a wide range of custom-built applications, to help develop interfaces to our engines. This is a challenging and highly technical role working on a variety of complex problems.   We work in a team and collaborative environment, applying the principles of Agile. You will work closely with our Lead Developer for meeting operational goals, as well as offshore teams (solution modelling and solving, client satisfaction and billability)Next steps If you are thinking about a new opportunity, then please apply via the link and I will be in touch. For any questions or a confidential discussion regarding the role please contact me directly on laura.ashe@sandpitinnovation.com

Name: Senior Product Analytics Analyst - Building AI/ML Products
Description: This role sits within Data Products among data scientists and engineers but will also work closely with the marketing squads in charge of personalisation products. You will be exposed to production and POC big data environments, advanced analytics and ML / AI personalisation projects, with training and exposure to many of the latest cutting-edge tools in the data.Key activities  Provide analysis and ongoing commentary on campaign performance driving personalisation Perform ad hoc analysis using SQL and other tools of your choice, and present findings to broad range of audience Build self-service reporting tools as appropriate. Propose opportunities for conducting A/B tests, and lead the implementation of testing plans Proactively share knowledge with other analysts and use Chapter time to keep learning new analytical techniques. Manage stakeholder relationships in marketing and ecommerce.  Skills required:  Is it essential that you have been an Analyst or a Senior Analyst in a solid commercial environment for a few years. Ideally you have some familiarity with Data Science concepts Extensive experience working in a large, complex customer analytics environment, ideally with some exposure to product analytics or marketing data and insights Good to have exposure to Big Query and Google Cloud Platform Advanced SQL for extracting, querying and relational databases are essential (ideally Teradata, but will consider other data warehouses) Strong visualisation skills are essential (Ideally Tableau) Statistical modelling with R or Python are highly regarded Exposure to cloud platforms is highly regarded (google could platform / GCP, AWS or Azure Preferred knowledge of statistical modelling tools and techniques e.g. segmentation, propensity models Tertiary degree in Mathematics, Marketing, Statistics, Computing or related analytical field Strong influencing skills with ability to effectively liaise at all levels of the business

Name: CTRM Test Analyst
Description: Company description:We keep millions of people moving every day and continue to be Australia's leading transport fuel supplier and convenience retailer. Our business is dynamic and often technical, and we rely on talented people who seek to find solutions. Whatever your journey, we're the fuel that gets you there. Ampol, Australia's own.Job description:About Ampol:Ampol is expanding into new and forward-facing Energy opportunities including e-mobility, hydrogen, batteries, renewables, and carbon. As the company executes on this vision, we are seeking to build leading digital and analytic capabilities with a deep connection to customers.About the role:CTRM Test Analyst is responsible for creating and executing both manual and automated test scenarios. Key to this role is ensuring software systems, applications and enhancements meet with business demands, functional requirements and technical specifications and are fit to be deployed into production.Reporting to the CTRM QA Lead, the role is also responsible for planning, scheduling, and reporting of test outcomes to ensure the stake holder awareness of test efforts, issues, and agreement of test outcomes.It is early in our journey, but we are moving quickly. This role will have the opportunity to contribute to the build of our systems capability and has substantial scope to influence its success.We are looking for a detail-oriented team member with the drive to: Perform static test reviews of the business requirements/User Stories and develop both manual and automated test scenarios for different phases of testing in a project (System Integration testing/End to End/UAT/Regression/NFR) Execute test scenarios and ensure the test results are recorded in appropriate systems and defects are identified and managed Setup Test Automation environments, prepare Test data and automation scripts based on agreed framework You will be part of a great Program team located in Sydney, Singapore, Melbourne and Brisbane. We are culturally diverse with a massive range of skillsets and experiences, so if you love to learn then you will love our team.About you:You will ideally have more than 5 years of proven testing experience in CTRM domain or products or the IT Fuel supply chain space. Your experience will be supported by a tertiary qualification in Information Technology.You will have demonstrated hands-on experience in the creation of Test Scenarios, Test Plans, Defect Reporting and Test Case design techniques for various test phases including sprints, system integration testing, end to end Testing and perf testing. 3 + years of Manual Testing and automation testing of complex architectures and applications using various industry standard automation tools Hands on Testing experience in the CTRM/ETRM supply chain domain with products including Allegro, Endur, Findur, AgTech, EKA, Fusion etc. and/or industry is highly desirable  Hands on experience in end to end trade life cycle testing across Front, Middle & Back offices(Trade execution, Valuations, supply operations, inventory management etc.) Proficient in using Atlassian Tools like Jira and Confluence & test management tools like HP ALM, Test Rails, ACCELQ etc. Experience working in both Agile Experience in conducting automation feasibility analysis, Interface testing & perf testing Clear and unambiguous communication with previous business partnering or consulting experience Additionally, you will have: Test automation frameworks and tools: ACCELQ, Selenium, BDD based framework Understanding of CI/CD concepts Experience in API testing and Microservices General SQL &scripting knowledge for use in preparing bespoke Test automation scripts ITSQB foundation certificate Experience in Cloud Applications (Microsoft Azure, AWS) Experience in Big Data Analytics tools: SPLUNK This is a 12 month maximum term contract which may have the opportunity to extend based on project requirements. At Ampol we encourage vaccination against Covid-19 as an effective measure in helping to protect our people and our communities.We're an equal opportunity workplace. We not only embrace diversity and inclusion; we celebrate what makes you unique. We welcome applications from people of all ages, cultural backgrounds, and diverse sexualities and genders (including if you identify as transgender). We also highly encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples to apply for roles with Ampol.Applications close on July 13, 2022.Thank you to our prospective agency partners for your interest, we are not taking CVs at this time.

Name: Data & Analytics Consultant - Brisbane
Description:
Who we are:
Our client is one of Australia’s leading Data & Analytics Consultancies. They have offices in Adelaide and Melbourne and are now expanding to Brisbane! They provide a fantastic work culture, flexible working arrangements, access to leading-edge technology and projects, professional development and much more!  
They are currently looking to fill multiple positions in their Brisbane team at the mid to senior levels. As a consultant, you will be supported and trained to become a leading Data Specialist, involved in challenging projects from start to end.
The Opportunity:
In this role, you will work collaboratively with their team and clients to create insightful solutions to help clients make informed decisions. Use your Data Engineering skills and experience to analyse, integrate, model, and move data to create data and analytics solutions for the clients. 
Technical Requirements for the role: 


Strong experience in on-premise and cloud-based technologies and creation of hybrid solutions 


Strong Microsoft Azure Data Services experience is preferable 


AWS or Google Cloud platform is advantageous 




Data integration, ETL, Data architecture, and modelling 


Database management systems (RDBMS) and its architecture 


Semantic models (multi-dimensional) 


If you have more than 2 years experience in any of the below please apply! 


IoT 


Machine learning 


Interactive visualisations 


Semantic models (Tabular/Columnar) 


Big data solutions 


Real-time data streams 


Mobile integration 


Data lakes & Databricks 


Other Requirements: 


A relevant tertiary qualification is highly advantageous 


Microsoft/AWS certifications are highly advantageous 


Ability to solve client business problems using Data and Analytical solutions 


Excellent written and verbal communication skills are a must 


Prior experience in client-facing roles, exceptional interpersonal & relationship building skills . 


 
If you are ready to take that next step in your career, this is an exciting opportunity to join a growing analytics solutions provider who value flexibility, collaboration and professional development.
For further information please contact Thilini Elkaduwa at EGM Recruitment on 0431 696 395.

Name: Cloud Engineer
Description: Servian is an award-winning, people-focused, global tech consultancy with a rich heritage in Data, DevOps/Cloud, Digital, Machine Learning and Cyber Security. We embrace innovation, change, and the positive impact it has on us and our clients. As a Servianite you will have the opportunity to work on a wide range of interesting projects, using a variety of emerging technologies. We aim to build an employee experience where you will grow more with us, not be drowned out by the loudest voice, and hence we strive to set you up for a career that will have a greater impact. Our business is focused on developing our people and offerings across the following:Cloud & Technology - Cloud Services (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform), DevOps and Automation inc HashiCorpData & Analytics - BI/DWH, Big Data Analytics, Data Engineering, Data Science and Advanced Analytics (Snowflake)Digital - Full stack Development, UI/UX Design, Mobile DevelopmentCustomer Engagement - Marketing Campaigns, Campaign Analysis, Customer InsightsArtificial Intelligence - Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Deep LearningCyber Security - DevSecOps, Penetration Testing, Multi-Cloud Security, Security Posture AnalysisThe Role:You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, being involved in implementing strategies and delivering on cloud solutions in GCP, Azure and AWS. What To Look Forward To:Implementing cloud solutions for clients, including infrastructure, data platforms and migration strategy.Working with clients to coach and share our solutions and approaches.Building out and mentor on Continuous Integration and Delivery, using modern tools like but not limited to: Terraform, GitLab, Azure DevOps.Maintaining accreditations with one of more of our key partners, AWS, Microsoft, GCP, and HashiCorp.Working in an agile environment/teams and delivered projects using agile methodologyAutomating the operating system layer with one or more common scripting languages (Bash, Python,  Powershell)Working with CI/CD workflows and exposure of their tools (Azure DevOps, CircleCI, GitLab etc)Automating testing and continuous integration and building CI pipelinesWorking with Infrastructure as Code tools (Terraform is the main)Working with centralised monitoring tools, either cloud native or otherwise Experience Required For Success: Understanding of DevOps principles and implementation.In depth experience with implementing at least one configuration management system e.g Ansible.Build pipeline (CI) experience; both design and implementation.Infrastructure as a service and platforms as a service.Outstanding ability to be agile, nimble and deliver on time.Automation and scripting experience.Experience in containerisation technology, Kubernetes, Docker, EKS, GKE, AKS, Podman.Experience with application architectures and how to re-architect for cloud.Willingness to learn about new and emerging technologies.Experience with HashiCorp tools; Consul, Vault, Terraform would be advantageousWe hire for mindset! If you don’t possess all of the above skills we can teach you what’s missing. So if this role resonates with you then hit that apply button! Why join Servian?Our career pathways are not a one size fits all, we help you identify your personal and professional goals through our mentorship program. Helping you put together an action plan and keep you accountable.Growth through unlimited L&D and goal-based learning - free access to Udemy, you pass we pay model for courses and certifications, internal run boot camps and communities of practice (Machine Learning, DevOps, WebDev, Agile/Scrum Guilds)Flat Structure - No silos or departments; have the opportunity to work across various tech stacks, industries and projects. We value trust and transparency, that’s why we have an open-door policy across the business. Create your own destiny -  We support our consultant’s creativity. If you have an idea, turn it into an initiative!Flexible WFH policy - We value work life balance, accountability and autonomy. Wellbeing & Benefits:We provide employees with Life Insurance, Income Protection Insurance and access to an Employee Assistance Program. Generous Parental leave.Substantial Referral fee. We value your opinion and want our employees to contribute to the success of Servian!Wellbeing and mental health initiatives - Yoga, Meditation, Steptember, Around the Bay.We are proud to have a sociable workplace that values diversity and celebrates achievements with quarterly company-wide events, social events and more. Think VR laser tag, wine tours and cooking classes.Monthly in person team lunches/dinners so you can connect with your colleagues outside of work! Consultant-led initiatives to get everyone excited, which include social and tech clubs (gaming, IoT, badminton, wellbeing, whisky and wine, etc.), meetups, and cloud vendor hackathons.Servian recognises individual differences and welcomes people from a variety of life and work experiences. The diversity of our people is core to our ability to innovate, grow and to fulfil our collective aspiration of helping people to own their tomorrow. A natural curiosity, a respect for differences and a growth mindset are valued at Servian. Come to the tech side… we have cookies! Apply below!

Name: Digital Transformation Analyst
Graduate Professionals - National Opportunities
Description: Why join ARRB: Where else will you make a meaningful impact on the lives of 25 million Australians per day and do your bit towards making the country sustainable?    ARRB is a supportive, culturally diverse and vibrant organisation which daily provides exciting opportunities for our teams to do great things, to tackle the big transport and infrastructure questions, and to see these solutions being practically applied.     If our values of Collaboration, Transformation, Integrity and Energy & Passion strike a chord with you, then join us and make your mark! This role offers passionate, proactive, talented and energetic professionals the opportunity to make a significant contribution to the sustainability of Australia’s future mobility system!    ARRB is committed to train young professionals who wants to establish their careers within the transportation infrastructure arena to become the next generation thinkers, thought-leaders and game-changers.  The aim of our experts is to provide mentorship, support and some challenges to help you thrive in your career to stand tall in years to come and be the expert within your chosen field.    About the role and you: We are looking for applicants who can demonstrate their interest/field of study in the below areas within the transportation industry including roads, rail, ports and airports.     We have graduate opportunities for applicants interested in the below fields:    Data Analytics (big data analysis, programming skills / data dashboards / interactive maps / GIS / spatial analysis) Mobility Futures (Artificial Intelligence, next generation transport systems, future fuels, Intelligent Transport Systems) Environmental Management - sustainability, transport and environmental economics, Materials Engineering – traditional road, bridge and rail building materials as well as recycled materials Infrastructure Design – methods and materials for safer, resilient and value-for money infrastructure, smart infrastructure Asset Management – infrastructure condition assessments, investment programming for better mobility outcomes, data technologies for infrastructure assessment Network and Traffic Management – modelling and prediction of capacity and demand, micro-mobility, active travel   Successful applicants will work on a wide range of research, advisory and data-related projects designed to deliver quality and best practice outcomes for our clients with guidance from our experts.       The successful candidates will have the following skills:  Recent Engineering/Science graduates who received their qualifications within the last 5 years Ability to confidently interact within a team made up of a diverse group of people located across Australia Confident communication skills (both verbal and written) Motivated to work and learn with excellent time management skills Excellent attention to detail and ability to solve problems creatively and practically Keen interest in research, creating new knowledge and practical solutions    What we offer:  At ARRB, we are proud of our thriving workforce.  We continue to attract the leading minds within the transportation infrastructure and related research arena.  We truly celebrate our culturally and gender diverse work environment.    We provide an exciting, dynamic and collaborative workplace with challenging roles, where your skills, knowledge and experience will be recognised and respected, including:  Opportunities to work with nationally recognised experts, who offer brilliant mentorship and support Opportunities to contribute to high-profile and interesting projects which make a difference to the community Healthy work-life balance, with flexible arrangements Access to 6 weeks of paid parental leave, extra 2 days of paid holiday leave in December Strong support for career development and further study, including an explicit step-by-step guide for progressing in the organisation and a range of professional development options A well-established social club, with regular socialising events, competitions, quiz events and tournaments We embrace diversity - highlighting a multidisciplinary workforce from all over the world within all of our offices across Australia Contemporary and modern work campuses  To be considered:  Applicants must be Australian Citizens / Permanent Resident of Australia who currently reside in Australia.  Applicants on visas cannot be considered for these vacancies. Please ensure you attach your CV, Cover Letter, Academic Transcript and answer the screening questions provided.   Clearly state on your Cover Letter for which state you are applying for. Only applications who provide all relevant information will be reviewed.
