Name: Microsoft BI Developer
Description: DWS is seeking an experienced and capable Microsoft BI Developer to join our Canberra office. Experience working in or with federal government departments would be ideal, but is not essential.The role will be working with a fantastic team on bespoke systems based on Microsoft BI tools and technologies for big data analysis.Type: Permanent, full timeStart: ASAPLocation: On-site, CanberraSalary: up to $150K (including super)Applicants MUST have Australian Citizenship. The successful person will need to gain and maintain baseline / NV1 security clearanceEssential Tech:  Strong SQL skills including SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS) and SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS), and Power BI Experience with enterprise data warehousing methodologies, including designing and maintaining complex data warehouses and corporate external data source pipelines Team Foundation Server experience is highly desirable  Required Experience / knowledge:  Complex, enterprise scale database maintenance and administration Business intelligence analysis Create reports in SSRS & Power BI Custom application administration and support Familiar with complex data warehousing and methodologies    Working at DWS offers you:  Ongoing professional and career development Paid learning and certifications (chosen entirely by you), with completion bonuses Corporate discounts on a range of services and products, including health insurance, gym memberships, Apple products and much more        About Us: Established in 1991, DWS is a professional Technology Consultancy and part of HCL Technologies. With offices across Australia, we have over 700 employees in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane and Canberra; providing services to a broad range of blue-chip corporate clients, as well as Federal, State and Local Government agencies. We provide a wide range of services including; IT consulting, managed application services, project management, customer driven innovation, digital transformation, data and business analytics, strategic advisory and productivity, and robotic process automation.   Applicants MUST have Australian Citizenship. The successful person will need to gain and maintain baseline / NV1 security clearance Ready for a new challenge? Click APPLY now! www.dws.com.au

Name: Business Transformation Consultant
Description: Role and Responsibility:The Business Transformation Consultant is responsible for building and supporting the big data platform. As aBusiness Transformation Consultant - Big Data, your responsibilities include:Work closely with business stakeholders, process owners and users to understand the service/product requirements.Liaise with stakeholders, external parties and/or research to understand Non-Functional Requirements(NFRs) to help ensure that the solution meets relevant standards and other system/solution quality requirements.Become a bridge between key client business stakeholders, project/iteration managers, solution architects/designers, developers, and testers Experience:To ensure success in the role you will possess the following skills:Minimum of 10+ years of experience as a tech BA or equivalent in IT Consulting or other technology business units across the industry.Minimum of 3+ years of business analysis experience in data initiatives such as data Governance, modernisation, migration, reporting, analytics, information management and data quality.Experience delivering projects based on Cloud Platform such as Azure, AWS, GCP and other modern data platforms· Understanding of containerisation, virtualization, infrastructure and networking.Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or related Engineering courses.One or more industry-recognised technology or project delivery certifications or badges.

Name: Senior Support Analyst
Description:
Westpac Group has a rich heritage and offers employees a multitude of opportunities. We aim to attract the best people inside and outside of the business – building an organisation where the best talent thrives.
The Westpac Group has been proudly advancing Australia for two centuries. Our success is built upon both our heritage and our ability to evolve. Our vision is to be one of the world's great service companies, helping our customers, communities, and people to prosper and grow. In GroupTech we're striving to be game-changing technologists, shaping the future of banking. We understand the big picture and focus on things that will move the dial for the Westpac Group.
The Westpac Group has a complex Information Technology environment that needs to deliver to the rapidly changing needs of our customers and employees, the ever-evolving IT landscape, and the Group's regulatory and statutory requirements.

How will I help?
We are looking for a high calibre individual who has operated as a senior support analyst within financial market technology who can serve as a subject matter expert and a consultant in not only supporting Data analytics platform and the various use cases built using this platform. The successful candidate is expected to play a key role in refining and maturing the highly complex capability. Individuals need to draw on many disciplines: Front office FICC trading and sales, front line support, data analytics, big data, documenting functional specifications, aid in testing & validation tasks, training & mentoring, implementation, and post implementation support.
Possession of a strong understanding of financial market systems is required as is a very strong knowledge of FICC trading ecosystems. We are looking for experienced and task focussed individuals who are open, strong communicators and enjoy working in high performance teams.  
Provide first line application/systems support for the Data analytics platform.
Ensure systems up time meets set SLA’s.
Ensuring our data, reporting and analytics platform are efficiently managed, including upgrades, patching, backup, and disaster recovery.
Maintain the integrity, completeness, and accuracy of data on a timely basis. Monitoring data pipelines ensuring it operate within acceptable limits, and continuously improving the efficiency, quality, and transparency.
Provide application support for the use cases deployed on the Analytics platform including investigating and escalating data quality and completeness issues.
Continually reviewing and updating processes to increase functionality and efficiency.
Manage security, access control of our data and platform assets.
Act as a key SME for the surveillance capability.
Continuous improvement including focus on automating manual process, produce automated reporting for the business users to deliver productivity and system health benefits.


What’s in it for you?
You will build your profile internally with senior stakeholders and be part of the future of a business that has been around for 200 years. You'll be working for an organisation that supports development, internal career moves and flexible working. Along with competitive salary, you’ll receive Westpac’s generous benefits and a whole array of customer discounts.

What do I need?
To be successful in this role, you need to have the following skills & personal attributes.
Technical and Industry Expertise:
Minimum of 5 years’ support experience within financial services.
 Regulatory Reporting Experience is Required
High attention to detail
Experience in providing application support
Development experience using Python or Spark
Experience in the use of SQL to run database queries. 
Formalised ITIL training methodology experience / qualifications
Strong analytical ability: Present knowledge and perform research, making logical analysis, evaluating risks/benefits. Recommending alternatives for courses of action and implements creative solutions to complex problems.
Self-Initiative: Initiates preventive measures and procedural changes. Ability to work cross-functionally reaching across business lines or operating units. Coaches, mentors, and influence others.
Ability to train, mentor, coach others to increase their proficiency levels.

Advantageous: 
Previous experience in a Trade Surveillance capacity developing such systems and associated alert logic
Experience in application testing
Understanding of the pre trade life cycle and detailed knowledge of pre trade FX / Rates trading activities. 
Proven dealings with senior management and vendors
Development experience using Rest APIs.



What is it like to work there?
As well as good pay and a great culture, joining the Westpac family means you’ll get some of the best banking, wealth, and insurance benefits in the market. We’ll even pay you to do volunteer or community work. We aim to provide one big, supportive team of people who love helping others succeed. Working with us you'll discover new ways of working, and an exciting range of roles to showcase your skills. As an equal opportunity employer, we’re proud to have created a culture and work environment that values diversity and flexibility – and champions inclusion.
The health and well-being of our employees is our top priority. We have developed clear standards to ensure our people are confident, safe, and healthy whether they are working from a Westpac Group site or working from home. These are based on expert medical advice and Safe Work Australia guidelines.
As part of our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, this role is open to experienced candidates seeking a discussion around workplace flexibility. We invite candidates of all ages, people with a disability and Indigenous Australians to apply.
For more information visit careers.westpacgroup.com.au

How do I Apply? 
Start here. Just click on the APPLY button.
The Westpac Group has implemented an Entry to Workplace Policy that requires employees and others entering our workplaces to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 by relevant dates set out in the policy (subject to applicable medical exemptions). Our employees are required to comply with the policy regardless of whether they are in customer-facing or non-customer-facing roles (as employees in non-customer-facing roles are required to attend the workplace under our Hybrid Working Strategy). Further, the Westpac Group is required to comply with State/Territory issued public health orders/directions which require relevant workers to be vaccinated against COVID-19 to enter workplaces.
By applying for this role, you acknowledge that you are aware of our Entry to Workplace Policy, and if you secure employment with us, you will be required to comply with the policy

Name: Data Engineer
Description: Do work that Matters As an experienced data engineer with proven expertise in software development and a passion for providing data-driven solutions, you're ahead of trends and work at the forefront of Big Data, ML, Decisioning, Visualisation and Data warehouse technologies.  Which is why we're the perfect fit for you. Here, you'll be part of a team of engineers going above and beyond to improve the standard of digital banking. Using the latest tech to solve our customers' most complex data-centric problems.  To us, data is everything. It is what powers our cutting-edge features and it's the reason we can provide seamless experiences for millions of customers from app to branch.  We're responsible for CommBank's key analytics capabilities and work to create world-leading capabilities for analytics, information management and decisioning. We work across the Teradata Group Data Warehouse, Hadoop Big Data Platform, Analytics Workbench for Machine Learning, Pega Decisioning, SAS, R, Tableau, Oracle BI, Ab Initio.  What will set you up for success? You're passionate about building industry leading group data products from scratch The design and construction of large-scale automated machine learning and data mining practices excites you You're ready to execute state-of-the-art coding practices, driving high quality outcomes to solve core business objectives and minimise risks You're capable of creating both technology blueprints and engineering roadmaps, for a multi- year data transformational journey You feel at home and can lead and drive a culture where quality, excellence and openness are championed You're constantly thinking outside the box and breaking boundaries to solve complex data problems We are interested in hearing from people who: Are experienced in design and development of Big Data, Visualisation and Data warehouse applications Are confident in building group data products from scratch, by integrating large sets of data derived from hundreds of internal and external sources Have a natural drive to educate, communicate and positively influence a large stakeholder group Have experience working in DevOps model environments Tech skills We use a broad range of tools, languages, and frameworks. We don't expect you to know them all but experience or exposure with some of these (or equivalents) will set you up for success in this team; Hadoop / Teradata platform, using Spark , TCF and various ETL frameworks. Strong proficiency in writing SQL queries. Scala, ANSI/ISO SQL, or AbInitio graph along with backend coding expertise in Java and Python. Exposure to Ab-Initio environments is highly regarded. Working with us:  Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career with CommBank is for you.  Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive, and flexible workplace with flexible work locations. One where we're driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.  Here, you'll thrive. You'll be supported when faced with challenges and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We're hiring engineers from across all of Australia, you'll be empowered to do your best work and be given the choice on when and where that work happens. We really love working here, and we think you will too.  If this sounds like you, apply now!  The health and safety of our people, customers and communities is our number one priority. This means that we require all of our employees to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. Please speak to us if you have any questions about this based on your individual circumstances. Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career here is for you. Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive and flexible workplace. One where we're driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.Here, you'll thrive. You'll be supported when faced with challenges, and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We really love working here, and we think you will too.We're determined to make a real difference for Australia's first peoples. We encourage all interested applicants to apply. If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick [link removed] to submit a valid application. We're keen to support you with the next step in your career.

Name: Services Sales Executive
Description: Cloud Services Sales ExecutiveGlobal Data & Analytics Software VendorUncapped earningsMelbourne - VICCompany Overview Are you passionate about making large companies smarter and analytics driven? We are a leading cloud data analytics platform company built for a hybrid multi-cloud world, solving the world’s most complex data challenges at scale. The world’s largest and most analytically sophisticated enterprises use our industry-leading Analytic technology solutions and its consulting services to enable them to capture, store, manage, integrate and analyse detailed data to understand and improve business performance.  Position Overview We’re looking for someone exceptional for an exceptional opportunity. We want a Services Sales professional to work with us to be responsible for the overall Services business development and delivery of Consulting, Transactional and Managed Services within an assigned account, accounts, or industry, playing a key role in account planning and execution, helping to redefine how to sell and deliver business-focused services to existing and new target customers.  You are highly respected for your knowledge, skills and experience to meet our customers’ business requirements through the use of data and analytics at scale. You are a good communicator with strong interaction with the customer understanding their needs, creating offers and mapping existing assets to solve their business problems. You will be working in a combination of physical and virtual office environments, including home, office, and customer site. Key Areas of ResponsibilityDevelop in-depth understanding of their customer’s objectives, including the business, industry, company profile, business plan and key initiatives of the organisation. Engage at all levels of the customer from the Senior Executives to the Database Administrator (DBA)Develop strong relationships and build advocacy with key decision makers at Customers.In conjunction with the Account Executive and other members of the account team define and enhance the account plan and strategy including the development of opportunities that drive Annual Recurring Revenue growth and Services Revenue.Identify, develop and own Services opportunities within their assigned accounts and industry.Own and manage the consulting funnel and pipeline of opportunities for their designated accounts or territories. This includes maintaining the funnel in Salesforce and to update active opportunities.Engage with customers at all levels from Senior Executives to DBAs to outline how data drives value and provide thought leadership - building strong and long-lasting relationships.Lead negotiator for proposals and contracts.Work with Program Managers and Project Managers to provide scoping, planning, cost estimating, and pricing of Consulting engagements within the overall Consulting portfolio for their account, in conjunction with the Consulting Manager/Director.Manage and own the development of proposals for Services, related Statements of Work and Bid Review documents.Direct, and support the execution and delivery of customer solutions from a services perspective, including participation in client steering committees, project audits and quality checks. Be the point contact for issue resolution and managing escalations.Be responsible for the Consulting forecast, orders, revenue, profit, engagement planning, engagement execution, engagement quality, and client satisfaction.Work with Project Managers and Practice Leaders to qualify skills and training required to meet your customer’s needs.Work with Global Development Centers to position cost effective offshore/dual shore opportunities and engage GDC resources during positioning, selling and delivery where appropriate.Provide direction for solution implementation engagements, of moderate to high complexity, or a collection of multiple projects. Act as a Program Manager / Director as required. Education and Experience Required BS, MBA, or MS in business, technical or professional discipline or equivalent work experience.10 plus years IT industry or related experience, with an “IT worldly” perspective.An acknowledged and consolidated experience within the Data domain (Data Warehouse, BI, Data Management, Data Analytics, Advanced Analytics, Big Data, etc.), being able to create solid and trustful working relationships with customers, understand their business strategy and priorities, and use Data & Analytics as an enabler to grow their business.Passion to win, entrepreneurial, high energy, responsive and results driven.Proven experience in customer relationship managementConsulting selling experience with a vendor or consulting firm is preferable.Experience and ability to work in a matrixed organisation.Business management experience including engagement management experience with multiple project streams and complex EIM or Analytics implementations.Experience in other competitive products. Knowledge in Open Source Analytics, DB2, Oracle, Analytics AppliancesOne or more Industries experience, ideally in industries such as Finance, Retail and Telco IndustriesStrong consultative, communicative, writing, and presentation skills.A people, customer and team orientation.A motivated, proactive, organized and “self-starting” attitude and working style. Strong personal and team goal orientation.Expertise in developing and delivering working documents that communicate and corroborate complex ideas.Strong planning and organisational skills.Demonstrated consultative approach to business problem solving internally or with the client/prospects and/or partners.

Name: Data Engineer
Description: Candidates must be Melbourne based - Permanent Opportunity Work as a Data Engineer with a renowned Global Consulting firm based out of Melbourne. Responsibilities and Skills required: Azure Experience including compute, storage, networking, and securityMust have experience with KUSTO Query LanguageExperience implementing scalable cloud-based environments and systems; service-oriented architectures and microservices; deploying resilient, scalable, high-throughput systems.Experience with deploying Infrastructure as Code using languages and tools such as Azure Bicep and Terraform.Microsoft Azure Data & Analytics PaaS & SaaS Services such as Databricks (Spark), HD Insight, Data Factory, Data Lake, Cosmos DB, SQL and DevOps or you have a similar technology stack expertise that can be transposedIn addition, you have experience with data modelling/warehousing techniques and data integrationSpark StreamingExperience in batch big data engineering skills including: Hadoop, Spark, Hive, HBase To be considered for the role click the 'apply' button or for more information about this and other opportunities please contact Natasha Bhatia on 03 86804237 or email: nbhatia@paxus.com.au and quote the above job reference number. Paxus values diversity and welcomes applications from Indigenous Australians, people from diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds and people living with a disability. If you require an adjustment to the recruitment process please contact me on the above contact details.

Name: Data Engineer
Description: About Horizon Power  Horizon Power is Western Australia's regional and remote power provider. We are passionate about what we do and strive to ensure our customers receive safe and reliable power to their homes, businesses, and communities.  We're a State Government-owned, commercially-focused corporation in regional WA. We do everything we can to provide quality, safe and reliable power to residents and major industries. We're doing our best to safeguard what's special about regional WA.  About the role  Reporting to the Data Management & Integration Lead, the Data Engineer role is responsible for expanding and maintaining the Data Platform's capability to support data pipelines, data flow, integration, and BI reporting.  Working with business data owners you will ensure that data is available; from internal and external sources while optimising data flow and collection through the data management platform and data pipeline architecture.  Responsibilities will include but are not limited to:Work with the business to gather and analyse business and technical requirementsAssembling large, complex data sets that meet functional / non-functional business requirementsDesigning, developing and implementing data pipelines for data migration & collection, data analytics and BI reporting & visualisationsSupport and maintain big data and streaming platforms and deployed solutionsWorking with stakeholders to assist with data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needsConfigure data governance tools for business glossary, metadata management and data quality managementIdentify and implement continuous improvements to maximise value of the data driven solutions and performance of the platformAbout you To be successful in this role you will have:Proven working experience as a Data Engineer/BI Analyst/BI Developer preferably in building data solutions by ingesting and processing data from various source systems and developing BI reports and dashboardsExperience with multiple data technologies and conceptsExperience using AWS, Snowflake and Kafka product suiteExtensive experience in SQL and PythonCommunication, negotiation, analytical, research and problem solving skillsKnowledge of and/or experience with Data integration and streaming technologiesKnowledge of best practice in data architecture, management, security and governanceAgile project methodology exposure (Desirable)Knowledge and experience of the utilities industry (Desirable) We care about our employees, as our focus is on people, safety and wellbeing to create a united and inspiring culture. That's why we offer a range of attractive remuneration packages and flexible working arrangements. If you want to be part of a business that's always looking for new ways in delivering energy solutions for regional growth and vibrant communities, we want to hear from you. We value an inclusive and diverse workplace and strongly encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Island people and people with diverse background to apply. Horizon Power requires all employees to be fully vaccinated against Covid-19 by their start date to ensure the safety and wellbeing of our people. If you are applying for a role at Horizon Power please consider this new requirement when submitting your application. Next steps If you're excited about the opportunity to be part of a high performing organisation undertaking incredible and diverse challenges whilst furthering your career, this could be the role for you, click on the Apply button below. Applications close on 15th of July 2022.

Name: Graduate Professionals - National Opportunities
Description: Why join ARRB: Where else will you make a meaningful impact on the lives of 25 million Australians per day and do your bit towards making the country sustainable?    ARRB is a supportive, culturally diverse and vibrant organisation which daily provides exciting opportunities for our teams to do great things, to tackle the big transport and infrastructure questions, and to see these solutions being practically applied.     If our values of Collaboration, Transformation, Integrity and Energy & Passion strike a chord with you, then join us and make your mark! This role offers passionate, proactive, talented and energetic professionals the opportunity to make a significant contribution to the sustainability of Australia’s future mobility system!    ARRB is committed to train young professionals who wants to establish their careers within the transportation infrastructure arena to become the next generation thinkers, thought-leaders and game-changers.  The aim of our experts is to provide mentorship, support and some challenges to help you thrive in your career to stand tall in years to come and be the expert within your chosen field.    About the role and you: We are looking for applicants who can demonstrate their interest/field of study in the below areas within the transportation industry including roads, rail, ports and airports.     We have graduate opportunities for applicants interested in the below fields:    Data Analytics (big data analysis, programming skills / data dashboards / interactive maps / GIS / spatial analysis) Mobility Futures (Artificial Intelligence, next generation transport systems, future fuels, Intelligent Transport Systems) Environmental Management - sustainability, transport and environmental economics, Materials Engineering – traditional road, bridge and rail building materials as well as recycled materials Infrastructure Design – methods and materials for safer, resilient and value-for money infrastructure, smart infrastructure Asset Management – infrastructure condition assessments, investment programming for better mobility outcomes, data technologies for infrastructure assessment Network and Traffic Management – modelling and prediction of capacity and demand, micro-mobility, active travel   Successful applicants will work on a wide range of research, advisory and data-related projects designed to deliver quality and best practice outcomes for our clients with guidance from our experts.       The successful candidates will have the following skills:  Recent Engineering/Science graduates who received their qualifications within the last 5 years Ability to confidently interact within a team made up of a diverse group of people located across Australia Confident communication skills (both verbal and written) Motivated to work and learn with excellent time management skills Excellent attention to detail and ability to solve problems creatively and practically Keen interest in research, creating new knowledge and practical solutions    What we offer:  At ARRB, we are proud of our thriving workforce.  We continue to attract the leading minds within the transportation infrastructure and related research arena.  We truly celebrate our culturally and gender diverse work environment.    We provide an exciting, dynamic and collaborative workplace with challenging roles, where your skills, knowledge and experience will be recognised and respected, including:  Opportunities to work with nationally recognised experts, who offer brilliant mentorship and support Opportunities to contribute to high-profile and interesting projects which make a difference to the community Healthy work-life balance, with flexible arrangements Access to 6 weeks of paid parental leave, extra 2 days of paid holiday leave in December Strong support for career development and further study, including an explicit step-by-step guide for progressing in the organisation and a range of professional development options A well-established social club, with regular socialising events, competitions, quiz events and tournaments We embrace diversity - highlighting a multidisciplinary workforce from all over the world within all of our offices across Australia Contemporary and modern work campuses  To be considered:  Applicants must be Australian Citizens / Permanent Resident of Australia who currently reside in Australia.  Applicants on visas cannot be considered for these vacancies. Please ensure you attach your CV, Cover Letter, Academic Transcript and answer the screening questions provided.   Clearly state on your Cover Letter for which state you are applying for. Only applications who provide all relevant information will be reviewed.

Name: Microsoft BI Developer
Description: DWS is seeking an experienced and capable Microsoft BI Developer to join our Canberra office. Experience working in or with federal government departments would be ideal, but is not essential.The role will be working with a fantastic team on bespoke systems based on Microsoft BI tools and technologies for big data analysis.Type: Permanent, full timeStart: ASAPLocation: On-site, CanberraSalary: up to $150K (including super)Applicants MUST have Australian Citizenship. The successful person will need to gain and maintain baseline / NV1 security clearanceEssential Tech:  Strong SQL skills including SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS) and SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS), and Power BI Experience with enterprise data warehousing methodologies, including designing and maintaining complex data warehouses and corporate external data source pipelines Team Foundation Server experience is highly desirable  Required Experience / knowledge:  Complex, enterprise scale database maintenance and administration Business intelligence analysis Create reports in SSRS & Power BI Custom application administration and support Familiar with complex data warehousing and methodologies    Working at DWS offers you:  Ongoing professional and career development Paid learning and certifications (chosen entirely by you), with completion bonuses Corporate discounts on a range of services and products, including health insurance, gym memberships, Apple products and much more        About Us: Established in 1991, DWS is a professional Technology Consultancy and part of HCL Technologies. With offices across Australia, we have over 700 employees in Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide, Brisbane and Canberra; providing services to a broad range of blue-chip corporate clients, as well as Federal, State and Local Government agencies. We provide a wide range of services including; IT consulting, managed application services, project management, customer driven innovation, digital transformation, data and business analytics, strategic advisory and productivity, and robotic process automation.   Applicants MUST have Australian Citizenship. The successful person will need to gain and maintain baseline / NV1 security clearance Ready for a new challenge? Click APPLY now! www.dws.com.au

Name: Data Engineer/Consultant
Description: Servian, is an award-winning, regional and global tech consultancy with a rich heritage in Data, DevOps, Digital app dev, Machine Learning and cloud. We embrace innovation, change, and the positive impact it has for us and our clients. All roles at Servian involve personal and technical development pathways which aim to facilitate your career growth. We aim to build an employee experience where you will grow more with us, not be drowned out by the loudest voice, and hence we strive to set you up for a career which will have a greater impact.We are currently looking for talented Data Engineers who are based out of Sydney, to help our clients deliver automation solutions. You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, being involved in implementing strategies and delivering on cloud solutions in Google Cloud, Azure and AWS.Our consultants are natural problem solvers - they are curious, ambitious and experts in their fields.  You will have the opportunity to collaborate and learn from them. You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, working with our clients to understand their needs and to help shape the engagements that allow Servian to provide services that will meet those needs. If you have a passion for learning new technologies, want to be tech agnostic, and work with like minded technologists, Servian is the place to grow your career and have fun in the process!You will be involved in:Development of end to end data pipelines. We are particularly interested in Google Cloud,  Azure, AWS or Snowflake experience.Advising on data architecture, data models, data migration, integration and pipelines and data analysis and visualisation.Implementing solutions for the establishment of data management capabilities including data models and structures, database and data storage infrastructure, master and metadata management, data quality, data integration, data warehousing, data transformation, data analysis and data governance.Development and execution of Data migrations.Supporting pre-sales activity to promote Servian, our capabilities and value to current and prospective clients.You will be:A strong analytical thinker and problem solver with thought leadership and commercial awareness.Experienced building end to end data pipelines using on-premise or cloud based data platforms.Experienced with hands-on delivery of solutions which include databases, advanced SQL and software development in languages such as Python, Scala, Java, TSQL, PL/SQL to name a few.Knowledgeable in relational and big data architectures, data warehousing, data integration, data modelling, data optimisation and data analysis techniques.Interested and knowledgeable in Big Data technologies and Apache ecosystem technologies such as Beam, Spark, Kafka, Hive, Airflow, NiFi, databases, integration, master data management, quality assurance, data wrangling and data governance technologies.Knowledgeable in Cloud Data Warehouse services. Experience in Google BigQuery, Snowflake, AWS Redshift, Azure SQL DWH or Azure Databricks is highly desirable.Experienced with public cloud platforms and cloud infrastructure, which is essential.Exposed to ETL/ELT and governance tools (inc Talend, Informatica, Matillion, FiveTran, IBM Datastage, Collibra)Interested in AI and ML technologies and principles.Able to migrate and transform large, complex datasets from diverse sources, structures and formats, modeled to support analysis for access to quality actionable insights.Why Servian?At Servian we believe talented technologists matter, this means we want to help grow your career and develop your passion in the ever-changing tech industry.Variety of interesting projects, using emerging technologies.Collaborative environment for talented technologists.Continuous learning and development across multiple dimensions including technology, leadership and commerciality.Wellbeing & BenefitsAccess to a wide range of internal training sessions, across both technical and consulting skills.Sponsored certifications across all our partner technology vendors.We provide employees with Life Insurance, Income Protection Insurance and access to an Employee Assistance Program.Generous Parental leave.We are proud to have a sociable workplace that values diversity and celebrates achievement with multiple company-wide, social, and family events throughout the year. Due to Covid-19, all social events are currently virtual.Inclusion & DiversityServian recognises individual differences and welcomes people from a variety of life and work experiences. The diversity of our people is core to our ability to innovate, grow and to fulfil our collective aspiration of helping people to own their tomorrow. A natural curiosity, a respect for differences and a growth mindset are valued at Servian.Our business is focused on developing our people and offerings across the following:Cloud & Technology - Cloud Services (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform), DevOps and Automation inc HashiCorpData & Analytics - BI/DWH, Big Data Analytics, Data Engineering, Data Science and Advanced AnalyticsDigital - Full stack Development, UI/UX Design, Mobile DevelopmentCustomer Engagement - Marketing Campaigns, Campaign Analysis, Customer InsightsArtificial Intelligence - Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Deep LearningCyber Security - DevSecOps, Penetration Testing, Multi-Cloud Security, Security Posture AnalysisIf this role sounds of interest, or you would like to hear about other exciting opportunities get in touch with the Servian Talent Acquisition Team.Applications open from 23.03.22 to 23.04.22

Name: Marketing Manager - Fitness Equipment
Description: Only applications which include a cover letter outlining how you can succeed in this role will be read. VERVE Fitness is an athlete driven fitness brand providing premium fitness equipment for commercial gyms and homes throughout Australia.We are searching for an experienced and self-driven Marketing Manager to join our marketing team. You will be responsible for developing and implementing new marketing strategies to drive growth and brand recognition and lead our marketing efforts by example. About You:Passionate about health and fitness.Passionate about skyrocketing the growth of an already successful brand.Self-driven with a passion for exceeding targets and goals.Want to be part of an exciting Australian company who is growing at a rapid pace on a path to international expansion.A can-do attitude, hardworking approach and ability to make things happen working on their own initiative.Enthusiasm, verve, and a commitment to giving their very best every day to serve our customers.A good sense of humour.  What is VERVE?verve\ ˈvərv \noun1. great energy and enthusiasm, especially in performance2. vigour, vitality and liveliness3. special ability or talentThese are the values of VERVE and they are the reason we exist. Our goal for you is that you bring more of your talent, presence of mind and unique ability into your training and your everyday life. At VERVE we want you to reach higher and push yourself beyond the norm. Quite simply, "good enough", is not part of the VERVE approach. You know there is more you can give and you're ready to unleash it.Sometimes we are taught to seek out compromise. Not us. We don't want you to compromise your health, your performance or your training. We hope you will uncompromisingly push to be your best. Role Responsibility:Set marketing goals and objectives with the Executive TeamPlan, implement and manage marketing strategyContribute to the overall growth of the companyReview and manage content marketing strategy Keep the marketing budget in checkTrack KPIs on a regular basis and present reportsWork with Design, Sales, Procurement and Customer Service teamsCreate and present marketing plans and strategiesUse data and reports to make evidence-based decisionsAnalyse the company's marketing strategy and suggest improvementsStay up to date with the latest technologyStay up to date with the latest best practicesDesign, plan and execute effective marketing campaigns (EDM, Socials, etc.), calendars and launch initiatives The Ideal Candidate Will Have:>3 years experience in marketing management with a demonstrated track record of brand building and growthA customer obsessed approachHands on experience with CRM and SEO tools like Google Analytics, Google Adwords, etc.An in-depth knowledge of big data analysisThe ability to take direction from the CEO and Executive TeamExcellent people, organisational and time management skillsGreat communication and interpersonal skillsExperience with Klaviyo, Later.com, Shopify Plus, Monday.comAbility to take direction and have a growth mindsetYou don't take feedback personally and can see the bigger pictureWe are offering a full-time position with a competitive salary package including superannuation and bonus for on target performance (Salary negotiable based on experience). This is a rewarding opportunity, for an ambitious individual who loves sales and a passion for the Health and Fitness Industry.Only applications which include a cover letter outlining how you can succeed in this role will be read.

Name: Business Intelligence - Graduate Program
Description: The demand for tech talentEvery company understands that their future success relies on innovation such as AI, machine learning, big data and cloud computing. The need to fuel that innovation is creating an unprecedented demand for new and ambitious tech talent. So, if you know that you’re analytical, innovative, and collaborative – a digital career path offers opportunities where your qualities will be highly respected and valued.But while demand is high, so is competition. If you’ve dreamed of turning your passion for tech into a career, the FDM Graduate Career Program can give you the edge. Our long relationships with top-tier client partners allows a foot in the door that can be out of reach to many graduates, giving you the opportunity to add big brands on your CV. From award-winning training to an exciting tech pathwayNo matter what your degree, if you have the attitude and aptitude, FDM can provide you with the skills to fuel a dream career in IT or business. In 2021 alone, we launched the careers of over 2,600 graduates globally.FDM Group is a FTSE 250 employer working with some of the world’s most reputable organisations such as HSBC, KPMG, ANZ and Macquarie.Over a 30+ year history, FDM Group has won many awards. In 2022 FDM has risen 5 places to #16 on the GradConnection Top 100 Graduate Employers and is again one of GradAustralia's Top 100 Graduate Employers.FDM is a company committed to diversity and inclusion, we celebrate difference because we want everyone to have equal opportunity to belong and grow in their career. We are active in creating a more gender-balanced workforce, with circa 33% of our senior management team and 31% of all employees identifying as female.Our program starts with fully-funded training through the FDM Academy, led by our expert training team, to get you job-ready in 6-14 weeks, depending on the career pathway you choose from either the technical or business streams. How is the FDM Business Intelligence Program structured?Your journey will begin with training out of FDM’s Academy. Like all interviews and assessments, this is done remotely in response to Covid-19, to ensure the safety of our community. You will receive the chance to gain industry recognised qualifications, as well as mentoring and support throughout. After successfully completing your training, you’ll have the technical and professional skills you need to step into an integral position with one or more of our industry-leading, multinational clients in Australia during the two-year program. What will I be doing?From Day One as an FDM Business Intelligence Consultant you’ll play a pivotal role in analysing and interpreting data to improve the operations and the performance of your company. Collaborating closely with the IT team, you’ll develop strategies to help the business gain and maintain competitive advantage.Based on your dedicated training you’ll become an expert at using the latest technology or machine learning to gather crucial insights before communicating your analysis to the high-level decision-makers of global businesses.No two days will be alike as you grow with this role - learning how to design and develop analytics tools and platforms to analyse data essential to maximising profitability, productivity and efficiency.Sharing your problem-solving abilities and innovative solutions will not just be personally rewarding but highly regarded by your team. What we are looking for:Bachelor’s degree, STEM major not requiredAn analytical, problem-solving mindsetExcellent communication skills and eagerness to build relationshipsPassion to work within the IT industry & the ambition to succeedAbility to commit to completing our full 2.5-year graduate program – whether eligible under a single visa or as an Australian citizen/permanent residentGeographic flexibility throughout Sydney and Melbourne to support our top-tier clients What we offer you:Fully-funded, industry-recognised training and qualificationsKey skills development e.g. stakeholder management, communication, planning and Microsoft ExcelA foot in the door to some of the world’s most reputable organisationsMentoring and on-going support throughout your entire FDM journeySocial events and networking Give yourself a head start – seize this opportunityThe industry demand for tech talent is so hot, there has never been a better time to launch an exciting IT career. Remember, you don’t need to have studied a STEM subject, what matters is your passion and drive.Our next round of courses is about to take off, so make your application now and give yourself the competitive advantage. The FDM Recruitment team will take you through the process and guide you to the path of your successful tech career.The world is at your fingertips, the possibilities are unlimited - all you have to do is click apply. FDM embraces diversity and encourages applications from people with disability. Candidates will have the opportunity to request support or reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process in order to demonstrate their ability to meet the inherent requirements of the job

Name: Senior Sales Executive (Data and Analytics)
Description: About us:DSpark are leaders in transforming geospatial and temporal mobility data to deliver business value and social impact. We provide powerful insights and capabilities through our products and advanced analytics services to help our clients make better business decisions by understanding how people move, where they go, and what they do. We've even developed products to aid in Australia’s Covid19 efforts.About the role:The best part about this role is the team. You'll work in a supportive environment with great leadership and have an innovative product to sell. Not to mention we're a fast growing scale-up with unlimited potential.On a day to day basis, you'll work with powerful data sets and advanced algorithms to help clients take advantage of new ways of developing insights and adapting strategies based on provable data. Your understanding of the strategic and operational challenges that governments and enterprises face will help you develop unique and valuable solutions via a consultative, data-driven approach.To summarise, this role is for a data evangelist who lives and breathes data; a futurist who can envision solutions that have never been done before; and a hunter with the expertise to develop winning sales strategies. It's for someone who is hungry for success and making a positive impact on society.About you:Previous experience in a similar role both hunting and farming for data sales opportunites across the ANZ region, with well-established professional networks in Australia;A passionate self-starter with a curious mind and collaborative attitude, highly skilled in solution selling and key account management;Tertiary qualified in a Business / Marketing discipline with extensive practical experience in a technical business development or pre-sales role, ideally in the Telco / Big Data / Data Science space;Excellent written and verbal communication skills with the ability to communicate with external agencies / vendors, senior Marketing leaders and C-suite executives;Engaging, with a motivated and sales-driven personality and genuinely passionate about developing new business relationships;Exceptional stakeholder management and interpersonal skills, driven by sales successAbility to provide technical sales consultancy to business leaders and key decision-makers;Able to leverage deep knowledge about the Australian market and build business networks to grow the demand for DSpark products and services. Why join us:At DSpark, we don't sit back and let the future happen to us – we're out there making it. By expanding into new technology and relentlessly improving every day, we're working to create a better tomorrow for all Australians.In addition to making a genuine social and business impact, you'll be part of a team that is invested in your growth. You'll have access to our global learning and development program, be mentored by some of the industry's best and have a worldwide network of career opportunities. We also give you discounts across a range of products, flexible work options, 12 weeks paid parental leave, discounted health insurance, paid volunteer leave, death and disability insurance, compassionate leave, and an outstanding employee assistance program for life's challenging moments.If you'd like to be part of the future of DSpark and our growth journey, please apply now. Other important stuff:We value our people and the communities we serve; being different, diverse and inclusive is important to us. We're also committed to Equal Employment Opportunity Principles and providing reasonable accommodations to all of our applicants. If you need a modification or special assistance to navigate our website or complete your application, please send an email with your request to sanghita.mukherjee@au.ncs-i.com.Applicants will need to have valid work rights for Australia and be willing to undergo background checks, including probity and police checks.

In 2022 FDM has risen 5 places to #16 on the GradConnection Top 100 Graduate Employers and is again one of GradAustralia's Top 100 Graduate Employers.FDM is a company committed to diversity and inclusion, we celebrate difference because we want everyone to have equal opportunity to belong and grow in their career. We are active in creating a more gender-balanced workforce, with circa 33% of our senior management team and 31% of all employees identifying as female.Our program starts with fully-funded training through the FDM Academy, led by our expert training team, to get you job-ready in 6-14 weeks, depending on the career pathway you choose from either the technical or business streams. How is the FDM Business Intelligence Program structured?Your journey will begin with training out of FDM’s Academy. Like all interviews and assessments, this is done remotely in response to Covid-19, to ensure the safety of our community. You will receive the chance to gain industry recognised qualifications, as well as mentoring and support throughout. After successfully completing your training, you’ll have the technical and professional skills you need to step into an integral position with one or more of our industry-leading, multinational clients in Australia during the two-year program. What will I be doing?From Day One as an FDM Business Intelligence Consultant you’ll play a pivotal role in analysing and interpreting data to improve the operations and the performance of your company. Collaborating closely with the IT team, you’ll develop strategies to help the business gain and maintain competitive advantage.Based on your dedicated training you’ll become an expert at using the latest technology or machine learning to gather crucial insights before communicating your analysis to the high-level decision-makers of global businesses.No two days will be alike as you grow with this role - learning how to design and develop analytics tools and platforms to analyse data essential to maximising profitability, productivity and efficiency.Sharing your problem-solving abilities and innovative solutions will not just be personally rewarding but highly regarded by your team. What we are looking for:Bachelor’s degree, STEM major not requiredAn analytical, problem-solving mindsetExcellent communication skills and eagerness to build relationshipsPassion to work within the IT industry & the ambition to succeedAbility to commit to completing our full 2.5-year graduate program – whether eligible under a single visa or as an Australian citizen/permanent residentGeographic flexibility throughout Sydney and Melbourne to support our top-tier clients What we offer you:Fully-funded, industry-recognised training and qualificationsKey skills development e.g. stakeholder management, communication, planning and Microsoft ExcelA foot in the door to some of the world’s most reputable organisationsMentoring and on-going support throughout your entire FDM journeySocial events and networking Give yourself a head start – seize this opportunityThe industry demand for tech talent is so hot, there has never been a better time to launch an exciting IT career. Remember, you don’t need to have studied a STEM subject, what matters is your passion and drive.Our next round of courses is about to take off, so make your application now and give yourself the competitive advantage. The FDM Recruitment team will take you through the process and guide you to the path of your successful tech career.The world is at your fingertips, the possibilities are unlimited - all you have to do is click apply. FDM embraces diversity and encourages applications from people with disability. Candidates will have the opportunity to request support or reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process in order to demonstrate their ability to meet the inherent requirements of the job

Name: Data Modeller / Curator
Description:
Location:  Broadmeadows
Role Type: Full Time Fixed, Ongoing
Remuneration: $118,731.75 - $122,293.70 + superannuation (based on qualifications and experience)
 
About the Role:
Reporting to the Director of Strategy, Architecture, Risk and Compliance the Data Modeller/Curator is responsible for developing the Data Catalog, Data Dictionary and Data Security layer for Bendigo Kangan Institutes Business Intelligence Platform.
The role will lead the Data Modelling and Curate data on our data-lake/warehouse, information management systems and AI capabilities as part of Bendigo Kangan Institutes Strategy and Enterprise Digital Plan. This is a specialist ongoing role and is critical to the implementation and ongoing maintenance of the Big Data store providing a "single source of truth" to the enterprise reporting and executive decision support.
You will be part of a close-knit team of five (5), that operate in an agile fashion. The team connects daily and openly support each other. As the team plays an integral part of Bendigo Kangan Institutes digital transformation, they are high performers and are delivery focused.
To be successful in this role, you will need demonstrated experience in conceptual and physical data modelling, data architecture, data warehousing technologies and practices and experience leading and implementing continuous improvement across an organisation.
We are excited about you because you have:

 A tertiary Degree in Data Analytics / IT or similar field
Experience using Enterprise grade business glossary and Data Catalog


Extensive experience in statistics and/or mathematics with a strong knowledge of statistical data modelling techniques
Demonstrated experience in data modelling, data architecture and data warehousing technologies and practices
Strong communication skills (written and verbal)
Ability to take ownership of work-related tasks and projects
Advanced Architecture Framework judgement
Strategic agility
Ability to prioritise issues in accordance with business impacts
Ability to collaborate across a team and build strong partnerships
Excellent stakeholder management skills (internal and External)
Drive to deliver results and outcomes

Why work for us?
We can offer you

A competitive remuneration package
Free onsite parking for most campuses
Novated car leasing
Access to services within and outside our campuses

Discounted services at some of our Metro campuses
Commuter Club Program
Travel Deals through Flight Centre Leisure Club

Professional development programs held weekly
Peer recognition program

Things we will require from you a little later...

A current Working with Children Check (obtained at own cost)
A current National Police Check (obtained at own cost)
Certified Right to Work document - Passport/Visa/Citizenship or Birth Certificate
COVID Vaccination Certificate.

To be appointed to the role the successful candidate will be required to provide evidence that they are fully vaccinated or provide a signed and completed Australian Immunisation Register immunisation medical exemption form to confirm that they are an exempted person in accordance with the Victorian Government's COVID-19 Mandatory Vaccination Directions.
 About us:
Bendigo Kangan Institute are the TAFE trading brands of Bendigo TAFE and Kangan Institute. As one of Victoria's largest TAFE providers, we want to stand out from the crowd with our state-of-the-art training centres offering a wide range of courses in a variety of fields. 
VETASSESS and eWorks are also part of our wider organisation. VETASSESS is Australia's leading assessment partner and eWorks designs, builds and supports online learning.
We want to make a real difference for our students and communities, and we give people the opportunity to be the best they can be each day. We are a flexible, innovative, and dynamic place of learning and working with a rich multicultural atmosphere. Our mission is to empower people and industry with the skills to create a bright future.
 
If this sounds like the role for you. Please click 'Apply for this job/Apply now', we would love to hear from you.
 
For further information regarding this outstanding opportunity, please contact Devendra Nambiar, Head of Technology Strategy, Architecture Risk and Compliance via dnambiar@kangan.edu.au
Position description can be viewed at :https://www.kangan.edu.au/information-and-resources/jobs 
Applications from candidates with valid working rights will only be considered.  We are a child safe and equal opportunity employer and therefore the successful candidate will be required to hold a current working with children check clearance. We value diversity in our workforce and encourage people from all backgrounds, abilities, and identities to apply for roles within our organisation.  If you require specific support to apply for this position, please contact peopleoperations@kangan.edu.au and we will work with you to identify the best way to assist. 
NOTE: BKI reserves the right to withdraw this advertised position at any stage.

Name: Business Analyst - Data Engineering Background
Description: The Company:Is a Top-Tier International Investment Bank head-quartered in Sydney. The bank has recently embarked on a large scale, bank-wide (5 year) Digital Transformation Initiative. The four mail pillars of the transformation are: Simplification = Consolidating similar systems that do the same thing Automation = eradicating needless manual processes wherever possibleDigitisation = modernising all of their client facing front ends (new responsive technologies) Data = utilising big data tools for more efficient and effect reporting & analytics The Project:As part of this program of work, the bank plans to build an innovative and future-ready Data Platform that will help the various capital markets business areas meet their customer’s needs, be regulatory compliant and be able to confidently translate and use their data.This team will take ownership of all data across all financial product groups, they will focus on data-gathering, analysis and then visualisation to the business areas.The Role:As a data-focused Business Analyst, you will help shape and deliver the bank's next generation Big Data/Data Analytics platforms.With a strong engineering background, you will be comfortable working alongside an agile team of engineers, data scientists, analysts, business, and technology stakeholders with a key focus on outlining the data road map that will support and service project stakeholders.What you will bring to the team:  A strong technical background - with Data Engineering experience (warehousing, modelling and pipelines) Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills Ability to work hands-on alongside a team of data professionals, vendors, and business stakeholders Proven experience gathering/eliciting/validating/documenting business requirements to design and deliver outcomes.   As well as the use of new and emerging technologies, embarking on large-scale transformative projects, the bank pride themselves on their work environment - which includes a healthy work/life balance (with over 80% of employees able to work from home), an 'engineering first' culture which favours technologists and their ways of working as well as on site cafes with complementary food and drinks.

Name: Software Engineer
Description: Job Title: Software EngineerReports to: Chief Technology OfficerSalary: A market competitive package including participation in The Yield’s employee share options planHours: Full TimeLocation: Sydney/Hybrid working About usThe Yield is hiring! Come join us as we change the face of agtech and help feed the world without wrecking the planet.We’re an agricultural technology company on a mission to transform food and farming practices with scalable digital technology.We use real time data and AI to power our technology to solve real challenges at farm level and throughout the food chain.We help commercial growers, input providers and marketers make faster, more informed decisions that impact yield and reduce risk. We do this by providing an integrated set of agtech solutions that sense, analyse and predict on-farm growing conditions, and then deliver information in a usable, insightful format.The Yield technology combines hardware, data analytics and user-friendly apps. Our agtech solutions can be applied across the food chain to help customers to drive profits and sustainability, scale faster and reduce risk. We help our customers to #growbetter.We are on the brink of global stardom! We are growing our team and expanding our presence globally. This year we commenced our launch into overseas markets with our Founder and CEO, Ros Harvey, spending much of her time in the US developing customer and investor networks and building our US team. Our VisionOur vision is to feed the world without wrecking the planet. We plan to do this through sustainable food production with AI-driven decision making on farm and along the supply chain adjusting in real time for weather. We aim to be the essential data and AI platform for large corporate growers in speciality crops globally.The world needs to produce 60% more food by 2050 to feed the planet at a time of unprecedented resource constraints. We aim to be a global leader in intelligent solutions in the food industry.The Yield has a highly focused team combining leading engineers, data scientists, agriculturists and technologists.We partner with some of the global giants of technology services like Bosch, Yamaha Motor Company and Microsoft. We have a deep commitment to open innovation, collaboration, and diversity. A core value is that we work with the best and share the rewards.Our Founder and CEO has spent her lifetime promoting inclusion and diversity at work. Our business is committed to creating the right culture, systems and flexibility for everyone regardless of gender, race, ethnicity, disability or sexual orientation to thrive and reach their full potential. We were awarded the Australian Information Industry Association (AIIA) inaugural #TechDiversity award in 2016 in recognition of our achievements. Check out our videos on our corporate values. RoleWe’re looking for a talented and passionate Software Engineer who will be responsible for designing and delivering high quality code in a timely manner.The Software Engineer at The Yield will work with the CTO, Software Engineering and Data Science teams to deliver amazing new features and take our product to the next level. You will be a part of a highly creative, agile, human centred development team who values your happiness, growth and personal development.You’ll be a highly motivated systems thinker who is exceptional at what you do. However, you're still eager to grow and hone in on your skill. You will work with an awesome engineering team who will guide you to take on more responsibility as you learn and grow within the organisation. You will also be someone who considers the customer impact when making decisions and has a real appetite for learning and growing, both as an individual and teammate. ResponsibilitiesThere's no typical working week at The Yield, but here are some of the things you might be working on, day-to-day:Development, release, and maintenance of our applications according to business needs.Design systems that focus on performance, scalability and stability.Build and deploy infrastructure to support the applications.Break down tough problems into simple, and elegant solutionsWork in a team of software engineers, data science engineers and DevOps engineersFollow and contribute towards engineering and design guidelines for developing highly scalable, available and fault tolerant systems.Be an example for thorough, meaningful code reviewsMentor less experienced members of the team and reviewing the work of peers.Ensure continuous improvement and development, keeping up with and leveraging new breakthroughs and advances in Machine learning, AI and Deep learningContribute to a cohesive, diverse, and high-performing team that is genuinely inclusive and gender-balancedEstablish good internal and external relationships, communicate verbally and in writing with key stakeholdersBe flexible and work independently - we need people who will do whatever it takes to get the job done.SkillsTo be successful in this role you will have:Minimum 2+ years of strong coding experience in PythonHands on experience designing and building REST APIs and managing the inherent challengesStrong knowledge and experience of Cloud Technologies (Azure / AWS)Knowledge of Big Data Concepts such as NoSQL databasesExperience building scalable and high performance systemsUnderstanding of design patterns across back-end and integrationGood understanding on Version control tools; Git and Git workflowsDemonstrated working knowledge of CI/CD (Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment)Strong organisational, communication and collaboration skills to build and strengthen working relationshipsExperience in leading development following Agile/Scrum framework with knowledge across agile concepts and methodologiesAbility to thrive in a dynamic and fast-paced environment of product discovery and developmentAbility to take ownership and work independentlyPositive, proactive mindset that is passionate about succeeding and expanding your skillsetSkills that are desired but not essential:.NET Core 2 & 3 (and upgrading from 2 to 3)Entity Framework knowledgeWorking with Cosmos and EventHub QualificationsTo be successful in this role you are likely to have:• Bachelor or Masters degree in Computer Science or a related field• Equivalent skills through experience and on the job learning More about usWe are looking for talented people who share our passion and hire on both skills and values. We are a truly diverse company and actively strive to be an industry leader in building inclusive technology teams. We offer a supportive and flexible working environment, including giving our staff the tools needed to work remotely.Check out our LinkedIn company page for further details.Enquiries: recruitment@theyield.com

Name: Lead Engineer
Description:
Lead Engineer (Data)
Data Platforms 
Sydney Based, Permanent Role 

How will I help?
The Lead Engineer (Data) will contribute to the data and technology strategy for value creation through our data products and assets. The Lead Engineer will lead a talented team of Engineers across Westpac and partner resources  for enabling business objectives to be delivered efficiently and effectively keeping our Engineering Delivery Teams at the forefront of industry evolution in software and data engineering, data science and machine learning concepts, practices, and technologies. We are surrounded by data, but often starved of insights – your job is to change that.
As the Lead engineer in the Data Strategy and Products Analytics area, you will be co-creating a roadmap to bring data to life for the organisation and to enable the federated use of data and insight products. You are unlocking the value of data and insights through technical practise, methodical research, high level design and information radiation across all technologists and data professionals in data strategy and products area.
What you will do
As a member of the Data Strategy and product analytics team contribute to data engineering best practices, standards and guidelines to enable build of Enterprise Data Products.
Actively partner with divisional, data and enterprise Architecture functions to create data product design and engineering roadmaps and promote through the relevant Design Authorities
Work in collaboration with the Chief engineers and Line-of Business Service Owner (Leads) to engineer and build Enterprise Data Products
Coordinate the planning and execution of Proof of Concepts in close collaboration with the Data Platforms Engineering and Data Architecture functions
Create and update Capability Maturity assessments across existing and emerging Data Products using the Scorecard to inform when to invest, maintain and when to retire
Demonstrate and communicate with Divisional Technologists and Business Partners the business and customer value of the Data Products and Services offered by Data Platforms
Engage closely with the Data Engineering Practice and Data Science COE to ensure regular assessment and alignment of process and practice maturity
Assess and understand the evolving requirements of Data Engineers, Data Scientists, Data Citizens, and other Data Professionals around the Division to ensure their experience in achieving their day-to-day outcomes is optimal – be an advocate for data professionals

What’s in it for me?
Joining Westpac has many benefits besides building a long and stable career. You’ll be able to purchase leave to facilitate your dreams or obligations and you’ll be encouraged to participate in the community through paid volunteer leave and secondments. You’ll also be entitled to a suite of online learning, training modules and career planning tools to grow with us. 
What do I need? 
Demonstrated engineering experience leading and contributing to agile teams of Engineers, Data Analysts and technical professionals
Advanced knowledge of Data Products /Data Mesh and modern Data Technologies including relational data, semi/unstructured data, and machine learning libraries/technologies
Advanced knowledge and implementation experience of Data Lakehouse on Public Cloud Services (Azure PaaS services preferred) and their usage and implementation across a complex data ecosystem
Excellent proficiency in Data Engineering framework and templates in Big Data and Cloud environments and designing as well as building CICD pipelines
Experience developing Data Models, Architectural Designs, Patterns and Roadmaps in a Data context

What is it like to work in Westpac?
We aim to provide one big, supportive team to help us reach our vision to become one of the world’s great service companies. Working with us you'll discover new ways of working, and an exciting range of roles to showcase your skills. As an equal opportunity employer, we’re proud to have created a culture where people can be their best, in an environment that values diversity and flexibility. And one where everyone belongs. 
How do I Apply?
Start here. Just click on the APPLY button.
As part of our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, this role is open to experienced candidates seeking a discussion around workplace flexibility. We invite candidates of all ages, people with a disability and Indigenous Australians to apply. The health and wellbeing of our employees is our top priority. We’ve developed clear standards to ensure our people are confident, safe and healthy whether they’re working from a Westpac Group site or working from home. These are based on expert medical advice and Safe Work Australia guidelines.
The Westpac Group has implemented an Entry to Workplace Policy that requires employees and others entering our workplaces to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 by relevant dates set out in the policy (subject to applicable medical exemptions). Our employees are required to comply with the policy regardless of whether they are in customer-facing or non-customer-facing roles (as employees in non-customer-facing roles are required to attend the workplace under our Hybrid Working Strategy). Further, the Westpac Group is required to comply with State/Territory issued public health orders/directions which require relevant workers to be vaccinated against COVID-19 to enter workplaces.
By applying for this role, you acknowledge that you are aware of our Entry to Workplace Policy, and if you secure employment with us, you will be required to comply with the policy.

Name: Data Engineer
Description: Data Engineer About this opportunityTechnology People have partnered with a homegrown Australian business who is now looking for a Data Engineer to develop and maintain their data pipelines. The role will also have a strong focus on utilisation of Power BI.  Our client works in small teams that use Agile methodology to keep up in a fast-paced business environment within Service Delivery Organization, they also closely cooperate with Ericsson SON PDU, customer units.  What you will do  Design data structures, develop data processing pipelines and prepare data Use large data sets to address business issues, deliver updates to stakeholders based on analytics, and support business needs Present data in a visually appealing manner using Power BI  You will bring  Relevant data engineering background Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or Systems (a Master’s Degree is preferred) Proficiency in modern programming language (Python, SQL etc.) Hands-on experience in designing, implementing, and maintaining data pipelines in an event-driven, microservices-based distributed landscape Understanding methodologies such as continuous integration and continuous delivery  It's a huge plus if you have  Experience in working with AWS, Azure, or GCP cloud providers Experience with Big Data technologies, stream processing (e.g.: Hadoop, Kafka) Ability and willingness to quickly adopt new technologies and/or business domains Experience in Telecommunication Industry, particularly in SON space

Name: Software Developer
Description: Brand new and exciting Junior Development Opportunities for passionate and driven candidates!  $110,000 - 135,000 + Super  What you'll get in returnCompetitive SalariesStock Options - be rewarded for contribution to the company's successStart-Up CultureSignificant fast track career growth - as the company grows you growGain experience in the hottest IT segment - Data & AnalyticsFlexible working locationPotential for international travel as we open offices around the world Your new company Your new organisation is a world-leading analytical data virtualisation solution company, and we passionate about being at the forefront of the analytics technology field. Enjoy the benefits of a Start-up culture - fast paced and dynamic, innovative, results driven, with a down to earth team who is supportive and collaborative.
