Name: Data Engineer/Consultant
Description: Servian, is an award-winning, regional and global tech consultancy with a rich heritage in Data, DevOps, Digital app dev, Machine Learning and cloud. We embrace innovation, change, and the positive impact it has for us and our clients. All roles at Servian involve personal and technical development pathways which aim to facilitate your career growth. We aim to build an employee experience where you will grow more with us, not be drowned out by the loudest voice, and hence we strive to set you up for a career which will have a greater impact.We are currently looking for talented Data Engineers who are based out of Sydney, to help our clients deliver automation solutions. You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, being involved in implementing strategies and delivering on cloud solutions in Google Cloud, Azure and AWS.Our consultants are natural problem solvers - they are curious, ambitious and experts in their fields.  You will have the opportunity to collaborate and learn from them. You will be working on exciting and interesting projects, working with our clients to understand their needs and to help shape the engagements that allow Servian to provide services that will meet those needs. If you have a passion for learning new technologies, want to be tech agnostic, and work with like minded technologists, Servian is the place to grow your career and have fun in the process!You will be involved in:Development of end to end data pipelines. We are particularly interested in Google Cloud,  Azure, AWS or Snowflake experience.Advising on data architecture, data models, data migration, integration and pipelines and data analysis and visualisation.Implementing solutions for the establishment of data management capabilities including data models and structures, database and data storage infrastructure, master and metadata management, data quality, data integration, data warehousing, data transformation, data analysis and data governance.Development and execution of Data migrations.Supporting pre-sales activity to promote Servian, our capabilities and value to current and prospective clients.You will be:A strong analytical thinker and problem solver with thought leadership and commercial awareness.Experienced building end to end data pipelines using on-premise or cloud based data platforms.Experienced with hands-on delivery of solutions which include databases, advanced SQL and software development in languages such as Python, Scala, Java, TSQL, PL/SQL to name a few.Knowledgeable in relational and big data architectures, data warehousing, data integration, data modelling, data optimisation and data analysis techniques.Interested and knowledgeable in Big Data technologies and Apache ecosystem technologies such as Beam, Spark, Kafka, Hive, Airflow, NiFi, databases, integration, master data management, quality assurance, data wrangling and data governance technologies.Knowledgeable in Cloud Data Warehouse services. Experience in Google BigQuery, Snowflake, AWS Redshift, Azure SQL DWH or Azure Databricks is highly desirable.Experienced with public cloud platforms and cloud infrastructure, which is essential.Exposed to ETL/ELT and governance tools (inc Talend, Informatica, Matillion, FiveTran, IBM Datastage, Collibra)Interested in AI and ML technologies and principles.Able to migrate and transform large, complex datasets from diverse sources, structures and formats, modeled to support analysis for access to quality actionable insights.Why Servian?At Servian we believe talented technologists matter, this means we want to help grow your career and develop your passion in the ever-changing tech industry.Variety of interesting projects, using emerging technologies.Collaborative environment for talented technologists.Continuous learning and development across multiple dimensions including technology, leadership and commerciality.Wellbeing & BenefitsAccess to a wide range of internal training sessions, across both technical and consulting skills.Sponsored certifications across all our partner technology vendors.We provide employees with Life Insurance, Income Protection Insurance and access to an Employee Assistance Program.Generous Parental leave.We are proud to have a sociable workplace that values diversity and celebrates achievement with multiple company-wide, social, and family events throughout the year. Due to Covid-19, all social events are currently virtual.Inclusion & DiversityServian recognises individual differences and welcomes people from a variety of life and work experiences. The diversity of our people is core to our ability to innovate, grow and to fulfil our collective aspiration of helping people to own their tomorrow. A natural curiosity, a respect for differences and a growth mindset are valued at Servian.Our business is focused on developing our people and offerings across the following:Cloud & Technology - Cloud Services (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform), DevOps and Automation inc HashiCorpData & Analytics - BI/DWH, Big Data Analytics, Data Engineering, Data Science and Advanced AnalyticsDigital - Full stack Development, UI/UX Design, Mobile DevelopmentCustomer Engagement - Marketing Campaigns, Campaign Analysis, Customer InsightsArtificial Intelligence - Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Deep LearningCyber Security - DevSecOps, Penetration Testing, Multi-Cloud Security, Security Posture AnalysisIf this role sounds of interest, or you would like to hear about other exciting opportunities get in touch with the Servian Talent Acquisition Team.Applications open from 23.03.22 to 23.04.22

Name: Data Engineer | Python - Great Opportunity to Learn ML Ops!
Description: Our client - a leading consulting enterprise in the Analytics, AI & machine learning domain - urgently require multiple engineers to join their practice on a permanent basis (Sydney or Melbourne locations)This is a fantastic opportunity for an ambitious engineering/programmer looking to get into ML Ops. The role would ideally suit Python developers or Data engineers looking to transition into AWS MLS Ops. You will "learn on the job" receiving extensive guidance and tuition for senior engineers, already highly versed in ML Ops. The successful candidates will work on preparing and deploying ML models, which includes working closely with data scientists, data engineers and the business to understand the data and model deployment requirements. In this role, the candidate will apply creativity and problem-solving skills to make massive amounts of data available for the machine learning platform. Requirements:  3 + years experience in python programming or data engineering experience  Some exposure (or desire to learn) AWS based ML OPS OR Devops, alternatively Data Engineering experience with ML environments Proficiency in Python, SQL and at least one big data language (Spark,Hadoop,Flume), comfortable in cloud platforms (AWS), git and CICD concepts. Desire to learn or hands on experience in all aspects of data processing, including data warehouse architecture/modelling and ETL processing knowledge or desire to learn AWS compatible ML Technologies – AWS - Sage maker, Tensorflow, Amazon ML Feature Store A results-oriented mind-set with strong analytical skills and problem-solving ability Strong interpersonal skills and ability to communicate clearly and effectively Strong communicator  Keen and ambitious learner   Responsibilities & Deliverables:Working under the tutelage and guidance of senior team members to:  Build and maintain data pipelines to serve ML models. Deploy prediction and reporting decision-making tools that serve business needs. Handle various ad hoc requests and debug projects. Interact with data engineering and data science teams to identify the requirements for model deployment. Help instantiate a robust CICD for all deployed ML models.  Perks & Benefits:  Hybrid work model - WFH in part with some time onsite Excellent career growth prospects & internal promotion opportunities Work closely with proven experience senior consultants for on the job up-skilling & learning  Join an organisation with a glass-door rating of 4+ who achieve client NPS of 9/10! A collaborative work environment, exceptional training, and career development Established, respected client of the most admired fortune 500 companies globally  Interested parties please apple now for a confidential initial conversation.

Name: Business Analysis & Business Intelligence - Graduate Program
Description: The demand for tech talentEvery company understands that their future success relies on innovation such as AI, machine learning, big data and cloud computing. The need to fuel that innovation is creating an unprecedented demand for new and ambitious tech talent. So, if you know that you’re analytical, innovative, and collaborative – a digital career path offers opportunities where your qualities will be highly respected and valued.But while demand is high, so is competition. If you’ve dreamed of turning your passion for tech into a career, the FDM Graduate Career Program can give you the edge. Our long relationships with top-tier client partners allows a foot in the door that can be out of reach to many graduates, giving you the opportunity to add big brands on your CV. From award-winning training to an exciting tech pathwayNo matter what your degree, if you have the attitude and aptitude, FDM can provide you with the skills to fuel a dream career in IT or business. In 2021 alone, we launched the careers of over 2,600 graduates globally.FDM Group is a FTSE 250 employer working with some of the world’s most reputable organisations such as HSBC, KPMG, ANZ and Macquarie.Over a 30+ year history, FDM Group has won many awards. In 2022 FDM has risen 5 places to #16 on the GradConnection Top 100 Graduate Employers and is again one of GradAustralia's Top 100 Graduate Employers.FDM is a company committed to diversity and inclusion, we celebrate difference because we want everyone to have equal opportunity to belong and grow in their career. We are active in creating a more gender-balanced workforce, with circa 33% of our senior management team and 31% of all employees identifying as female.Our program starts with fully-funded training through the FDM Academy, led by our expert training team, to get you job-ready in 6-14 weeks, depending on the career pathway you choose from either the technical or business streams. How is the FDM Business Intelligence Program structured?Your journey will begin with training out of FDM’s Academy. Like all interviews and assessments, this is done remotely in response to Covid-19, to ensure the safety of our community. You will receive the chance to gain industry recognised qualifications, as well as mentoring and support throughout. After successfully completing your training, you’ll have the technical and professional skills you need to step into an integral position with one or more of our industry-leading, multinational clients in Australia during the two-year program. What will I be doing?From Day One as an FDM Business Intelligence Consultant you’ll play a pivotal role in analysing and interpreting data to improve the operations and the performance of your company. Collaborating closely with the IT team, you’ll develop strategies to help the business gain and maintain competitive advantage.Based on your dedicated training you’ll become an expert at using the latest technology or machine learning to gather crucial insights before communicating your analysis to the high-level decision-makers of global businesses.No two days will be alike as you grow with this role - learning how to design and develop analytics tools and platforms to analyse data essential to maximising profitability, productivity and efficiency.Sharing your problem-solving abilities and innovative solutions will not just be personally rewarding but highly regarded by your team. What we are looking for:Bachelor’s degree, STEM major not requiredAn analytical, problem-solving mindsetExcellent communication skills and eagerness to build relationshipsPassion to work within the IT industry & the ambition to succeedAbility to commit to completing our full 2.5-year graduate program – whether eligible under a single visa or as an Australian citizen/permanent residentGeographic flexibility throughout Sydney and Melbourne to support our top-tier clients What we offer you:Fully-funded, industry-recognised training and qualificationsKey skills development e.g. stakeholder management, communication, planning and Microsoft ExcelA foot in the door to some of the world’s most reputable organisationsMentoring and on-going support throughout your entire FDM journeySocial events and networking Give yourself a head start – seize this opportunityThe industry demand for tech talent is so hot, there has never been a better time to launch an exciting IT career. Remember, you don’t need to have studied a STEM subject, what matters is your passion and drive.Our next round of courses is about to take off, so make your application now and give yourself the competitive advantage. The FDM Recruitment team will take you through the process and guide you to the path of your successful tech career.The world is at your fingertips, the possibilities are unlimited - all you have to do is click apply. FDM embraces diversity and encourages applications from people with disability. Candidates will have the opportunity to request support or reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process in order to demonstrate their ability to meet the inherent requirements of the job.

Name: Marketing Analyst
Description: Brighter Futures Start hereAs Australia's biggest and most loved retailer, we've been brightening up everyday life for families for over 50 years. At our stores, distribution centres, and offices in Australia and New Zealand. All around the globe. Our diverse and inclusive 47,000 strong team come together for a common cause. Giving families easy access to our on-trend products and incredibly low prices - it's the heart of everything we do.As a leader in the retail market, we're optimistic about our future and yours. We're relentless in our pursuit for results, but changing at a rapid rate, giving you challenging work that you'll be proud of. We celebrate your uniqueness and individuality. Because at Kmart it's not just what you do, it's who you are that makes everyday living brighter. Join the teamWe have an exciting opportunity for enthusiastic data analytics professionals to join the newly established centralised Customer Insights and Analytics unit. The Customer Insights and Analytics unit allows us to build a deeper understanding of Kmart's customer behaviour and drive customer-centric decision making throughout the organisation.This role will be a part of Customer Analytics team working closely with Kmart's marketing and digital engagement teams to measure the impact of our campaigns and optimise them.  What will I do?As a Marketing Analyst you will: Drive the adoption and use of data and analytics in customer marketing initiatives by developing processes for analysis and activation by bringing together data scattered across the marketing stack and data warehouses Create strategic recommendations that will shape future customer focused marketing activity and provide tactical inputs to the campaign development process by presenting past learnings in whiteboard forums Perform exploratory analysis to uncover opportunities for campaign optimisation and customer value delivery Provide intelligent and value add analysis by leveraging techniques that may include;  complex business logic and conceptual design, customer insights and segmentation, propensity modelling, control group creation/testing, real time decisioning and ROI analysis   Create compelling, intuitive dashboards to enable the business with critical metrics, with a focus on data automation, anomaly detection, and actionable data visualisation Manage delivery of insights by coordinating across business stakeholders as well as onsite and offshore analytics team members  What do I need to be successful? Bachelor's degree (ideally in a quantitative field like Computer Science, Engineering, Statistics, or Mathematics) with coding ability Strong SQL skills are mandatory while Python or R programming skills are helpful to work with large volumes of customer data and extract insights Familiarity with data visualization tools (e.g. PowerBI, Tableau) and experience working with enterprise data warehouses including Big Data and Cloud technologies (e.g. AWS, Teradata) Prior experience in a ‘hands-on' data analytics role Retail or e-commerce experience, with the ability to think outside the box, apply business logic, and develop bespoke analytical solutions Ability to foster strong and impactful relationships with team members, the wider analytics organisation and business stakeholders Clear and concise communication style, flexible to suit relevant audience  What's in it for me? Flexible working through our Flex Where, Flex When, Flex Well policy. This role can suit you, with a combination of working from home, on the road, in stores and occasionally in Kmart's National Office in Mulgrave! A dynamic learning and support program Competitive remuneration A discount card for Kmart, Target, Officeworks and Bunnings, plus other benefits An inclusive, fun recognition program A bonus program (where eligible) Development opportunities across Kmart Group (comprised of Kmart, Target and Catch) as well as the broader Wesfarmers Group. Wesfarmers Share Plan access (where eligible)  What's it like to work there? At Kmart, we celebrate the rich diversity of the communities in which we operate and are committed to creating inclusive and safe environments where all our team members can contribute and succeed. We believe that all team members should feel valued, respected and safe irrespective of your gender, ethnicity, indigeneity, religious beliefs, education, age, disability, family responsibilities, sexual orientation and gender identity and we encourage applications from all candidates. We believe that everyone should have the opportunity to do well when applying or working at Kmart, therefore we encourage you to share any feedback by emailing diversity@kmart.com.au if you would like any adjustments. If you would like to explore a career with Kmart and this sounds like the perfect role for you - apply now!

Name: Cloud Consultant, Data, Analytics, Google Cloud Professional Services
Description: Individuals applying for this position will not be eligible for immigration sponsorship.At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google’s technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan(https://reconciliationactionplan.withgoogle.com/) for more information.Note: By applying to this position you will have an opportunity to share your preferred working location from the following: Sydney NSW, Australia; Melbourne VIC, Australia.Minimum qualifications:Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.5 years of experience project managing and delivering technical solutions.Experience architecting, designing, and deploying distributed data processing systems with one or more open source technologies.Experience in technical consulting delivery for data solutions in cloud environments.Preferred qualifications:MBA or Master's degree in Computer Science or Engineering field.Cloud certification.7 years of experience demonstrating technical client service.Experience with reading software code in one or more languages such as Java, JavaScript, or Python.Experience designing and deploying large scale distributed data processing systems with one or more technologies such as Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Cassandra, Redis, Hadoop, Spark, HBase, Vertica, Netezza, Teradata, Tableau, or MicroStrategy.Experience devising migration approach, and migrating on prem data processing systems to cloud.About the jobGoogle Cloud helps employees and organizations empower their employees, serve their customers, and build what’s next for their business — all with technology built in the cloud. Our products are engineered for security, reliability, and scalability, managing the full-stack from infrastructure to applications to devices and hardware. Our teams are dedicated to helping our customers — developers, small and large businesses, educational institutions and government agencies — see the benefits of our technology come to life.As a Cloud Consultant for Data and Analytics, you will work directly with Google’s customers on critical projects to help them transform their businesses. You will provide management, consulting and technical aptitude to customer engagements while working with client executives and key technical leaders to deploy solutions via Google’s Cloud Platform.You will also work closely with key Google partners currently servicing accounts to manage programs, deliver consulting services, and provide technical guidance and best practice expertise.You will travel 30% of the time for client engagements.Google Cloud accelerates organizations’ ability to digitally transform their business with the best infrastructure, platform, industry solutions and expertise. We deliver enterprise-grade solutions that leverage Google’s cutting-edge technology – all on the cleanest cloud in the industry. Customers in more than 200 countries and territories turn to Google Cloud as their trusted partner to enable growth and solve their most critical business problems.ResponsibilitiesWork with customer technical leads, client executives, and partners to manage and deliver successful implementations of cloud solutions becoming a trusted advisor to decision makers throughout the engagement.Work with internal specialists, product and engineering teams to package best practices and lessons learned into thought leadership, methodologies, and published assets.Interact with sales, partners, and customer technical stakeholders to manage project scope, priorities, deliverables, risks/issues, and timelines for successful client outcomes.Advocate for customer needs in order to overcome adoption blockers and drive new feature development based on your field experience.Propose solution architectures and manage the deployment of cloud based big data and analytics solutions according to complex customer requirements and implementation best practices.Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing our Accommodations for Applicants form.To all recruitment agencies: Google does not accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Google employees or any other organization location. Google is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.To learn more about US requirements around COVID vaccination requirements for Google workspaces, read our Vaccination Entry Policy.

Name: Cloud Consultant, Data, Analytics, Google Cloud Professional Services
Description: Individuals applying for this position will not be eligible for immigration sponsorship.At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google’s technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan(https://reconciliationactionplan.withgoogle.com/) for more information.Note: By applying to this position you will have an opportunity to share your preferred working location from the following: Sydney NSW, Australia; Melbourne VIC, Australia.Minimum qualifications:Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.5 years of experience project managing and delivering technical solutions.Experience architecting, designing, and deploying distributed data processing systems with one or more open source technologies.Experience in technical consulting delivery for data solutions in cloud environments.Preferred qualifications:MBA or Master's degree in Computer Science or Engineering field.Cloud certification.7 years of experience demonstrating technical client service.Experience with reading software code in one or more languages such as Java, JavaScript, or Python.Experience designing and deploying large scale distributed data processing systems with one or more technologies such as Oracle, SQL Server, MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Cassandra, Redis, Hadoop, Spark, HBase, Vertica, Netezza, Teradata, Tableau, or MicroStrategy.Experience devising migration approach, and migrating on prem data processing systems to cloud.About the jobGoogle Cloud helps employees and organizations empower their employees, serve their customers, and build what’s next for their business — all with technology built in the cloud. Our products are engineered for security, reliability, and scalability, managing the full-stack from infrastructure to applications to devices and hardware. Our teams are dedicated to helping our customers — developers, small and large businesses, educational institutions and government agencies — see the benefits of our technology come to life.As a Cloud Consultant for Data and Analytics, you will work directly with Google’s customers on critical projects to help them transform their businesses. You will provide management, consulting and technical aptitude to customer engagements while working with client executives and key technical leaders to deploy solutions via Google’s Cloud Platform.You will also work closely with key Google partners currently servicing accounts to manage programs, deliver consulting services, and provide technical guidance and best practice expertise.You will travel 30% of the time for client engagements.Google Cloud accelerates organizations’ ability to digitally transform their business with the best infrastructure, platform, industry solutions and expertise. We deliver enterprise-grade solutions that leverage Google’s cutting-edge technology – all on the cleanest cloud in the industry. Customers in more than 200 countries and territories turn to Google Cloud as their trusted partner to enable growth and solve their most critical business problems.ResponsibilitiesWork with customer technical leads, client executives, and partners to manage and deliver successful implementations of cloud solutions becoming a trusted advisor to decision makers throughout the engagement.Work with internal specialists, product and engineering teams to package best practices and lessons learned into thought leadership, methodologies, and published assets.Interact with sales, partners, and customer technical stakeholders to manage project scope, priorities, deliverables, risks/issues, and timelines for successful client outcomes.Advocate for customer needs in order to overcome adoption blockers and drive new feature development based on your field experience.Propose solution architectures and manage the deployment of cloud based big data and analytics solutions according to complex customer requirements and implementation best practices.Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing our Accommodations for Applicants form.To all recruitment agencies: Google does not accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Google employees or any other organization location. Google is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.To learn more about US requirements around COVID vaccination requirements for Google workspaces, read our Vaccination Entry Policy.

Name: Full Stack Engineer
Description:
The Enterprise Data Platforms team is transforming the way Macquarie works with data and analytics. Are you a senior full stack developer with experience in Java, Linux, Javascript web development, with an interest to learn more about big data and data governance? As a senior developer in the team, you would be responsible for engaging with users, translating user stories into design and code, and deploying/supporting the production system, as well as supporting and mentoring junior team members and encouraging good development practices. 
We anticipate that to excel in this role you will have:

the ability to work directly with stakeholders, management, and other developers to design and build solutions
to be comfortable with changing priorities and ambiguous requirements in a small-team agile environment
experience with React, Angular or similar web framework and Node.js.
experience with server-side Java. 

Additional experience in the following will be highly valued:

experience with AWS, git, Linux, shell scripting and Devops methodologies
exposure to big data, Spark, Hadoop, and related tools
experience with relational databases and SQL.

If this sounds like an ideal career opportunity, please apply or for more information reach out to chirag.bhojani@macquarie.com
About the Corporate Operations Group
The Corporate Operations Group brings together specialist support services in Digital Transformation & Data, Technology, Operations, Human Resources, Business Services, Business Improvement & Strategy, and the Macquarie Group Foundation. We deliver service excellence to ensure Macquarie is open for business, deliver on transformational change, invest in our people and have deep relationships with our customers.
Our commitment to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion 
The diversity of our people is one of our greatest strengths. An inclusive and equitable environment enables us to deliver innovative and sustainable outcomes for our people, clients, shareholders and communities. From day one, you'll be encouraged to be yourself and supported to perform at your best. If our purpose of ‘empowering people to innovate and invest for a better future’ is as inspiring to you as it is to us, please apply. With the right technology, support and resources, our people can work in a range of flexible ways.
We are committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity, equity and inclusion. We encourage candidates to speak with a member of our recruitment team if you require adjustments to our recruitment process to support you, and the type of working arrangements that would help you thrive.

Name: Software Engineer
Description:
All Systems GO! Be part of the next generation of Defence technology
An opportunity to have a unique position at the forefront of Health and Usage Monitoring (HUMS) for the F/A-18 Super Hornet, EA-18G Growler and Hawk Mk127 Aircraft.
Enjoy flexibility, engaging work and a culture that embraces diversity and open-mindedness
Be a part of a high performing team that is well regarded throughout BAE as a leader in the industry. 
Become a part of a culture that embraces innovation and forward thinking.

At BAE Systemswe are all systems go as we continue to drive innovation and seek passionate and talented people to join our business. We currently have an exciting opportunity as a Software Engineer within our Aircraft, Training and Sustainment team on the F/A-18F, EA-18G and Hawk HUMS project.
What this opportunity will mean for you:

Purposeful work where your efforts are recognized in an environment where you can thrive
Joining an organisation that is passionate about developing some of the most impressive careers in the world  
Industry-leading flexibility options to unlock the talent and diversity of every individual
Unique opportunities to contribute to programs of national significance whilst growing your skills
A strong safety culture, inclusive teams and work to be proud of, underpinned by a compelling set of values
Gain an in-depth understanding of Health and Usage Monitoring on the ADF Hornet and Hawk fleets.

Your new role:

In your new role you will work with other members of the Engineering Team, under the direction of the HUMS Engineering Team Lead to fulfil this responsibility and the specific roles described here-in
Undertake all assigned software engineering activities in accordance with the identified project directives and standards. 
Undertake requirements analysis and develop detailed design, participating in associated reviews
Undertake the integration and validation of the design including contributing to the integration and validation plans and reports
Support qualification activities to ensure that the product meets all requirements including safety and regulatory requirements
Develop software engineering related documentation in accordance with appropriate standards.
Provide regular status information to the relevant supervisors as required.
Work effectively as part of a Software Engineering team and provide assistance to other team members as required.
Assist in the development of project infrastructure such as tools deployment, metrics collection and process development.
Develop innovative ideas that drive efficiencies in project workflow.

About you

Graduate or Junior Software Engineer with < 5 years' experience
A Computer Science, Software Engineering, or Information Technology degree qualification.
Experience in developing application and/or website software under the Windows environment using the any of the following languages and frameworks:

C#,
ASP.NET MVC/WebAPI,
jQuery (and AJAX)
Javascript/Typescript
CSS 3
HTML5.
Experience in Oracle or Microsoft SQL databases.
Understanding of future technologies and associated data warehousing, i.e. Advanced Analytics, Artificial Inelegance, Machine Learning, and Big Data, etc.



Clearances
As Defence security clearance is required for this role, applicants must be Australian citizens and eligible to obtain and maintain appropriate clearance. 
International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) are applicable and as such, your nationality may be a factor in determining your suitability for this role.
Further information regarding clearances is available at: https://careers.au.baesystems.com/opportunity.html
Applications should be addressed to: Ben Woodrow Talent Acquisition Specialist and made online here. Confidential enquiries are welcome via email: Ben.Woodrow@baesystems.com
Please be aware that pursuant to different State government health directions, vaccination mandates regarding your ability to attend our Company sites may be applicable.  Please be prepared to discuss your vaccination status with our recruiters as part of the recruitment process.
We are a 2021 Circle Back Initiative Employer - we commit to respond to every applicant.
Our culture
We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive environment where our people can thrive. For us that means ensuring that the voices and talents of our employees are valued and that everyone has a sense of belonging. We do not tolerate discrimination because of differences, such as age, ability, ethnicity, gender, gender identity or expression, religion, or sexual orientation.
If you would like to know more information about how we are supporting our employees, you can view our policies and initiatives here: https://au.work180.co/employer/bae-systems/benefits
 
To learn about other employment opportunities at BAE Systems, please visit: www.baesystemscareers.com.au

Name: Data Scientist
Description: A new opportunity reporting into the Senior Manager, Data & Analytics has become available based out of our Melbourne office when not working remotely.  The Data Scientist has accountability for creating and delivering data-driven value across Health Services via the utilisation of data to discover insights, predict behaviour and visualise results and patterns observed through the application of statistical and machine learning techniques on data.  How will I help?  Key accountabilities include but are not limited to: Collaborate with internal customers to identify their business problem and work with them to provide meaningful, actionable insights and keep stakeholders informed of progress.Collate and manipulate data from multiple sources for the purpose of analysis and tactical reporting and feed this into our strategic data roadmapDevelop marketing related statistical models to support retention, acquisition, segmentation and customer lifetime value to inform next best actionProvide insights into customer behaviour, profitability and business performance and provide recommendations for optimisation of key business metrics and to improve customer experienceApply advanced analytics techniques - machine learning, statistical modelling, data mining etc. to develop algorithms and deliver intelligenceProvide quality assurance, leading practice guidance and collaborate with Data Engineers and AnalystsUtilise big data technologies, provide innovation and thought leadership What's in it for me?  As well as a competitive salary, a range of Bupa benefits and flexible working/ work from home arrangements, you'll be challenged and encouraged to innovate. You will partner with colleagues who are dedicated to delivering exceptional experiences. We respect and consider everyone, knowing your difference will make the difference.  Perk highlights: Discount on our health insurance, travel, car, home, contents and pet insurance products as well as discounts when you attend a Bupa Dental clinic or purchase glasses from a Bupa Optical store.A dedicated internal wellbeing team provides you with a range of services, such as a global resilience program, regular training opportunities on a range of wellbeing topics and access to a variety of wellbeing discounts.An additional well-being day each year to treat yourself. What do I need? Previous experience in customer insights or marketing analytics. Knowledge of these concepts applications in the health care industry would be ideal.Relevant postgraduate qualifications in data science, statistics, mathematics or similar disciplineDeep knowledge of statistics & machine learning techniques and algorithmsCommercial experience of building and improving advanced analytics solutionsExcellent scripting and programming skills including Python, R and SQLExpertise in analysing data sets, quantitative analysis, data mining and creating data visualisations (ie. Tableau and Power BI) to tell stories and provide business insightsAble to move, extract, manipulate and analyse data. Knowledge of ETL processesAbility to communicate complex information in a clear, succinct mannerDemonstrated ability to work well within virtual and agile team environmentsDemonstrated experience consulting with stakeholders to design analytical products & solutionsStrong communication and data-storytelling skillsThe ability to work with a high level of autonomy About Bupa  Bupa is an international healthcare group which has a purpose to deliver longer, healthier, happier lives and making a better world for more than 70 years. In Australia and New Zealand, Bupa assists more than 5 million customers through a broad range of health and care services including health insurance, aged care, rehabilitation, dental, optical, medical, hearing and medical visa services.  Our people reflect the diversity of our community. At Bupa, your wellbeing, identity and own story is respected and valued.

Name: Principal Solution Designer
Description:
Principal Solution Designer 
Data Platforms
Sydney Based, Permanent Role  

How will I help?
The Strategic Risk Data Environment (SRDE) project aims to bolster the Group’s growing analytics capability by revolutionising the way in which we do analytics and use data to drive decisions and insights.  There are vast data assets across the Group and people are needed to help architect and build processes to help reduce effort to acquire, process, store and analyse data through a fit-for-purpose analytics platform.
The Principal Solution Designer role is the intersection of analytics, systems and project delivery, providing thought leadership and innovation for analytical data. The function is accountable for the overall solution design of the extraction, transformation and creation of analytically ready data, that is, data specifically created in an agile manner for use in descriptive, diagnostic, predictive and prescriptive analytics. 
The main accountability of this role is to play a lead role in designing, governing and implementing strategic risk data solutions which meet the needs of both the business and IT. This role requires to work closely with the Enterprise Architects, Information Architects and act as the liaison between the Analytics team, various technology teams including strategic partners and the various business areas.
What you will do
Designing optimal solution to prepare analytically ready data for use in descriptive, predictive and prescriptive analytics.
Work with business units to understand credit risk related data elements, including identification of relevant reference data, metadata and data lineage.
Ability to work collaboratively within an Agile delivery framework.
Analyse source system data and identify any derived measures that are used by business.
Development of data definitions, including business rules, physical level data rules, field types, formats, profiling, data sourcing and end usage of the data.
Data Publication, involving managing the transition of data from a conceptual state, such as a prototype, strategy or model, to operational state in a system for decisioning.  Ability to provide the link between systems functions, analytics or modelling and project functions.
Source data identification, involving identifying the optimal source of the required data variables (e.g., those required for modelling, calculation and reporting). 
Data Investigation - Analyse data for issues to help determine the root cause of the issue and where required, the development of business rules that need to be applied. 
Provide thought leadership and subject matter expertise on analytical ready data to the analytics, projects, systems and business teams.
Maintain and enhance analytical data knowledge through the publication of information into the analytics knowledge management solution.

Development, management and support of analytically ready data.
The development of analytical data routines for extraction, alignment, transformation and preparation for analytical consumption.
Engineering, detailed design and optimisation for data processes that exist in the Analytics Data Layer.
Development and enhancement of the Analytics Data Framework by providing thought leadership on how analytics data needs to be managed, delivered and created.
The creation and management of automation to schedule data processes and publish analytics
Embedding of the Agile culture and delivery methodology into the business for on-going changes.

What’s in it for me?
Joining Westpac has many benefits besides building a long and stable career. You’ll be able to purchase leave to facilitate your dreams or obligations and you’ll be encouraged to participate in the community through paid volunteer leave and secondments. You’ll also be entitled to a suite of online learning, training modules and career planning tools to grow with us. 
What do I need? 
Essential:
Credit Risk and/or Banking Product experience
5+ years of Solution Designing experience for a large and complex data processing platforms.
7+ years experience in a large and complex financial services organisation.
10+ years experience within projects and/or delivery of business and technology solutions, involving engineering of complex data processes.
10+ years of Advanced SQL and SAS experience particularly in data manipulation, cleansing using Base SAS, SAS/Macro, SAS DI Studio, SAS Enterprise Guide, SAS Management Consle and overall SAS Platform.
10+ years of demonstrable experience in batch scheduling jobs using LSF and Control-M and r
7+ years hands on experience using Unix/Linux servers and execution SAS jobs in batch.
7+ years of experience in data quality analysis and remediation.
Excellent knowledge about Cloud Platforms and hands on experience working on Big Data Analytics using Hadoop and Azure.

Preferred:
Experience in data analysis and modelling.
Hands on use of the Atlassian toolset of JIRA, Confluence and BitBucket.

Education: 
Tertiary qualifications in Maths, Statistics, Quantitative, Business, Computer Engineering or equivalent business experience.

Name: Software Engineer - Financial Markets
Description:
How will I help? 
The vision of the Financial Markets division within Westpac Institutional Bank is to be No.1 in Australia and New Zealand delivering customer service excellence sustainably. You will be  working in Digital Analytics and Systematic Trading (DAS), a unique, diverse, highly qualified and exciting team. DAS’s purpose is to deliver on our Financial Markets vision by creating a digitally enabled and data-driven business. Sitting within DAS is the Digital workflows and UX team, where you will be instrumental in  transforming our digital footprint, business productivity and client service.
This team is seeking a business minded Software Engineer to design and implement end to end business solutions. You will be working directly alongside Financial Markets sales, trading, quant, data analytics and technology teams to support and guide the business in their digital transformation journey. Utilising your Full-Stack Developer skills, you will help to deliver our Smart Desktop Vision which will  supercharge the productivity and efficiencies of our sales and traders. You will be utilising your technical expertise to: 

Utilise ReactJS on OpenFin to create interoperable micro-application front ends;
Create Spring boot microservices; 
Leverage CI/CD and Kubernetes to ensure High Availability of applications and services;
Leverage SQL Server, Palantir and Kafka to drive the applications.

You will also:
Partner and communicate with internal and external stakeholders and providers, including the Financial Markets Leadership Team;
Develop web applications and data driven tools using JavaScript, Java and other Full-Stack Developer languages like Python, PySpark, and SQL;
Operate with autonomy on projects to prioritise deadlines and deliverables.

What’s in it for me?  
Westpac Group has been around for over 200 years. In our chosen markets and customer segments, Westpac Financial Markets is a global business that competes successfully with top tier banks. To remain as competitive as we have been, the business will need to continue to evolve as markets and trading floors are being transformed globally by the use of new technologies. Within Westpac Group, the Financial Markets business is recognised as a strategic, significant business unit delivering results with great growth opportunities. The Digital Workflows and DAS team within Financial Markets is unique amongst our Australian peers. This is an unmatched opportunity to work in a team where your expertise and skillset will be directly influential on, and recognised by, the Financial Markets business.  So we’ll back you in the development of your career, internal career prospects, and flexible working. You’ll also keep learning to grow, supported by a fantastic team of like-minded people within a highly performing, can-do and collaborative environment. 

What do I need?
You will be a motivated, enthusiastic and highly technical individual who can embrace agile and lean software development practices while providing a consultative approach to interacting with key stakeholders. You will have experience in creating and presenting software solutions and tools to the business while contributing to end to end development of web applications.
Some further advantageous skills:
Financial Services/Markets experience is not required.
Advanced skills programming in JavaScript, HTML, CSS with ReactJS exposure.
Advanced experience programming in Java, ideally using spring boot.
Solid SQL experience; exposure to big data is a bonus.
Experience with Kafka, Python/Pyspark, SQL Server or Palantir is a plus.
Tertiary degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering or similar relevant field or practical experience required.

How do I Apply? 
Start Here. Just click on the APPLY button.
As part of our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, this role is open to experienced candidates seeking a discussion around workplace flexibility. We invite candidates of all ages, people with a disability and Indigenous Australians to apply. 
 
The health and wellbeing of our employees is our priority and we will ensure that physical distancing requirements are met in all our workplaces as long as required.

The Westpac Group has implemented an Entry to Workplace Policy that requires employees and others entering our workplaces to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 by relevant dates set out in the policy (subject to applicable medical exemptions).

Our employees are required to comply with the policy regardless of whether they are in customer-facing or non-customer-facing roles (as employees in non-customer-facing roles are required to attend the workplace under our Hybrid Working Strategy). Further, the Westpac Group is required to comply with State/Territory issued public health orders/directions which require relevant workers to be vaccinated against COVID-19 to enter workplaces.
By applying for this role, you acknowledge that you are aware of our Entry to Workplace Policy, and if you secure employment with us, you will be required to comply with the policy.

Name: Data Platform Architect
Description:
The speed of change is throwing traditional business methods into question and disrupting the relevance of entire industries. Capgemini, a global leader in consulting, digital transformation, technology and engineering services, is at the forefront of innovation and well placed to address opportunities for our clients in the evolving world of cloud, digital and platforms. Building on its strong 50-year heritage and deep industry-specific expertise, Capgemini enables organisations to realise their business ambitions through an array of services from strategy to operations. Capgemini is driven by the conviction that the business value of technology comes from and through people. Today, it is a multicultural company with over 270,000 team members in almost 50 countries. With Altran, the Group reported 2020 combined revenues of EUR 15.8 billion. Learn more about us at www.capgemini.com [link removed].
Let's talk about the team:
Our Insights and Data team helps our clients make better business decisions by transforming an ocean of data into streams of insight. Our clients are among Australia's top performing companies and they choose to partner with Capgemini for a very good reason - our exceptional people.
 Let's talk about the role and responsibilities:

Define and ensure a comprehensive and coherent view across Business, Information, Systems and Technology, not just to design IT systems but to deliver Business Change which may also be supported and enabled by IT.
Define solutions strategies and roadmaps. Builds Capgemini's image and reputation to the client and the marketplace. Leads coordination of architecture solutions to meet senior level expectations at both client and Capgemini and/or partners. Leads strategic planning of technology and business solutions for the enterprise.  Demonstrates thought leadership in topics in the architect community and shows a passion for technology. Demonstrates business acumen by delivering the architecture program.
Define and ensure comprehensive and coherent view across Business, Information Systems and Technology
Define strategy and architecture for data estate modernisation, legacy to cloud data migration, data pipeline, data analytics, machine learning pipeline, data trust and data engineering solutions
Drive business change supported and enabled by Data and AI
You will provide technical solutions to project team to perform design to deployment related activities, provide guidance, perform reviews, prevent, and resolve technical issues
You will work with stakeholders including the Product, Data and Design teams to assist with data-related technical issues
You will assess and propose methods to improve system performance by conducting tests, troubleshooting, and integrating new element

Let's talk about your capability and experience:  

Have a minimum of 10 years IT experience and minimum 5 years in solution architecture with data background, whilst leading architecture and solutioning strategy
Develop portfolio products and service solutions for Capgemini and Clients
Demonstrate technical strategy leadership in one or more technology areas and/or one or more customer facing situations
Show proven thought leadership in technical implementation and practices
Lead and motivate multi-functional teams in dispersed or complex environments
Set and manage the client's expectations from the start
Be able to drive projects and initiatives from conception through to implementation 
Demonstrate excellent written, verbal communication and listening skills
Harness your excellent teamwork and leadership skills
Have experience managing business and technical stakeholders, managing multi-shore resources in a particular technical area (those being configuration, customisation, data estate modernisation, integration)
Be Knowledgable and experienced in Functional Architecture Design, Technical Solution Design
Have experience with cloud data platforms and technologies (AWS/Azure) and Big Data technologies (Hadoop/Spark)

Let's talk about what's in it for you!
Passionate people are Capgemini's Ace of Spades - join us to discover a career that will challenge, support and inspire you. Working at Capgemini you'll find the rewards are more than just financial. You will work alongside some very smart and inspiring people on exciting projects and you will also enjoy incredible benefits.  We offer flexible work practices and 40 hours of self-development every year with a huge selection of learning opportunities to choose from. Capgemini constantly aims for excellence in its operations and the employee experience it provides. In line with our Purpose, Flexible Working aims to improve the overall people experience by providing an optimal work-life balance, more autonomy and freedom in when, where and how we work.
As "Architects of Positive Futures", Capgemini actively supports the community in 3 ways:
Diversity and Inclusion - we believe diversity of thought fuels excellence and innovation, which is why we positively encourage applications from suitably qualified candidates regardless of their gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, religion, ability, intersex status or age.  To support our commitment to diversity and inclusion, we celebrate or recognise special events and days of significance that are important to our employees such as Diwali, Bastille Day, Pride, IDAHOBIT, IWD and International day of people with Disabilities.  Our Employee Resource Groups Women@Capgemini, OutFront, Indigenous, Parents and Carers and Sustainability Community of Practice support the grassroots passion of employees to drive our diversity agenda and effect change.
Digital inclusion - at Capgemini we are using our skills to drive social impact initiatives focusing on helping society address the impact of the digital and automation revolution.  We also provide employees with opportunities to give back to the community through charity projects and volunteer days.
Environmental Sustainability - Capgemini joined the CDP's (Carbon Disclosure Project) prestigious "A list" for its commitment to the Net-Zero economy. As well as focusing on helping our clients transform towards more sustainable business models, Capgemini recently announced its commitment to becoming a netzero busines by 2030.
Recognised by Ethisphere as one of the World's Most Ethical Companies for the last 9 years in a row, ethics and values are at the heart of Capgemini's corporate culture and business.  Embedded in our DNA, our seven values - Honesty, Boldness, Trust, Team Spirit, Freedom, Fun and Modesty - have remained the same since company inception in 1967. To see how we bring these values to life, visit www.capgemini.com/au-en/careers/ [link removed] and listen to some of our employee's stories.
#GetTheFutureYouWant - Come join us, bring your whole self to work, create new possibilities for you, your customers and your community and help us to be Architects of Positive Futures. 

Please note unsolicited resumes from employment agencies or other third parties will not be considered.#LI-YT1

Name: Associate Professor/Professor, Renewable Energy
Description: At UTS the concepts of equity and social justice are key to our core and purpose. We are recognised widely as supporting inclusivity and valuing diversity. We are among the first Australian institutions to receive the Athena SWAN Bronze Accreditation for our commitment to action addressing gender equity in the STEMM disciplines. UTS Equal Futures celebrates and supports women in academia through every stage of their career.As part of Athena SWAN, UTS has set an overarching target of 40 per cent academic women in STEMM by 2022. The School of Electrical & Data Engineering is committed to UTS's target and supporting the career development of women academics. UTS Women in Engineering & IT program fosters a network of passionate females and males who are actively involved in the development of our next generation of young engineering and IT professionals.   The School of Electrical & Data Engineering is recruiting an Associate Professor or a Professor to provide academic, research and professional leadership, and to develop and lead research and industry engagement activities, as well as deliver both UG and PG teaching in Electrical Engineering, with a renewable energy focus. The position will be based at the centrally located UTS Campus in Ultimo and will report directly to Head of Discipline, Professor Dylan Lu.The School of Electrical & Data Engineering is deeply engaged in research of national and international standing in many areas. Key areas include: wireless communications and networking, Internet of Things (IoT), applied electro-magnetics and antennas, electrical systems and power electronics, image processing, computer vision, machine learning, cybersecurity, big data analytics and big data systems, and RF IC design. Our School hosts three IEEE Fellows and 3 ARC DECRA grant holders and we conduct research funded by government agencies and national and international industry partner.About the role• Teaching-related leadership and research-based teaching practice at the program level (Level D), or discipline related (Level E), courses in Electrical Engineering.• Attract significant national competitive funding and industrial funding• Provide service and leadership at the School, Faculty and University levels• Supervision of undergraduate and postgraduate project studentsAbout you• A PhD degree in Electrical Engineering or closely related disciplines• Familiarity with relevant industry practices in Electrical Engineering courses - renewable energy, energy storage, electrified transportation, electrification or related fields• Demonstrated knowledge of recent advances in Electrical Engineering courses - renewable energy, energy storage, electrified transportation, electrification or related fields• Successful teaching and course development experience in Electrical Engineering and renewable energy• Experience and track record in research with demonstrated outcomes that include research publications, grants and research supervision in Electrical Engineering, renewable energy, energy storage, electric vehicles, smart grids, electrification or related fields.Base Salary Range: $161,730 to $201,100 pa (Level D - E)This role attracts 17% superannuation (pension) in addition to the base salary.UTS staff also benefit from a wide range of Employee Benefits include flexible work practices, child care centres, generous parental leave and salary packaging opportunities.This position is full-time and appointment will be made on a continuing basis.Our vision is to be a leading public university of technology recognised for our global impact. We are a dynamic and innovative university, ranked by the Times Higher Education as Australia's top young university, and located centrally in one of the world's most liveable cities. With a culturally diverse campus life and extensive international exchange and research programs, UTS prepares graduates for the workplaces of today and tomorrow. How To ApplyFor the full list of the selection criteria and role responsibilities please click the apply link and download the Position Statement from the UTS website. UTS is committed to diversity and inclusion in our workforce and we encourage applicants where relevant to include a relative to opportunity or career disruption/break statement within their CV.You are required to address the selection criteria in your submission in a separate document.   Only those applications submitted via the UTS online recruitment system will be accepted.  Current UTS employees should apply through their UTS Employee Self Service function.As you will be unable to save your application once started, please have all required documents and information available prior to commencing.Please ensure that the file name for each document submitted includes IRC220841 and your name.Specific enquiries or issues with your application may be directed to Pam Price in the UTS Recruitment Team at recruitment@uts.edu.au.Please be advised that as part of the selection process that you may be requested to deliver a presentation, the audience for which may include individuals not on the Selection Panel.Closing Date:  Monday 27th June 2022 at 11.59pm (AEST)AccessibilityUTS Recruitment cares about digital accessibility. If there is any content in our advertising that you have struggled with, please make us aware so that we can make our information accessible to all.In addition, if you have a disability that requires adjustment to the recruitment process or an alternative application pathway please contact recruitment@uts.edu.au for assistance.UTS is recognised widely as supporting inclusivity and diversity through our Wingara Indigenous Employment Strategy, Social Impact Framework, and UTS Access and Inclusion Plan.We welcome applications from women, Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those who identify as LGBTIQ, and applicants from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

Name: Digital Marketing Web Analyst
Description:
Are you a Digital Marketing Web Analyst who is passionate about delivering a comprehensive website analysis? We’re recruiting a Digital Marketing Web Analyst responsible for supporting the delivery of strategic and tactical initiatives to market across Macquarie Bank’s digital channels.   Reporting to the Head of MarTech, you’ll be responsible for the accurate tracking of our web performance and marketing activities while contributing to creating targeted and personalised digital experiences for our customers. 


Your deep, working knowledge of Digital Analytic platforms, dashboards and reporting, coupled with best-in-class practices will see you drive results across the business. This role will play an essential role in the broader business initiatives that will contribute to the success of the business.
Your Key Responsibilities Will Include 



Collecting and transforming data from a variety of digital marketing & analytics, CRM tools and big data environments
Analysing data, trends, and results, as well as translating into business impact for stakeholders
Working alongside business teams to establish the analytical problem and design an appropriate data solution





You’ll Bring The Following Skills And Experience



Experience working in analytics teams
Data extraction and wrangling operations using SQL/Alteryx/Python/R
Data visualization tools like Tableau, Power BI, Data Studio
Experience with predictive and optimization data models and reporting packages
Ability to analyse large disparate datasets
An analytical mind and inclination for problem solving

If this sounds like you, click through the link and apply!


About Banking and Financial Services
Banking and Financial Services is Macquarie’s retail banking and financial services business, providing a diverse range of personal banking, wealth management, business banking and vehicle finance products and services to retail clients, advisers, brokers and business clients. 
Our commitment to Diversity and Inclusion 
The diversity of our people is one of our greatest strengths, and in combination with our inclusive environment, it enables us to deliver innovative and sustainable outcomes for our people, clients, shareholders and communities. From day one, you'll be encouraged to be yourself and supported to perform at your best. If our purpose of ‘empowering people to innovate and invest for a better future’ is as inspiring to you as it is to us, please apply. With the right technology, support and resources, our people can work in a range of flexible ways.
We are committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity and inclusion. We encourage candidates to speak with a member of our recruitment team if you require adjustments to our recruitment process to support you, and the type of working arrangements that would help you thrive.

Name: Software Developer (Mid-Senior Level)
Description: Just Digital People have teamed up with an exciting company who is looking for their next Software Developer (Mid-Senior) to join their company at an exciting time of growth. They are one of Australia’s fastest growing tech start ups with plans to expand their game changing solution across the globe.    Being in the game since 2013, they have still maintained their “start-up culture” and believe that empowerment and creativity is key. By democratising big data and delivering deeper value for their clients, they are revolutionising the world of data and analytics. Instant analytics, any data, anywhere means better-informed and faster decisions, giving their clients a competitive edge.    Your responsibilities:   Analysing, designing, implementing, and testing programs Developing frontend applications Work closely with Senior Software Engineers Work in an Agile cross-functional team, collaborating successfully. Actively participate in and contribute to the improvement of Agile and lean processes and practises. Contribute to the design of software, systems, interfaces, and products on a functional and technological level. Understanding of test automation, continuous integration and delivery, and system configuration management is required to support integrated applications.    Skills:  Scala/Java/Apache Spark Bonus points if you have: Scala Play/JavaScript/Ignite/Solr/Arrow Experience developing workflow engine Experience with building, testing and deployment Have experience with SDLC Be able to work well in a team but also independently and is outcome driven Ability to work in a fast paced environment Have an easy going and kick a** attitude!  Joining these guys will mean you will be part of a team that will never stop challenging you. You will continuously be learning, evolving and growing your skills to an expert level. You will be closely mentored by Senior Devs that will take you on the journey of lifelong learning experiences! If you would like to join the journey to pioneer a new standard in Data and Analytics, then get applying!    Natalie Youkhana Just Digital People ph/txt: 0451 441 691 nat@justdigitalpeople.com.au w: www.justdigitalpeople.com.au    If this position not quite the right one then don't worry! Name: Data Scientist
Description: We are working with....Konnexus has been given the opportunity to work with a leading financial services organisation to find a Data Scientist to work in their team. Our client has teams across the Eastern seaboard, and has exciting projects within the machine learning space. Due to the ongoing growth of the business, an opportunity has presented to join the Data Science team in a permanent opportunity.  As a Data Scientist you will be doing….   Presenting complex ideas and use case outcomes to large audiences Discovering, developing and promoting new data science use cases Building prototypes Building proof of concept models Be a key member of machine learning projects  You will be someone who has....  Experience with SQL, R/Python and the ability to pick up new languages Quantitative academic background (Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics etc) Proven experience delivering analytical use cases in large organisations Exceptional communication skills, both written and verbal Experience with big data/cloud technologies desired  In return, you will be offered....  Annual bonus of 10% in addition to attractive salary package Hybrid working environment Ability to move interstate Work for an organisation that offers continuous development and training   If this position is of interest to you, please click ‘Apply’ or you can send your details to fiona@konnexuscg.com or call Fiona on 0400 638 844 quoting reference #1250523 for a confidential chat. Name: Lead Data Engineer
Description: Lead Data EngineerCloud based optimisation London - Hybrid WorkingPermanent£80 000-£110 000.****please note position does not offer sponsorship****As a Senior/Lead Data Engineer, you will be responsible for designing and developing data processing and data persistence software components for solutions which handle data at scale. Working in agile teams, Lead Data Engineers providing strong development leadership for team members and take responsibility for the quality of the codebase as well as the match to user needs.We are seeking more high calibre people to join our Data & Analytics capability where you will grow and contribute to industry-leading technical expertise.What will you do?As a Data Engineeryou'll be working to develop data processing software primarily for deployment in Big Data technologies. The role encompasses the full software lifecycle including design, code, test and defect resolution.Additionally, you'll be working with architects to ensure the software supports non-functional needs and will be collaborating with colleagues to resolve implementation challenges and ensure code quality and quality and maintainability remains high.What does the ideal candidate look like?Software development experience in SaaS and PaaS services from AWS, Mircrosoft or Google, Databricks or Snowflake, Java, Scala, or Python.Experience in developing and maintaining data pipelines, as well as experience in non-functional needs of ETL/ELT data processing solutions such as robustness, performance, and security.Thorough knowledge of RDBMS and NoSQL data stores and of working with data in a variety of structures including JSON and XML.Experience in coaching and mentoring junior and experienced technical staff.Has experience using continuous integration tools and techniques and is aware of best practice.If you're determined in overcoming obstacles; honest when dealing with others; respectful of how you treat others; creative to find solutions to complex problems and cooperative by sharing information, knowledge and experience, then this role is for you!If Interested, please send the latest copy of your CV to hugh.richards@opusrs.com to arrange an interview

Name: Industry Ecosystem Partner Architect, Retail, Google Cloud
Description: At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google’s technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan for more information.Note: By applying to this position you will have an opportunity to share your preferred working location from the following: Sydney NSW, Australia; Melbourne VIC, Australia.Minimum qualifications:Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience15 years of experience as an enterprise architect in either a cloud computing environment or equivalent experience in a customer-facing roleExperience in cloud computing and cloud market and dynamicsPreferred qualifications:Experience with structured Enterprise Architecture practices, hybrid cloud deployments, and on-premise-to-cloud migration deployments/roadmapsExperience in enterprise technology buying and evaluation processExperience in building, architecting, designing/implementing highly distributed global cloud-based systemsExperience in network infrastructure, security, and application developmentKnowledge of technology solutions and ability to learn, understand, and work quickly with new emerging technologies, methodologies, and solutions in the cloud/IT technology spaceAbility to deliver results and work cross-functionally, engage/influence audiences, and identify expansion engagementsAbout the jobWhen leading companies choose Google Cloud it's a huge win for spreading the power of cloud computing globally. Once educational institutions, government agencies, and other businesses sign on to use Google Cloud products, you come in to facilitate making their work more productive, mobile, and collaborative. You listen and deliver what is most helpful for the customer. You assist fellow sales Googlers by problem-solving key technical issues for our customers. You liaise with the product marketing management and engineering teams to stay on top of industry trends and devise enhancements to Google Cloud products.As part of the Partner Engineering organization, Industry Ecosystem Partner Architects lead cross-functional teams of experts to help our partners design, plan, implement, and govern enterprise cloud strategies. As a Industry Ecosystem Partner Architect, you will embody executive-level qualities, facilitate the conversation, and direct the execution of the Partner Sales team by combining both technical vision and business insight. You will partner with Value Engineering to articulate the true total value of each technical solution and the overall business partnership with Google Cloud.From startups building their first app to billion-user consumer companies crunching big data, the Google Cloud Platform gives developers and businesses the most advanced data and analytics solution on the market, along with Google's secure, high performance infrastructure. Our team of technical account managers and software engineers work with partners across all functions to develop solutions that harness Google's planet-wide platform to solve the world's most challenging problems.ResponsibilitiesLeverage knowledge of industry challenges and drivers in various markets to represent Google Cloud’s industry solutions narrative with identified partners complementing the solutions and capabilities.Work with the field Industry Principal Architects and customer engineers to identify the priority solutions by market and industry and work with the Independent Software Vendor (ISV) PE team if required to bring components from the ISV ecosystem to complete the industry solution framework.Leverage technical architecture expertise to advise the Google Cloud practices within the partner organizations for building solutions.Engage with the executives along with the partner teams to influence the approach and shape the potential solution outcome.Provide advisor consultancy to the partners on Google's suite of products, portfolio, and future innovations and serves as a point of contact for strategic interactions on solutions and roadmap.Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing our Accommodations for Applicants form.To all recruitment agencies: Google does not accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Google employees or any other organization location. Google is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.To learn more about US requirements around COVID vaccination requirements for Google workspaces, read our Vaccination Entry Policy.
