Name: Senior Systems Engineer (CI-CD)
Description: Senior Systems Engineer - CI CD You'll enjoy solving analytical problems to help our team to reach highest potential and earn stakeholder trust We nurture and support our people through career development and Flexibility Together we can deliver the future of banking and customer satisfaction Do work that matters  Technology (BU) is responsible for the world leading application of technology and operations across every aspect of CommBank, from innovative product platforms for our customers to essential tools within our business. We also use technology to drive efficient and timely processing, an essential component of great customer service.  Chief Data Office's vision is to achieve better customer outcomes resulting in sustainable competitive advantage through analytically led decision making. We are also committed to providing high quality information to manage our business and meet regulatory obligations. We provide a range of services to our internal customers across all business units of the Group including strategy, architecture, data science, business intelligence, engineering and program delivery.  We are accountable for the Group's key analytics capabilities including Big Data (Omnia, Teradata), BI/Analytics Applications (like SAS, Tableau, Alteryx, Oracle BI, Zeppelin, Jupyter, RStudio, H2O, Trifacta, Collibra, Alation) and Decisioning (Pega) platforms. We are focused on enhancing these to create world-leading capabilities for analytics, information management and decisioning.  See yourself in the team  A Senior Systems Engineer in the Decisioning team is responsible for designing, deploying and operating the team's BI and analytics applications, in line with Agile and DevOps principles.  You will work with a range of different tools and technologies. And interact with a broad set of teams and customers across the bank. A knack for identifying and suggesting improvements to process inefficiencies is a must.  We believe in using the right tool for the job so an open mind and an ability to learn new tech stacks, languages and frameworks will go a long way.  We are interested in hearing from people who can: Understand our customers' core business objectives and design end-to-end solutions to address them with primary focus on scalable architecture and design. Use your analytical mindset to drive decisions based on data. Participate in the full lifecycle of agile projects (ideation through implementation). Be recognised as an SME for platform and application characteristics such as operational overhead, cost of change, appropriate use cases, and demonstrate an understanding of these characteristics in your Approach to development, support and operations of the platform and applications. Support strategic direction by understanding the business outcomes the squad is working towards solve, and how the work of the squad relates to customer outcomes. We use a broad range of tools, languages, and frameworks. We don't expect you to know them all but experience or exposure with some of these (or equivalents) will set you up for success in this team; 5 + of experience in system architecture and design Experience in vendor and open source application deployment and management Strong programming skills in Python and/or Nodejs Strong scripting skills in at least one of the following scripting languages such as Bash/shell, PowerShell. Strong background in Linux and experience in automation and configuration management tools such as Ansible, Puppet, Chef etc. Experience in containerised application deployments e.g. Docker Experience with Git for version control and Artifactory for artefacts management. Implementing continuous integration and delivery pipelines using Teamcity and/or Jenkins. Experience in Amazon Web Services (AWS) and/or Microsoft Azure Experience of working with Kubernetes/ECS Working with us:  Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career with CommBank is for you.  Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive, and flexible workplace with flexible work locations. One where we're driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.  Here, you'll thrive. You'll be supported when faced with challenges and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We're hiring engineers from across all of Australia, you'll be empowered to do your best work and be given the choice on when and where that work happens. We really love working here, and we think you will too. Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career here is for you. Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive and flexible workplace. One where we're driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.Here, you'll thrive. You'll be supported when faced with challenges, and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We really love working here, and we think you will too.We're determined to make a real difference for Australia's first peoples. We encourage all interested applicants to apply. If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick [link removed] to submit a valid application. We're keen to support you with the next step in your career.

Name: Azure Data Engineer
Description:
Is innovation part of your DNA? Do you want to enable a connected future for people, organizations, and society?
Join our growing global NTT team and you’ll be part of the world’s largest ICT company (by revenue). We’ve combined the capabilities of 28 remarkable companies to become one, leading technology services provider. Together, we help our people, clients, and communities do great things with technology to create a more secure and connected future. We employ 40,000 people across 57 countries. By bringing together the world’s best technology companies and emerging innovators, we work together to deliver sustainable outcomes to businesses and the world. Innovation is part of our DNA. We believe it’s key to what makes us different. So, we strive to move forward, challenge the status quo, and drive excellence through the technologies we integrate and the services we deliver around the world. The result is connected cities, connected factories, connected healthcare, connected agriculture, connected conservation, connected mobility, and connected sport. Together we enable the connected future.
Want to be part of the team?
This is a unique opportunity to join our passionate Data & Analytics team in our Melbourne office. As an Azure Data Engineer, you will use your Azure experience in assisting our clients with ongoing projects and implementations. 
Your day at NTT

Lead the implementations of Cloud, Analytics, Data Lake, Data Warehousing and Data Visualisation projects 
Implementing ETL (extract, transform and load) pipelines, monitoring/maintaining data pipeline performance and implementing big data or analytics solutions. 
Implementing solutions using Azure Data Components  
Provide data and analytics thought leadership to clients. 

What would make you a good fit for this role?

Experience with the Azure Data Components (Azure Data Factory, Azure SQL, Azure Data Lake, Azure Analysis Services, Azure Synapse and Azure Databricks)
Data Modelling skills and competent communication/presentation skills  
Ability to translate business requirements and architecture into a working solution
Experience in Continuous Integration using Azure DevOps is desirable
Experience with Microsoft BI Stack (SQL Server, SSAS, Tabular, SSIS, SSRS) is desirable
Join our growing global team and accelerate your career with us. Apply today.
For more information about this or other opportunities, please contact Krisalyn Matining. Please quote our job reference number 566910.About usNTT Ltd. is a leading global technology services company. Working with organizations around the world, we achieve business outcomes through intelligent technology solutions. For us, intelligent means data driven, connected, digital and secure. As a global ICT provider, we employ more than 40,000 people in a diverse and dynamic workplace that spans 57 countries, trading in 73 countries and delivering services in over 200 countries and regionsNTT is proud to be an equal opportunity employer with a global culture that embraces diversity. We are committed to providing an environment free of unfair discrimination and harassment. We do not discriminate based on age, race, color, sex, religion, national origin, disability, pregnancy, marital status, sexual orientation, gender reassignment, veteran status, or other protected category.

Name: Data Engineer (cap hire)
Description:
The speed of change is throwing traditional business methods into question and disrupting the relevance of entire industries. Capgemini, a global leader in consulting, digital transformation, technology and engineering services, is at the forefront of innovation and well placed to address opportunities for our clients in the evolving world of cloud, digital and platforms. Building on its strong 50-year heritage and deep industry-specific expertise, Capgemini enables organisations to realise their business ambitions through an array of services from strategy to operations. Capgemini is driven by the conviction that the business value of technology comes from and through people. Today, it is a multicultural company with over 270,000 team members in almost 50 countries. With Altran, the Group reported 2020 combined revenues of EUR 15.8 billion. Learn more about us at www.capgemini.com [link removed].
Let's talk about the team:
Our Insights and Data team helps our clients make better business decisions by transforming an ocean of data into streams of insight. Our clients are among Australia's top performing companies and they choose to partner with Capgemini for a very good reason - our exceptional people. Due to continued growth within Capgemini's Insights & Data practice we intend to recruit a AWS Data Engineer with relevant consulting and communication skills. If you are already working in a consultancy role, or have excellent client-facing skills gained within large organizations, we would like to discuss our consultant opportunities with you. This role can be positioned to work from anywhere in Australia (Sydney, Melbourne, Adelaide, Brisbane or Perth)
 Let's talk about the role and responsibilities: 

Build robust, efficient and reliable data pipelines consisting of diverse data sources to ingest and process data 
Design and develop real time streaming and batch processing pipeline solutions  
Assemble large, complex data sets to meet functional / non-functional requirements 
Design, develop and implement data pipelines for data migration and collection, data analytics and other data movement solutions 
Work with stakeholders and data analyst teams to assist with data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needs 
Collaborate with Architects to define the architecture and technology selection 

Let's talk about your qualifications and experience:  

A minimum of 3 years previous experience as a Data Engineer with at least 2+ years of AWS hands on technical experience
Previous experience in programming eg. Core Java/Python/Scala programming; Hadoop Stack eg. Hive, Spark (Core and Streaming), Kafka, Flink, NIFI;
Experience working on stream transform using Spark Streaming or Flink;
Experience working on change data capture in a big data ecosystem;
Experience in building real time or batch ingestion and transformation pipelines;

Should be able to work on AWS - S3, EMR, Redshift 


Should be able to implement the Data Vault & start schema Framework using redshift


Should be able to work with Devops team on Orchestrating Airflow works


Good understanding on iPython and Bigdata and Hands on SQL


Let's talk about what's in it for you!
Passionate people are Capgemini's Ace of Spades - join us to discover a career that will challenge, support and inspire you. Working at Capgemini you'll find the rewards are more than just financial. You will work alongside some very smart and inspiring people on exciting projects and you will also enjoy incredible benefits.  We offer flexible work practices and 40 hours of self-development every year with a huge selection of learning opportunities to choose from. Capgemini constantly aims for excellence in its operations and the employee experience it provides. In line with our Purpose, Flexible Working aims to improve the overall people experience by providing an optimal work-life balance, more autonomy and freedom in when, where and how we work.
As "Architects of Positive Futures", Capgemini actively supports the community in 3 ways:
Diversity and Inclusion - we believe diversity of thought fuels excellence and innovation, which is why we positively encourage applications from suitably qualified candidates regardless of their gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, religion, ability, intersex status or age.  To support our commitment to diversity and inclusion, we celebrate or recognise special events and days of significance that are important to our employees such as Diwali, Bastille Day, Pride, IDAHOBIT, IWD and International day of people with Disabilities.  Our Employee Resource Groups Women@Capgemini, OutFront, Indigenous, Parents and Carers and Sustainability Community of Practice support the grassroots passion of employees to drive our diversity agenda and effect change.
Digital inclusion - at Capgemini we are using our skills to drive social impact initiatives focusing on helping society address the impact of the digital and automation revolution.  We also provide employees with opportunities to give back to the community through charity projects and volunteer days.
Environmental Sustainability - Capgemini joined the CDP's (Carbon Disclosure Project) prestigious "A list" for its commitment to the Net-Zero economy. As well as focusing on helping our clients transform towards more sustainable business models, Capgemini recently announced its commitment to becoming a netzero busines by 2030.
Recognised by Ethisphere as one of the World's Most Ethical Companies for the last 9 years in a row, ethics and values are at the heart of Capgemini's corporate culture and business.  Embedded in our DNA, our seven values - Honesty, Boldness, Trust, Team Spirit, Freedom, Fun and Modesty - have remained the same since company inception in 1967. To see how we bring these values to life, visit www.capgemini.com/au-en/careers/ [link removed] and listen to some of our employee's stories.
#GetTheFutureYouWant - Come join us, bring your whole self to work, create new possibilities for you, your customers and your community and help us to be Architects of Positive Futures. 

Please note unsolicited resumes from employment agencies or other third parties will not be considered.
 #LI-AR1

Name: Presales Consultant
Description: Presales ConsultantSydney  Job Purpose The role of Presales Consultant is a key role related to the business expansion in Australia. The candidate should be a hands-on technology Presales specialist with a proven history of working within IT outsourcing businesses that are ideally focussed on bespoke applications development. The role requires a strong background in Presales and Bid Management and a good understanding of Application architecture, systems design, and software development. The person should have proven experience in building client relationships and senior stakeholder management. The candidate must have the ability to engage in opening discussions with stakeholders, rapidly identifying and formulating their requirements and issues and both developing and effectively communicating solutions appropriate to resolving their issues. The role requires the Presales specialist to continuously improve the Bid and Presales processes, and to deliver efficiencies and agility while responding to prospective opportunities. The incumbent will also be expected to  engage with a Bid Team consisting of Technical Architects, Business Analysts and Project Managers (acting as Bid Managers).    Responsibilities Presales Support  Provide presales expertise in Australia in support of the business opportunities . Manage full bid lifecycle from lead to close for new opportunities Own the quality of overall deliverables throughout the end-to-end sales process Facilitate client workshops that assist in    analysing the business processes, evaluating existing systems, surfacing the business requirements and needs, identifying existing system inefficiencies, assessing the potential for change and optimisation shaping solutions during the sales cycle    Work closely with Architects and Analysts in order to design solutions to client needs – identifying any requirements for adaptations Work with the delivery organisation to provide commercial models for proposals including project plans, scheduling, costing and resourcing plans Build strong client recommendations and value propositions that highlight our key strengths and cost optimisation potential of proposed solutions  Solutions  Work with the Business Analysts, Developers and Stakeholders and act as a conduit to identify the best-in-class solution and ensure the successful delivery of proposals Lead requirements capture and solution shaping, help with prototyping and proof of concept development as required Challenge the delivery team to define and deliver new solutions that enhance the Solutions portfolio Keep abreast of emerging technologies Maintain a strong understanding of modern applications and technologies  Delivery  Project Delivery Act as central point of contact for assigned bid opportunities and manage the system design decision making process Provide post-sales support to project managers and ensure a seamless handover process to the Delivery team Take ownership and responsibility for clients risks and issues, as and when required     Qualifications Essential skills/experience  Previous experience in a client-facing Presales or sales role A masters degree level qualification with equivalent business experience. Excellent skills in writing proposals spanning business and technology domains Must have a good understanding of Enterprise systems, Digital Technology including Cloud, Mobility, Big Data Analytics, Blockchain and IoT and preferably, some hands-on development experience Keen learner with the ability to understand the architecture of new and emerging technologies and objectively challenge the solutions proposed by the delivery team Great problem-solving and analytical abilities and experience in designing new solutions. Name: Start your new career as a Data Analyst
Description: Data is explodingThe demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of first-class data analysts and data scientists.If you are passionate about data, we have the best way to get you into your new data career.How does it work?The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx. In addition, you will be trained by our team of experts in all the soft skills needed to become an outstanding consultant.The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career.Do I get paid to learn?Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience.Key datesThe Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round in Sydney is April, August and November.The applications for the August 2022 intake close on the 30th of May, 2022.What’s in it for you  Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technologyBecome a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platformIt’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultantGain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in AustraliaLearn from the best data and analytics experts in AustraliaStudy in a creative workspace in central SydneyDetails of the role    Four months of classroom trainingFour client engagements, each 6 months longThe result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second yearWhen you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to youWe’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you have full working rights for AustraliaWhat we’re looking for   Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience. What we are looking for is:Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every dayData-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomesTech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy itCuriosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and whyResourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re askingFast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this roleCreativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible formsApplication ProcessWe do things differently and we’re proud of it. So forget about the application process you might be used to.Here’s how the process works:Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us!The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the applicationWe are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

Name: Director, Risk - Digital, Data & Analytics
Description: This is an outstanding opportunity to join one of Australia's major Banking groups in a senior, strategic and influential risk oversight role.  The position reports to the General Manager Risk and will be responsible for providing expert 2nd Line review, challenge and advice across the Digital, Data and Analytics (DD&A) and Customer Onboarding portfolios, with a broader objective of driving and embedding more effective risk management practices and controls throughout the Business.     This will include managing programs of work in response to various regulatory changes facing the industry, and will require significant stakeholder engagement and influencing skills.  Specifically, your responsibilities will include:  Proactively lead Operational Risk & Compliance Oversight capability for the DD&A and Customer Onboarding business/functions, ensuring that key business risks are identified, assessed and continually monitored; Engage with key business leaders and senior stakeholders to ensure they are aware of and executing their risk management accountabilities on an ongoing basis; Act as the 2IC/delegate to the GM Risk as required; Undertake activities necessary to review and challenge the effectiveness of first line risks and controls and continually identify opportunities to support the first line to optimise return within risk appetite Provide expert advice on risk and compliance issues whilst contributing to the design of effective mitigation strategies and controls. Ensure any incidents/breaches, material risks, loss events and/or deviations from the Risk Management Framework are escalated and managed on a timely basis. Leverage specialist skills and subject matter expertise from other Risk teams as required.  This is a business critical role that will require you to keep abreast of marketplace, regulation and business specific developments within digital banking, data and customer onboarding.  You will act as a subject matter expert on data and digital/financial product, KYC, and broader risk measurement considerations whilst ensuring risk & compliance disciplines is understood and adhered to by the business.   Tertiary qualified in a numerical discipline with post graduate qualifications desirable, you have 10+ years’ professional experience in financial services risk management, with a proven history in supporting the delivery of strategic initiatives that positively change and drive business performance in a safe and sustainable manner.  Experience with digital, data or customer onboarding related areas would be highly regarded.    For more information about this opportunity, please contact Tim Carmichael at SMC Executive on 0409 154 322 otherwise to apply, please click on the Apply link below.

You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to youWe’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you have full working rights for AustraliaWhat we’re looking for   Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience. What we are looking for is:Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every dayData-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomesTech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy itCuriosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and whyResourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re askingFast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this roleCreativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible formsApplication ProcessWe do things differently and we’re proud of it. So forget about the application process you might be used to.Here’s how the process works:Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us!The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the applicationWe are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

Name: Data Analyst
Description: At the Y our vision is simple – Amplify Your Voice. Shape Our Community. Challenge Our World.  We believe in the power of inspired young people.About the opportunityWorking with a diverse organisation with varied lines of business you'll be exposed to technologies old an new as we modernise business systems and mature our practices around all things data.  As a Data Analyst you will:  Focus on data modelling, design, analysis and interpreting services used to understand the Y’s data, building knowledge and information that enhances our business processes, products and services as well as deeper understanding of our customer and staff. Build, deploy, and maintain data support tools, metadata inventories, visualisation and definitions for database file/table creation. Work closely with members of the Data & Development team as well as the broader IT team and stakeholders across the Y in order to identify, recommend, develop, model, analysis, implement and support data and analytics solutions to satisfy their information needs.  This is a 12 month full time opportunity with potential for permanency.  You'll combine working from home with working from our Box Hill offices 1 to 2 days per week.  About youYou'll really enjoy creative problem solving and engaging with project and business stakeholders to understand and service data needs.  In addition you will:  Excellent SQL skills using SQL Server and Azure SQL Database Visualisation experience using Power BI Data extraction using SSIS and Azure Data Factory Exposure to finance systems such as TechOne would be highly advantageous.  At the Y, we are committed to empowering all Children and Young People to feel safe and be safe. As such, we ensure that all of our candidates are appropriately screened (including police check, working with children check and reference checks). To learn more about our commitment to safeguarding children and young people visit victoria.ymca.org.auIn keeping with current Victorian health directions it is a requirement that staff attending our facilities are fully vaccinated. Please be aware that you will be required to provide evidence of your vaccination status as part of the recruitment process. About the Y At the Y, we believe in the power of inspired young people. A community not-for-profit organisation with 17 million participations annually across Australia. 5,000 staff and volunteers serve at more than 150 locations every day. We partner with government and private capital to deliver programs and services that include community recreation, adventure and stadium sports, camping, learn to swim, children's programs, early learning, youth services, and social enterprises.  Benefits  At the YMCA, we value our people. Working for us means you’ll enjoy great work/life balance and a range of benefits which improve your wellbeing and help you develop as an individual, such as:    Flexible working arrangements   Opportunities for career development and growth   Free access to gyms, recreation, and aquatics centres across the state   Free access to the Virtual Y – online health and wellness    How to Apply  Working for the YMCA is a rewarding and challenging experience for those with a positive attitude, zest for life and who seek to contribute to the bigger picture. If this is you, click the Apply button or email careers.vic@ymca.org.au for further information.

Name: Customer Experience Specialist (On-Site)
Description: Winner of 2022 Australian Financial Review (AFR) BOSS Magazine Best Places to Work for Employee Experience! Check out a message from our CEO below!Who We AreVista is a Global e-commerce powerhouse with a dynamic and exciting entrepreneurial culture. Vista creates customer value (and delight) through accessible, cutting-edge technology. We are the marketing partner to millions of small businesses around the world. For more than 20 years, and with over 9000 team members Globally, we use our love of all things tech, design, manufacturing, and customer care to help small businesses feel big.Your New RoleDo you live and breathe improving customer experience? Do you like being in the action? Where the rubber hits the road? Are you good at connecting people and resolving problems? This is a pivotal role, acting as the main contact point, between the Melbourne manufacturing facility, third party fulfillers and customer contact centres to deliver on our high expectations to customers.This position holder will advocate for customers in manufacturing, by providing strategic support and direction. You will partner with manufacturing and our customer service teams, forging and maintaining strong relationships between the departments, streamlining communications and operations, whilst working together to mitigate customer impacting issues and improve the end-to-end customer experience.As part of the role, you will be responsible for coordinating and carrying out customer remediation activities, including owning the reporting requirements and leading communications between departments to ensure all stakeholders are advised of emerging issues. As the go to person for our manufacturing sites, you will be able to jump on, provide operational support and ensure coverage during lively, peak and holiday periods. Developing good global relationship is key to maximising the value of both global and local changes implemented from this group.Your role will involve:Representing the CARE In Manufacturing department locally and internationally, in cross-functional projects and meetings by providing feedback on customer experience and updates on current initiatives.Leading and maintaining global relationships and expectations between manufacturing, our call centres and central teams.Maintaining and continuously improving the feedback and communication process between Operations, Quality and Logistics teamsProactively allying and collaborating closely with internal and external team members to continuously enhance customer satisfaction and ensure compliance with high quality standardsProactively developing new processes to prevent process failures targeting significant increases in customer satisfactionMaintaining a robust remediation and reporting process, through identifying, coordinating, and providing feedbackCompiling statistics, interpreting data and taking appropriate action to ensure important metrics, quality criteria and individual goals are metCreating and sharing valuable customer insights to the local manufacturing teams through ad-hoc, daily, weekly, and monthly operational meetings, incorporating the use of customer feedback, imagery, and data sets to support user stories.Continuously being responsible for, reviewing, and providing recommendations and inputs on the CARE processes and frameworks to find opportunities and build on the team’s ability to deliver a strong program of advocacy and support for our customers.Line management of two direct reports.Providing support for all other tasks as required.Key Responsibilities:Strategic ownership of credits and complaints framework and global reportingReporting and providing recommendations on credit and complaint reduction for the ANZ & Singapore Lines of Business (LOB)Reporting and providing recommendations on remediation strategy, customer impact and cost to the LOB as well as driving improvementsBuild and maintain solid relationships with manufacturing teams through participation in projects and meetings, including delivering customer feedback content relevant to the local teams on a regular cadenceLine management, coaching and mentoringActing as the POC for CIM in global and local meetings, to share insights, updates on initiatives as well as flag emerging issues and trends.In return you will bring:Tertiary qualifications, preferably in commerce, business or similarProven track record in customer satisfaction improvementsExperience in a high-volume manufacturing facility (preferred)Excellent communication and presentation skillsProficient in data analyticsLine management experience with the ability to coach on the jobAble to paint the big picture and extremely detail focusedAble to provide direction to others, and also jump on the tools to do process work as required and your own manual analysisStrong stakeholder engagement and management skillsStrong project management skillsAbility to create a positive and inspiring working atmosphereHybrid model both on site at our Deer Park manufacturing facility and remote working model – with the expectation of remote attendance at some early and late weekly meetingsWhy You'll Love Working HereWe’re an inclusive community.We believe in the unique contributions of everyone within a diverse, global organisation. We work together to empower each other, creating a space in which each of us can spark our next great idea.We’re growing. That means you can too.We’re becoming the expert design and marketing partner to small businesses. We’re passionate about what we want to achieve, so we leverage our growth to support your ambitions and help you achieve your career goals.Some of our Perks:Paid Parental LeaveAn inclusive way of working through our Vista BehavioursAn entrepreneurial cultureHolistic 24/7 Wellbeing support for you and your familyOnsite Physio ProgramWellbeing LeaveBirthday leavePurchased leaveFocussed time for learning & developmentFlexible ways of workingEqual Opportunity Employer:Vista, a Cimpress company, is an Equal Opportunity employer committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity and inclusion.

Name: Market Data Analyst
Description: About the company:  Working for one of the big 4 banks in Australia as a Market Data Analyst to join the Market Data Team to be involved in delivering, integrating APIs, and be responsible maintaining the entire company’s Market Data Platform and Products.    Responsibilities        Working in a fast-paced Markets environment, you will use your FX, Equity and Commodities knowledge to drive efficient Data transfers. Name: Data Analyst - Strategic Store Space Optimisation Initiatives
Description: Data Analyst - Strategic Store Space Optimisation InitiativesAre you looking for an opportunity to combine your analytical skills with your ability to communicate a compelling story and build great relationships? If so, this is the ideal role for you!  Be an advocate for the use of customer-focused data and insights in the business Work with a team that supports growth and career development Norwest based with WFH flexibility About the Role As we continue to increase our customer focus and lead the food market within Australia we will continue to place a greater emphasis on strategic thinking and the ongoing development of a high-performing Commercial team.You will have the opportunity to work on one of the biggest strategic initiatives within the Woolworths business - to deliver a differentiated offer for our customers, leveraging our data and insights to inform our space strategy and ranging decisions.About the Role The Macro Space Analyst is positioned within the Space and Insights team and is responsible for analysing space utilisation and performance within our stores. The individual will be responsible for deriving data-driven, fact-based recommendations to ensure store designs are customer-centric and maximise the shopping experience for our customers. Key responsibilities include, however not limited to: Partner with our Merchandising & Space Tribe in the delivery of tailored stores through data-driven space management As an analyst, you will assist with the delivery of customer-focused floor plans, optimising space allocation across departments and categories, while driving continuous improvement initiatives Deriving data-led insights, providing recommendations on space strategy and striving to maximise our Return on Space Identify store opportunities through structured analysis and problem solving across different areas; support the build and delivery of multi-store programs driving significant incr. sales and profit outcomes Incorporate strategic insights from qualitative and quantitative consumer and category research Consult and collaborate confidently with stakeholders across the business to achieve desired outcomes  We Offer  An exciting career - As our business grows, so do the opportunities for our team members Strong career progression and succession opportunities into more senior strategy positions or other business roles across Woolworths Group Paid parental leave, Headspace Days Strong mentorship and development; opportunity to collaborate with some of the brightest and best minds in Australia Flexible working arrangements, excellent employee benefits & unparalleled growth opportunities  We value diversity and aim to create a vibrant and inclusive workforce that reflects the communities we serve.  About You  You are an analytical thinker, with capability of breaking information into component parts, patterns, and relationships & with a passion to understand customer behaviour and its links to commercial outcomes. You will have strong experience in interpreting data and deriving actionable insights to make recommendations for commercial strategies. You are a critical thinker who is able to adapt to new situations, and know-how to maximise value, sometimes, with limited information and inputs.  You will have:   A minimum of 1-2 years experience in relevant roles e.g analyst, category executive, sales analyst, account executive - Required Confident communicator and storyteller; with strong visualisation, verbal, and written skills - Required Advanced Excel functions e.g. pivot tables, formulas, and conditional formatting; with basic SQL skills a plus  Bachelor Degree in Business, Marketing, Finance or related subject or equal professional experience - Desirable Understands the FMCG industry and commercial processes of Woolworths and Suppliers - Desirable  If you share our customer-first culture and enjoy influencing stakeholders, & meet a number of requirements (and not all), we encourage you to submit your application #work180  Apply via www.wowcareers.com.au or alternatively connect with us on Linkedin for further information    Grow with the Group Woolworths Group has announced it will be requiring Australian team members to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 (subject to medical and religious exemptions). As an inclusive, team-first company, our people are at the core of everything we do.  We care deeply about creating a workplace where our team members feel valued, respected and empowered. We are committed to providing equal opportunity regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation or life stage. We are proud to be recognised as a Gold Tier Employer in the Australian Workplace Equality Index for LGBTQ+ inclusion and as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality by the Workplace Gender Equality Agency. As our Group continues to evolve, innovate and support our communities, we encourage our team members to do the same with their own careers, by providing ongoing opportunities to grow and make a real difference.  We value flexibility, and encourage our team members to work in ways that meet their work/life commitments and support their wellbeing.  We work hard to create a safe and inclusive environment for all, and most importantly, we're all about creating better experiences - for our customers and for each other. We'd love to hear from You If you meet a number of the requirements, but not all, we encourage you to submit your application. You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn [link removed] or via www.wowcareers.com.au [link removed]. #LI #work180. Our Talent Acquisition Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. Woolworths Group is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

Name: Casual Registered Nurse
Description: IQVIA is looking for Registered Nurses who are interested in joining one of our many at home patients programs.This program is directed at previously treated patients with cancer.Administration: IV cannulation infusionPatient visits: Fortnightly, +/- 2 days, or 28 days +/- 2 days depending on the dose. Name: Analyst - Real-World Solutions

Name: Business Intelligence Analyst
Description: Business Intelligence AnalystAbout the Company: Founded in 2002, Maas Group Holdings Pty Ltd (MGH) is a leading independent Australian construction materials, equipment and services provider focused on growing civil, infrastructure and mining end markets. MGH is a public listed company on the ASX, MGH is a multi-national conglomerate experiencing sustained growth across its key business units of Property Development, Civil Works, Plant Hire, Construction Materials, Electrical and Under Ground Mining & Tunneling. MAAS Groups continued growth is underpinned by a substantial committed delivery pipeline of projects and further investment strategies in infrastructure projects by state and Commonwealth Governments over the next 3-5 years as well as local governments building better communities. About the role: An exciting opportunity exists for a contractor as a Business Intelligence Analyst and will be responsible for EDW maintenance and continuous development to drive business intelligence.  The analyst will administer, maintain the (EDW) while developing the systems used to present financial and operational metrics. This includes supporting systems integration, dimension mapping for timely and meaningful management reporting across Maas Group of Companies. Duties include: Accountable for understanding business stakeholders’ data requirements, documenting data interfaces and data mappings, and analysing and interpreting data; understand and participate in data sourcing activities; act as Data SMEDevelop business and technical requirement documents; design and execute Data Quality checks; support Data modelling; maintain Business Metadata in the Azure Enterprise Data Warehouse through to visualisation from Power BiManage and collect all business metadata.Manage all data integration points and confirm all dimensions.Analyse data and present data through reports that aid data in formed decision-makingCreate customize charts and custom calculations as per requirementsCreate dashboards and interactive visual reports using Power BIConvert business requirements into technical specifications and decide timeline to accomplishAct as a key participant in business improvement projects for aligning key data requirements of the business and project outcomes.Drive development of reporting to ensure the continuous improvement of business intelligenceSupport quality assurance and user acceptance testing; provide post production support for both maintenance and enhancement solutionsChampion data driven initiatives and coach managers to enforce standards in all development initiatives involving data modelling, data quality, data dictionary consistency across systems and meta data management. Coordination of suppliers and or resources on projects Assist the business with financial transformation, driving process improvement initiativesWork with advisers to ensure development and maintenance projects are on time and budgetRespectfully challenge team members with a mindset of best practice and continuous improvementKnowledge & Skills required include: Minimum experience of 2 or 3 years working with BI tools, or any data-specific roles. Sound knowledge of database management is expected in the forms of SQL querying, data modeling, data warehousing, business intelligence, and OLAP (Online Analytical Processing). Strong data analytics skills with an ability to see the big picture and communicate insights in layman’s terms to relevant stakeholders. The candidate will be able to drill-down data and visualise data in the best possible way through charts/reports/dashboards. Proven ability developing custom BI solutions. This includes understanding technical aspects as well as software development architecture to transform requirements into technical presence.Strong controllership and results orientation.Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Dynamics and Excel is desirable.Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment.Experience with integration of systems and businessesA hard working, collaborate and hands on attitude who can demonstrate excellent judgment.Takes ownership of outcomes and can balance accuracy with timeliness. You can learn more about Maas Group Holdings by visiting our website. https://maasgroup.com.au/

Name: Employer Brand Specialist
Description:
We are looking for an Employer Brand Specialist to unleash their creativity and help us attract the best and brightest to William Buck.
We know we are great, but we want you to help tell our story and showcase our genuine and compelling - EVP. 
We want you to motivate people to push the apply button!
Your role will involve implementing new and exciting ideas and technology. We want you to push the boundaries to drive and execute our employer brand strategy including content creation and amplification. 
This role is focused on engaging and connecting with our audience. We need you to find innovative ways to share the authentic stories of life at William Buck, helping us to attract more great talent who fit our culture and values. 
We want our EVP to competitively differentiate William Buck in the talent market and to resonate with candidates from the moment they first hear about us, to when they settle into their role, and years later when they are still with us.
Obviously, ROI still needs to be top of mind, so you will focus on how we can leverage data-driven analytics to make the biggest possible impact
You will have experience in: 
Identifying and implementing a variety of bespoke sourcing channels, attracting talent to meet current and future workforce needs 
Designing and executing employment brand strategies, developing recruitment marketing campaigns and changing the landscape of attracting talent through employer branding
Candidate experience, onboarding and engagement of current talent
Marketing strategy development
Internal communications and stakeholder management including coaching at a senior level
Management of multiple projects and working to deadlines
Thinking creatively about words, pictures, and videos and how to best use these to make us stand out as exciting and desirable employer of choice
Data Analytics and using feedback to measure and evaluate effectiveness of activities
If this opportunity excites you as much as it does us, we would love to meet you!

Name: Data Platform Architect
Advertiser: Talent – SEEK Recruitment Agency of the Year | 7 Time Winner
Description: Our client is an industry leading, innovative and iconic Australian Organisation that has been awarded (on multiple occasions) for being a major adopter of new technologies, and a highly visible Cloud focussed approach. The opportunities to make a difference within excitingly new as well as inflight initiatives are unlimited in this ever-changing technology landscape.You will be part of a highly collaborative and growing network of technology and data experts, who are taking on today’s biggest, most complex business challenges using the latest data and analytics technologies. Our client is committed to nurturing your talent in their highly inclusive culture that values diversity. You will have an opportunity to work in a team of Cloud Data Engineer, Data Modelers and Data Architects covering all aspects of Data including Data Management, Data Governance and Data Migration. What you need:·        Around 7 years of experience with Data warehousing methodologies and techniques.·        5-6 years of experience with the Azure Data architecture in migration, methods and cloud data solutions.·        4 years   working in implementing data & analytics platforms ·        Well experienced working in the data architecture space·        Experience in AGILE projects and delivering business value from the technical assets·        Exposure working with SAP technologies·        Exposure in Spark, Scala, Python, SQL scripting languages.·        Experience working on relational databases like SQL DB/DW and NoSQL Platforms like HBase, MongoDB, Cassandra etc.·        Have strong technical competency working with Azure cloud platform services and technologies·        Experience in data modelling with strong implementation background in Data Vault ·        Experience working with streaming capabilities and lambda architectureSome of the below certifications will see you in good stead for this role:·        AZ-303: Microsoft Azure Architect Technologies·        AZ-304: Microsoft Azure Architect Design·        DP-200 Implementing an Azure Data Solution·        DP-201 Designing an Azure Data Solution·        Implementing DevOps on Azure platformIf the role appeals to you please apply now, or reach out and connect with Aman Singh 0405 33 0001

Name: Senior Data Analyst
Description: About Us...DBM Consultants have been providing data-empowered consulting services to some of Australia’s biggest organisations for 30 years. We deliver critical evidence-based advice to drive strategic decision-making and enhance customer experiences. We are widely regarded as one of the best agencies for quantitative research and our flagship syndicated study, DBM Atlas, is  Australia’s most comprehensive financial services data ecosystem offering robust, customer-experience driven insights that help our clients to drive growth, improvement and innovation. Our team regularly receives external recognition including winning Campaign Agency of the Year Awards for three years running (2019, 2020 and 2021) for the high value work we provide our clients and the engaging environment we offer our staff. About the Role...DBM Atlas is the most comprehensive financial services database of its kind in Australia, comprising over 80,000 respondents per year and has been running for 10+ years so you can just imagine the power of the data we have at our fingertips! We also have lots of data partnerships in place In this role, you'll play a key role in supporting our researchers to deliver our research programs by supporting a range of survey scripting, sample management and data analysis tasks. You will use a range of tools including IBM Dimensions, SQL, Python, and Excel VBA. You will be someone who takes pride in their work and are able to deliver to deadlines. You will love to get it right every time! As a senior role within our team, some experience within a market research agency, and/or an understanding of the research process would be ideal. About Life at DBM… At DBM we're proud of our culture. We have three core values: Deliver the WOW Factor; Fuel the Team; Be Bold.We work hard, but also like to have fun and think it’s the people that make DBM a truly great place to work. In addition to a competitive remuneration package we give our people the opportunity to share in our success through our performance bonus scheme. We encourage all our people to pave their own career path and find ways to grow through our consistent DBM Academy learning and development sessions. We also offer a range of initiatives and benefits to foster a highly engaging workforce and ensure our people maintain as sense of balance, including: Generous leave offerings including a day off every year for your birthday, paid parental leave, wellbeing leave, study leave and the opportunity to purchase additional annual leaveReward and recognition programs including opportunities for performance bonuses every 6 months Share in our profit through our company performance scheme Flexible working arrangements including flexibility to work from both home and the office Access to corporate discounts including health insurance, gym memberships and retail productsMonthly technology allowance to help cover to the cost of your personal phone or home internetA health and wellbeing program including monthly meditation sessions, annual flu vaccination, a wellness hub and access to free counselling through our Employee Assistance Program.  DBM is committed to the principle of equal opportunity employment  and would welcome any requests for reasonable adjustments or flexible work arrangements. This role can be done on either a full-time or 4-day week (0.8FTE basis). We are also committed to providing equity and through our DBM-Access program we commit to ensuring any candidates who are Indigenous Australians, Refugee/Asylum seekers or have a disability will be immediately shortlisted for interview for guaranteed ‘access’ to hiring managers. Please indicate your request for DBM-Access in your cover letter.Only candidates with work rights in Australia will be considered.

Name: Big Data Engineer
Description:
About Us: Infosys is a global leader in next-generation digital services and consulting. We enable clients in more than 50 countries to navigate their digital transformation. With over four decades of experience in managing the systems and workings of global enterprises, we expertly steer our clients through their digital journey. We do it by enabling the enterprise with an AI-powered core that helps prioritize the execution of change. We also empower the business with agile digital at scale to deliver unprecedented levels of performance and customer delight. Name: Asset Management Solution Architect
Description:
IntroductionAt IBM, we know that transformation drives change, and it is in our DNA to continuously transform. Our Business Transformation Consultants help drive large scale change that spans IBM business units and geographies. As a part of this team, you will have the unique opportunity to be a part of driving IBM’s ongoing transformation as a company that continuously innovates and leads the market.Your Role and ResponsibilitiesWith the rise of new and exciting technological trends including machine learning, AI, IoT, Big Data and Predictive Analytics, IBM Consulting is looking for an experienced Asset Management Solution Architect to join our Asset Manufacturing and Optimisation team.You will have Tier 1 package solution implementation experience and experience leading the development of Asset Performance Management solutions and models on modern cloud data platforms. You will be a trusted consultant for your clients for both your functional and technical expertise in the Asset Management space (EAM, APM, AIP).

You will be part of an ANZ and global innovative and dynamic team solving complex client challenges with innovative solutions
Your responsibilities in this role will include:

Proactively engage with clients
Understand client needs and define technical and non functional requirements;
Define the technical solution in the context of the client’s IT infrastructure, their IT policies and data standards, and collaborate with the client’s IT team
‘Lead from the front’ and deliver consulting and mentor team members
Participate in client meetings to communicate status or give demos in showcase workshops
Work effectively individually and with team members toward customer satisfaction and success
Responsible for providing effort estimates
Participate in meetings, such as sprint planning, stand-ups, demos, and retrospectives
Be keenly aware of timelines and budgeting to deliver in a timely manner
Ability to understand complex technical concepts and present them in simple terms to non-technical team members and clients

To ensure success in the role you will possess the following skills:

Excellent client advisory and relationship building skills
Excellent communication and writing skills (to attend client meetings and speak with clarity, write requirements in clear business terms, etc.)
Demonstrated experience with Packaged Solution consulting in the Enterprise Asset Management, Asset Investment Planning, Asset Performance Management space
Demonstrated experience with solutioning for Azure / AWS, IoT, Edge.
At least 5 years’ experience architecting solutions in the Asset Management Space (APM, EAM, AIP, Digital Twins, etc.)
Experience with putting together formal solution architectures using industry recognised architecture frameworks
Excellent experience in modelling tools (Visio, Aris, UML)
Highly desirable:

Experience in Natural Resources (Oil and gas, mining, Energy and Utilities)
Experience in developing predictive and asset optimisation models using AI/ML/Optimisation techniques
Formal qualifications as a Solution Architect
Experience with other Tier 1 consulting firms
Experience working with large teams of multi-disciplinary consultants distributed in multiple geographies
Understanding of Sustainability drivers in Asset Intensive industries,
Prior Consulting experience in Reliability Centred Maintenance
Working understanding of ISO standards related to Asset Management such as ISO55001, ISO14224



Required Technical and Professional ExpertiseAs above
Preferred Technical and Professional ExpertiseAs above

Name: Staff Big Data DevOps Engineer
Description:
Company Description


At ServiceNow, our technology makes the world work for everyone, and our people make it possible. We move fast because the world can’t wait, and we innovate in ways no one else can for our customers and communities. By joining ServiceNow, you are part of an ambitious team of change makers who have a restless curiosity and a drive for ingenuity. We know that your best work happens when you live your best life and share your unique talents, so we do everything we can to make that possible. We dream big together, supporting each other to make our individual and collective dreams come true. The future is ours, and it starts with you.  With more than 7,400+ customers, we serve approximately 80% of the Fortune 500, and we're on the 2021 list of FORTUNE World's Most Admired Companies®.  Learn more on Life at Now blog and hear from our employees about their experiences working at ServiceNow.


Job Description


What you get to do in this role

Architect and drive the end-end Big Data deployment automation from vision to delivering the automation of Big Data foundational modules (Cloudera CDP), prerequisite components and Applications leveraging Ansible, Puppet, Terraform, Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes to deliver end-end deployment automation across all ServiceNow environments.
Automate Continuous Integration / Continuous Deployment (CI/CD) data pipelines for applications leveraging tools such as Jenkins, Ansible, and Docker.
Deploy, monitor, maintain and support Big Data infrastructure, applications on ServiceNow Cloud and Azure environments.
Fine tune and troubleshoot Hadoop components and other data analytics tools in the environment: HDFS, YARN, Hive, HBase. Spark, Kafka, RabbitMQ, Impala, Kudu, Redis, Hue, Kerberos, Tableau, Grafana, MariaDB, and Prometheus.
Provide production support to resolve critical Big Data pipelines and application issues and mitigating or minimizing any impact on Big Data applications. Collaborate closely with Site Reliability Engineers (SRE), Customer Support (CS), Developers, QA and System engineering teams in replicating complex issues leveraging broad experience with UI, SQL, Full-stack and Big Data technologies.



Qualifications


To be successful in this role you have

10+ years of overall experience with minimum 7+ years in Big Data DevOps 
Demonstrated advanced level experience in delivering end-end deployment automation leveraging Puppet, Ansible, Terraform, Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes 
Deep understanding of Hadoop/Big Data Ecosystem and professional experience in Hadoop administration
Experience securing Hadoop stack with Sentry, Ranger, LDAP, Kerberos KDC
Working knowledge of Cloudera CDP/CDH installation, administration and migration.
Good knowledge in querying and analyzing large amount of data on Hadoop HDFS using Hive and Spark Streaming and working on systems like HDFS, YARN, Hive, HBase. Spark, Kafka, RabbitMQ, Impala, Kudu, Redis, Hue, Tableau, Grafana, MariaDB, and Prometheus.

NOTE: Due to the nature of work related to this position, the employee needs to be an Australian Citizen with the capability to obtain a security clearance.


Additional Information


ServiceNow is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, creed, religion, sex, sexual orientation, national origin or nationality, ancestry, age, disability, gender identity or expression, marital status, veteran status or any other category protected by law. All new employees hired in the United States are required to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19, subject to such exceptions as required by law. If hired, you will be required to submit proof of full vaccination or have an approved accommodation, by your start date. Visit our Candidate FAQ page to learn more. If you require a reasonable accommodation to complete any part of the application process, or are limited in the ability or unable to access or use this online application process and need an alternative method for applying, you may contact us at talent.acquisition@servicenow.com for assistance. For positions requiring access to technical data subject to export control regulations, including Export Administration Regulations (EAR), ServiceNow may have to obtain export licensing approval from the U.S. Government for certain individuals. All employment is contingent upon ServiceNow obtaining any export license or other approval that may be required by the U.S. Government. Please Note: Fraudulent job postings/job scams are increasingly common. Click here to learn what to watch out for and how to protect yourself. All genuine ServiceNow job postings can be found through the ServiceNow Careers site. Work personas Work personas are categories that are assigned to employees depending on the nature of their work. Employees will fall into one of three categories: Remote, Flexible or Required in Office.  Required in Office A required in office work persona is defined as an employee who is contracted to work from or aligned to a ServiceNow-affiliated office. This persona is required to work from their assigned workplace location 100% of the work week based on the business needs of their role. Flexible  A flexible work persona is defined as an employee who is contracted to work from or aligned to a ServiceNow-affiliated office and will work from their assigned workplace location roughly 3 days/week or less (generally around 40-60% of the work week). Flexible employees may choose to work the remaining working time from their workplace location or home. Flexible employees are required to work within their state, province, region, or country of employment. Remote A remote work persona is defined as an employee who performs their responsibilities exclusively outside of a ServiceNow workplace and is not contracted or aligned to a ServiceNow-affiliated office, including those whose place of work (pursuant to their terms and conditions of employment) is their home. Remote employees are required to work within their state, province, region, or country of employment.
