Name: Data Engineer
Description:
Job Description:
DXC Technology (NYSE:DXC) - where brilliant people embrace change and seize opportunities to advance their careers and amplify customer success.  We use the power of technology to deliver mission critical IT services that move the world. DXC.com
DXC Analytics provides customers with access to industry leading analytics technologies and people.  DXC Analytics has an opening for a Data Engineer in Sydney or Melbourne.
The role:
As Data Engineer you will be developing solutions to solve complex financial crime problems, automatically identifying and matching customer data as well as creating pipelines that enable dynamic entity resolution using next-gen analytics technologies for our Tier 1 clients.  You will support our customers in connecting the dots using advanced network analytics to create context and unlocking the hidden value in their data.
You will work as a member of a large data engineering team and be responsible for managing, transforming and cleansing high volume data, providing advice and technical consulting to our customers in the adoption of big data analytics technologies.
What You Will Bring to the Role:

A minimum of 2 years of experience in big data technologies & developing data-processing pipelines
Working knowledge of Spark or similar big data product (e.g. Hadoop or Elasticsearch)
Understanding of functional programming languages would be highly desirable (e.g. Scala)
Experience working with a common programming language used in analytics (e.g. Python, Java, R)
Experience with public cloud platforms
Sound analytical skills and attention to detail
Positive attitude with a passion for supporting your team and clients; and offering creative solutions and insights
Australian citizenship or Permanent Resident Status for Australia

Our culture and benefits
DXC is committed to building better futures for our customers, colleagues, environment, and communities. We take care of each other and foster a culture of inclusion, belonging and corporate citizenship. We put this to action developing and implementing societal initiatives within our Social Impact Practice. #WeAreDXC
Our “people first” philosophy means we offer competitive remuneration, benefits, training and career opportunities that reflect our commitment to improving the lives of our employees, and the communities in which we live and work. 
We are an Equal Opportunity Employer 
DXC is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and we welcome submissions from people from all walks of life. We celebrate our diversity and recognize it is the unique contributions of our people that give us our edge. We stand by the ‘bring your whole-self to work’ philosophy. It is our inclusive culture that powers our results, and our company grows only if our people grow.
For more information, visit http://www.dxc.technology/analytics/offerings/139783-services_solutions

Name: Senior Data Engineer
Description:
Senior Data Engineer – ETL Developer

You are determined to stay ahead of the latest Big Data, ML, Decisioning, Visualisation and Data warehouse technologies
We're one of the largest and most advanced Data Engineering teams in the country
Together we can build state-of-the-art data solutions that power seamless experiences for millions of customers

Do work that matters
As an experienced data engineer with proven expertise in software development and a passion for providing data-driven solutions, you’re ahead of trends and work at the forefront of Big Data, ML, Decisioning, Visualisation and Data warehouse technologies.
Which is why we’re the perfect fit for you. Here, you’ll be part of a team of engineers going above and beyond to improve the standard of digital banking. Using the latest tech to solve our customers’ most complex data-centric problems.
To us, data is everything. It is what powers our cutting-edge features and it’s the reason we can provide seamless experiences for millions of customers from app to branch.
We’re responsible for CommBank’s key analytics capabilities and work to create world-leading capabilities for analytics, information management and decisioning. We work across the Teradata Group Data Warehouse, Hadoop Big Data Platform, Analytics Workbench for Machine Learning, Pega Decisioning, SAS, R, Tableau, Oracle BI, Ab Initio.
See yourself in our team
This is an exciting opportunity to join an engaging, dynamic and friendly team as an experienced Senior Data Egnineer - ETL Developer.
IMS&S team is responsible for providing input and direction to the data strategy components of
IMS & CommSec strategy. The roadmap of project activities related to supporting the information management target state.
Working with the group capabilities to leverage the future state of operational activities for the appropriate management, access, governance and quality of key data repositories. Act as a custodian of information assets and be the SMEs across all data focused activities such as - capture, store, transform and analyse. 
Key accountabilities includes:

Design and Implementation of solutions as per the agreed specifications
Attends to both business and technical considerations when developing solutions
Review business requirements and provide feedback and guidance on data requirements for database development
Review performance and scalability of SQL Server databases, highlighting areas of improvement to the team and management
Work closely with other teams to ensure the availability, robustness and functionality of the supported systems
Build, Develop, & Test robust and secure code.
Transformation of data and use of Data loading tools (ETL)
Contribute to the design of the ETL Layer and staging to target mappings
Working with business analysts to define business rules for data quality management and migration
Conduct the release & implementation to production
Create and promote pattern & framework based development, promote secure coding practices
Work with CI/CD initiatives and reduce legacy/technical debt

We are interested in people who:

Are experienced in design and development of Big Data, ML, Decisioning, Visualisation and Data warehouse applications
Are confident in building group data products from scratch, by integrating large sets of data derived from hundreds of internal and external sources
Have a natural drive to educate, communicate and positively influence a large stakeholder group

We use a broad range of tools, languages, and frameworks. We don’t expect you to know them all but experience or exposure with some of these (or equivalents) will set you up for success in this team;

5+ years of work experience with technical data concepts, data warehousing techniques, ETL-SSIS development, standard data structures and presentation tools. 
Design, develop and maintain ETL processes using SSIS.
Are confident in database developments - SQL Server, Oracle, Teradata.
SQL skills targeting performance optimisations, robustness and scalability, with ability to write complex SQL Code, SSIS packages
Managing the existing Data Marts and design and develop future data warehouse solutions 
Work with Onshore/Offshore team & partners for delivery
Desirable - GitHub enterprise, TeamCity, Octopus, PowerShell
Optional - Artifactory, SSRS, PowerBI

Working with us:
Whether you’re passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career with CommBank is for you.  
Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive, and flexible workplace with flexible work locations. One where we’re driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day. 
Here, you’ll thrive. You’ll be supported when faced with challenges and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We’re hiring engineers from across all of Australia, you’ll be empowered to do your best work and be given the choice on when and where that work happens. We really love working here, and we think you will too. 
The health and safety of our people, customers and communities is our number one priority. This means that we require all of our employees to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. Please speak to us if you have any questions about this based on your individual circumstances.

If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.
We're aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.
Advertising End Date: 22/07/2022

Name: Data Analyst | Data and Analytics
Description:
Data Analyst | Data and Analytics
 
 




 Location: 
 
 Melbourne
 
 



 Other locations: 
 
 Anywhere in Country
 
 



 Date: 
 
 24-Jun-2022
 
 


At EY, you’ll have the chance to build a career as unique as you are, with the global scale, support, inclusive culture and technology to become the best version of you. And we’re counting on your unique voice and perspective to help EY become even better, too. Join us and build an exceptional experience for yourself, and a better working world for all. 
The opportunity
EY DnA is the data and advanced analytics capability within EY Asia-Pacific, with over 500 specialist employees working across multiple industry sectors.
As a Data Analyst, you will support our clients in defining and implementing a data journey aligned with their strategic objectives. Some of your responsibilities will include:

Be a part of one of our successful delivery teams and get an opportunity to move into a more consultative role working across various data environments and helping our clients solve their business problems with data.
Be responsible for creating requirement specifications, analysing requirements, creating visual models, facilitating elicitation sessions, and digging around in the data when needed. 
Designing and building reports – capture data requirements for the client and team.
Creating requirements specifications, analysing requirements, creating visual models, facilitating workshop sessions, and using the necessary business analyst tools. 

To qualify for the role, you must have 
  

Worked in a similar Data Analyst position for at least 3-5 years with a focus on data management, data profiling and data quality
Ability to understand and identify business rules and processes
Conducted process mapping and requirements gathering workshops with non-technical stakeholders
Working with relational databases and database querying languages SQL, PL/SQL, T-SQL
Knowledge of Data Quality and Profiling/Cleansing
Have knowledge and experience of all phases of software development including requirements analysis, design, coding, testing, defect management.
Due to the nature of the client base, you MUST BE an Australian Citizen

Ideally, you’ll also have

Experience in engaging with both technical and non-technical stakeholders 
Strong consulting experience and background, including engaging directly with clients
Experience in SAP Finance, Procurement or SAP SuccessFactors HR & Payroll
Experience in a delivery role on Data Migration, Business Intelligence, Data Warehousing, Big Data or analytics projects 
Ability to problem-solve and think critically
Technical reconciliation and reporting skills
Some development experience would be advantageous but not essential

What We Offer
A tech career @ EY means working with 40,000 fellow technologists who are creating cutting edge applications in blockchain, AI, cloud, analytics, robotics and cyber, harnessing tech to power the human enterprise and build a more equitable, sustainable world. We offer world class training and a free Tech MBA to all our people. 
Globally at EY, we are committed to offer


Continuous learning: You’ll develop the mindset and skills to navigate whatever comes next.

Success as defined by you: We’ll provide the tools and flexibility, so you can make a meaningful impact, your way.

Transformative leadership: We’ll give you the insights, coaching and confidence to be the leader the world needs.

Diverse and inclusive culture: You’ll be embraced for who you are and empowered to use your voice to help others find theirs.
  

We hold a collective commitment to foster an environment where all differences are valued and respected, practices are equitable, and everyone experiences a sense of belonging. If you require any adjustments to the recruitment process in order to equitably participate, we encourage you to advise us at the time of application via contactrecruitment@au.ey.com or phone +61 3 8650 7788 (option 4).
The Exceptional EY Experience. It’s Yours To Build.
EY | Building a better working world 
 
EY exists to build a better working world, helping to create long-term value for clients, people and society and build trust in the capital markets.  
 
Enabled by data and technology, diverse EY teams in over 150 countries provide trust through assurance and help clients grow, transform and operate.  
 
Working across assurance, consulting, law, strategy, tax and transactions, EY teams ask better questions to find new answers for the complex issues facing our world today.

Name: Senior Consultant Engineer
Description:
Senior Consultant Engineer

Job no: 778985
Business unit: Technology and Enterprise Operations
Position location: 700 Bourke St
Work type: Permanent Full time
Location: Aust - WA Metro



Opportunity for a Senior Consultant Engineer

Be part of an innovative and collaborative team culture
At NAB, we are committed to working flexibly

About the role
As a Senior Consultant Engineer, you will be part of the Foundational Platform Engineering team in Enterprise Data and Analytics that are building NABs strategic data lakehouse, and will be responsible for the design, development and deployment of capability aligned with the business roadmap and driving efficiencies that enhance availability, performance and stability of strategic data services.
What you’ll be doing
As an experienced Senior Consultant Engineer and an expert in the use of specific technologies and the software development discipline, you will be the ‘go to’ person to help plan, design, deliver and support features that deliver customer value and mature our service capabilities.  You will have broad experience in analysis, design, development, documentation, testing and support responsibilities and be a thought leader in driving best practices in the team.
What you’ll bring

Extensive demonstrated experience across DevOps, Cloud and Data Engineering
Experience designing and supporting API enabled cloud applications
Prior experience with CDC tools (HVR experience highly regarded) and Databricks
Technical skills in software delivery such as CI/CD, Automated Deployments, Automated Testing, Build Servers, Software / Source Code Configuration Management.
Solid experience in large scale data transformation, design and solution delivery experience of high-quality data processing pipelines and solutions in a professional services environment.
Experience in data lake or warehouse integrity and reconciliation; tracking and reconciling data movement and transformation.
Expertise in designing and building maintainable and scalable end to end big data solutions in HDFS, Kafka, Apache Spark, Hive, EMR, Airflow and Python or other similar tools.
Extensive knowledge of core AWS data services such as: S3, RDS, Redshift, Glue, Athena, DynamoDB, EMR, Kinesis, Kinesis Firehouse.
Ability to provide technical mentoring and guidance to less experienced members of the development team
Execute and drive hands-on design, to maximise and implement best practice CI/CD across the team.
Work with delivery teams to achieve success through the adoption of CI/CD and DevOps practices, processes and tooling.

What we can offer
From education and volunteer leave to learning benefits and banking discounts, we offer access to a wide range of employee benefits. You can learn more about these at http://www.nab.com.au/about-us/careers/working-at-nab/benefits

NAB, invested in you
At NAB, we believe success comes from our people. We're committed to supporting your talent and skills through your career, as you help us build a culture that affects change for our customers - and for the community too.
To be eligible to apply, you must have Australian or New Zealand citizenship or permanent residency status.

Name: Senior Analyst Data Engineer
Description:
Senior Analyst Data Engineer

Job no: 778488
Business unit: Technology and Enterprise Operations
Position location: 700 Bourke St
Work type: Permanent Full time
Location: Aust - VIC Metro


Opportunity for a Developer to join the Test Data Management team
Showcase your exceptional experience in Big Data and Data Engineering

At NAB, we are committed to flexible working 


A career that gives you more
Your career at NAB is about more than money, it's about serving our customers well and helping our communities prosper.
We have an opportunity for a Senior Analyst Engineer to join the Test Data Management (TDM) team. This team leads the TDM design as well as oversees the build, implementation and transition of TDM changes to TDM Operations.
About the role 
As a Senior Analyst Engineer, you will be responsible for supporting various service offerings related to the TDM Asset, primarily focussed on building, maintaining and supporting Big Data delivery automation pipelines utilising & promoting best DevOps practices. This role is both strategic and operational to ensure that technical solutions enable operational excellence, are secure, reliable, scalable, cost optimized and maintainable. 
What you’ll be doing 
Your role will include but not limited to: 

Creation and maintenance of delivery pipeline tooling. Including build/deploy/CI/infrastructure scripts, monitoring, logging 
Setting up automated environment provisioning that will setup secure cloud and on premise  
Supporting the infrastructure and application layer, both in Production and non-Production environments 
Supporting the build team (Dev and Test) to be self-sustained through training and troubleshooting 
Continually learning and researching best practices and tooling for Big Data delivery 

What you’ll bring 

Demonstrated experience in application development
Proven background in deploying and managing Big Data solutions 
Experience in designed and implemented CI/CD pipelines 
Strong working knowledge of test automation principles 
Demonstrated experience establishing environments in the cloud preferably AWS, and/or Azure
Working knowledge of Cloud (AWS) environments 
Strong hand-on experience on Hadoop & Docker

Name: CTRM Test Analyst
Description:
About Ampol:
Ampol is expanding into new and forward-facing Energy opportunities including e-mobility, hydrogen, batteries, renewables, and carbon. As the company executes on this vision, we are seeking to build leading digital and analytic capabilities with a deep connection to customers. 
About the role:
CTRM Test Analyst is responsible for creating and executing both manual and automated test scenarios. Key to this role is ensuring software systems, applications and enhancements meet with business demands, functional requirements and technical specifications and are fit to be deployed into production. 
Reporting to the CTRM QA Lead, the role is also responsible for planning, scheduling, and reporting of test outcomes to ensure the stake holder awareness of test efforts, issues, and agreement of test outcomes.
It is early in our journey, but we are moving quickly. This role will have the opportunity to contribute to the build of our systems capability and has substantial scope to influence its success.
We are looking for a detail-oriented team member with the drive to:

Perform static test reviews of the business requirements/User Stories and develop both manual and automated test scenarios for different phases of testing in a project (System Integration testing/End to End/UAT/Regression/NFR)
Execute test scenarios and ensure the test results are recorded in appropriate systems and defects are identified and managed
Setup Test Automation environments, prepare Test data and automation scripts based on agreed framework

You will be part of a great Program team located in Sydney, Singapore, Melbourne and Brisbane. We are culturally diverse with a massive range of skillsets and experiences, so if you love to learn then you will love our team.
About you:
You will ideally have more than 5 years of proven testing experience in CTRM domain or products or the IT Fuel supply chain space. Your experience will be supported by a tertiary qualification in Information Technology.
You will have demonstrated hands-on experience in the creation of Test Scenarios, Test Plans, Defect Reporting and Test Case design techniques for various test phases including sprints, system integration testing, end to end Testing and perf testing.

3 + years of Manual Testing and automation testing of complex architectures and applications using various industry standard automation tools
Hands on Testing experience in the CTRM/ETRM supply chain domain with products including Allegro, Endur, Findur, AgTech, EKA, Fusion etc. and/or industry is highly desirable  
Hands on experience in end to end trade life cycle testing across Front, Middle & Back offices(Trade execution, Valuations, supply operations, inventory management etc.)
Proficient in using Atlassian Tools like Jira and Confluence & test management tools like HP ALM, Test Rails, ACCELQ etc.
Experience working in both Agile
Experience in conducting automation feasibility analysis, Interface testing & perf testing
Clear and unambiguous communication with previous business partnering or consulting experience

Additionally, you will have:

Test automation frameworks and tools: ACCELQ, Selenium, BDD based framework
Understanding of CI/CD concepts
Experience in API testing and Microservices
General SQL &scripting knowledge for use in preparing bespoke Test automation scripts
ITSQB foundation certificate
Experience in Cloud Applications (Microsoft Azure, AWS) 
Experience in Big Data Analytics tools: SPLUNK

This is a 12 month maximum term contract which may have the opportunity to extend based on project requirements.
At Ampol we encourage vaccination against Covid-19 as an effective measure in helping to protect our people and our communities.
We’re an equal opportunity workplace. We not only embrace diversity and inclusion; we celebrate what makes you unique. We welcome applications from people of all ages, cultural backgrounds, and diverse sexualities and genders (including if you identify as transgender). We also highly encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples to apply for roles with Ampol.
Applications close on July 13, 2022.
Thank you to our prospective agency partners for your interest, we are not taking CVs at this time.

Name: Manager, Data Risk & Analytics, Group Audit
Description:
How will I help?
You will interact directly with technology and business units and other Group Audit home teams. You will participate in independent reviews to assess frameworks and policies, identify risks, validate controls and assess compliance with regulatory guides and standards across the Westpac Group to identify areas for remediation and opportunities for enhancement.
Major accountabilities:

Assist in audit planning, including the selection of audit scope to support the testing of processes, risks, controls and plans.
Execute audit fieldwork: 
 
Test the design and operating effectiveness of controls,
Identify and document audit issues using insights gained from executing audit fieldwork, data analytics and data visualisation, and agreeing management action plans.
Collaborate within own home team and with Group Audit business audit teams and subject matter experts in risk and compliance.
Coach and develop others in GA to uplift their data risk management and data assurance capabilities.
 
Assist in the reporting stages of the audit engagement, including preparing and discussing audit reports with management.  These audit reports form the basis of the messages reported to the Westpac Group Board Audit Committee on a quarterly basis.
Able to collaborate closely with diverse stakeholders (senior and junior level, technical and non-technical) in a team environment. Can also work independently and prioritise allocated tasks and time accordingly.
Participate in home team and Group Audit initiatives and continuous improvement initiatives, such as executing Group Audit’s data risk management strategy.
 What’s in it for me?We’ll back you with a great team and all the opportunities you'd expect from a company whose purpose is to help Australians and New Zealanders succeed. You’ll be working for an organisation that supports development, internal career moves and flexible working.
What do I need?

We are looking for a high-performing individual who has at least 3 years of data risk management experience, preferably in audit, risk, assurance or consulting with a strong knowledge of, and capability with:

data risk management, including data governance, data quality management, data privacy and data security, and industry standard approaches such as DCAM;
APRA and other global guidelines on data risk management, including CPG-235 and BCBS 239;
enterprise data management frameworks, policies, standards, governance metrics and associated implementation risks;
stakeholder management (communication and influencing skills), project management and collaboration/relationship building skills;
proven team leadership, coaching and staff development skills, ability to solve complex problems, and identify root causes of issues.
  The following additional knowledge or experience will be highly desirable: 

a degree in Information Systems, Engineering, Maths or an equivalent field;
data analysis using approaches such as SQL, Alteryx and data visualisation;
information systems including databases, data warehouses, big data platforms, data governance tools;
financial services industry experience.
  What is it like to work there?As well as good pay and a great culture, joining the Westpac family means you’ll get some of the best banking, wealth and insurance benefits in the market. We back our employees by helping them work towards industry-recognised qualifications, using online learning, training modules and career planning tools for you to grow with us. We’ll even pay you to do volunteer or community work.  As an equal opportunity employer, we’re proud to have created a culture and work environment that values diversity and flexibility – and champions inclusion. 
How do I Apply?
Start here. Just click on the APPLY button.
The Westpac Group has implemented an Entry to Workplace Policy that requires employees and others entering our workplaces to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 by relevant dates set out in the policy (subject to applicable medical exemptions). Our employees are required to comply with the policy regardless of whether they are in customer-facing or non-customer-facing roles (as employees in non-customer-facing roles are required to attend the workplace under our Hybrid Working Strategy). Further, the Westpac Group is required to comply with State/Territory issued public health orders/directions which require relevant workers to be vaccinated against COVID-19 to enter workplaces.
By applying for this role, you acknowledge that you are aware of our Entry to Workplace Policy, and if you secure employment with us, you will be required to comply with the policy.

Name: Data Engineer
Description:
Data Engineer - Sydney Office - Permanent Full Time
Who We Are
We’re working to shine a light on all thing’s property. Our business is built around connecting the steps throughout the property journey to create a better experience for people. We call it the property marketplace, and it’s driven by our data.
As we change the way people engage with property, we need diverse thinkers to help us. So even if you don’t meet 100% of the following criteria, we’d love you to apply anyway. 
Your Purpose
We’re looking for a talented and experienced Data Engineer to join our data department team. The data team creates value for the Domain Group by building re-usable data assets that enable every single department in the group to deliver value from our data rapidly. We do this by maintaining data infrastructure to collect, designing and implementing data pipelines to create and deliver re-usable datasets.
A Day in the life
As part of the Domain Group, you’ll have the opportunity to work with all our areas to design data solutions across all aspects of our property eco-system, from listing and agent, to consumer behaviour, email, and sales data.

Ability to work in complex problem spaces and design datasets and solutions that reduce that complexity;
You’re at ease working with data, at the detail, and conceptually;
You are pro-active, creative and entrepreneurial;                                                                                                    
Leveraging data from a variety of sources to build internal and external dashboards and reports
Work with data engineers, product managers and product analysts to understand data needs.         
Attributes

3+ year experience working as a Data Engineer leading with complex environments and big data technologies;
Ability to read / write very complex SQL statements;
Experience in semi-structured and unstructured data is highly desirable;
Experience designing, building and operating data pipelines;
Airflow, dbt, SSIS (for legacy migration)
Experience with various ETL tools is good to have
SnowFlake experience is highly desirable;
AWS Experience (EC2, S3, EMR, etc) 
Experience on any programming languages(C#, Python, R);
Experience working on Tableau or any similar data visualization tool 

Why join us
We’re the perfect size for you to make a real impact, and we’ve created a working culture where you can be you. This means fun, safe spaces where you can enjoy a real sense of belonging:

We have industry leading parental leave and wellbeing policies in place
Perks include Domain Home Loans and Domain Insure discounts and 5 weeks annual leave
You'll enjoy ‘Perkbox’ discounts on a range of offerings across healthcare, entertainment, food and utilities
We’re driven by the belief that open minds open doors. We value the creativity and innovation that diversity of thought brings and are committed to building an inclusive workplace where you can be you.

What’s Next?
We promise to give your application our full attention and to get back to you with a response either way. If it’s a good match, one of our recruitment consultants will give you a call, so keep your phone handy.
We hope you’re excited by the possibilities of a career with us. 
Apply now to turn them into realities!

Thorough written and communication skills.

Sound skills to use all Microsoft Office packages.

Name: Data Scientist/Senior Data Scientist
Description:
Primary DetailsTime Type: Full timeWorker Type: EmployeeData Scientist/Senior Data Scientist
Location: NSW / VIC / QLD / SA / Remote
Type: Permanent, full time position (open to remote working)
At QBE, our purpose is to enable a more resilient future.
We’re an international insurer and reinsurer with a local presence in 27 countries.
Leveraging our deep expertise and insights, QBE offers commercial, personal and specialty products and risk management solutions to help people and businesses manage risks, build strength and embrace change to their advantage.
We’ve been cultivating resilience since 1886, when our founders started a marine insurance company in Townsville, Australia to give early pioneers a safeguard against uncertainty.
Today, we employ more than 11,600 people around the world, and our product portfolio includes property, motor, crop, energy, marine and aviation insurance.
The opportunity
Our Australia Pacific Data & Analytics team has evolved over the past 4 years since its inception, growing to 50+ team members to transform the insurance industry and QBE as a business. We have leveraged technologies and produced creative solutions to offer the best-in-class digitised processes and experience for our customers. 
We currently have an exciting opportunity within the team for a curious and meticulous Data Scientist or Senior Data Scientist. The role serves as a modelling and data science partner for assigned business areas responsible for the scientific integrity of work products, including study design, research methodology, and the deployment of statistical approaches and modelling. Moreover, it will play an influential role within the team, providing thought leadership and technical guidance to peers.
Key Responsibilities

Leading analytical conversation with business centred on “The art of the possible using data science”, exploring data from a modelling perspective, and performing initial exploratory data analysis to assess business value
Working with information management specialists to identify and classify new feature sets, explore machine learning algorithms, and extract new feature sets
Working in close partnership with analytics managers to size analytical opportunities and execute plans that ensure a positive commercial return
Developing, implementing and maintaining analytical models to identify fraud, drive recoveries and renewals, drive profitable growth, and improve underwriting, pricing and claims performance
Building analytical application designs and prototyping to test ideas and drive innovation in an agile fashion
Working with analytics partners to build and operationalise models, quantifying and analysing model performance, and overseeing model refreshing requirements
Managing analytical projects and coordinating activities with other shared services partners by prioritising relevant activities and providing subject matter expertise
Assisting in the development of commercial propositions involving the use of analytics within insurance core functions through own analysis, prior experience, and research & development
Implementing fit-for-purpose analytics tools and infrastructure that will be adopted by end users (e.g. claims handlers)
Contributing to IT strategy
Positively promoting the department, division and company as a whole, in order to maximise brand leverage and develop the team’s profile
Actively undertaking personal development to ensure up-to-date skills and knowledge
Acting as a point of reference to guide and advise junior members of the team to ensure sharing of knowledge and best practice
Contributing to a positive environment by demonstrating cultural expectations and guiding leaders to reward performance, and valuing “can do” people, accountability, diversity and inclusion, flexibility, continuous improvement, collaboration, creativity and fun
Adopting QBE values in personal work behaviours, decision-making, contributions and interpersonal interactions
Managing own career development by soliciting feedback and valuing other perspectives

Your Story So Far

Degree qualified in econometrics, mathematics, statistics or related discipline
Expert understanding of data modelling techniques, tools/language - R, Python, Scala, SAS, etc.
Strong knowledge of statistical/data mining methods and application in a business environment
Experience in working in Big data technology (Hadoop, NoSQL DB)
Track record of implementing models that deliver significant sustained business impact
Good understanding of Data Science domain, statistical and analytical model development and implementation
Proficient in machine learning techniques and related disciplines
Significant data management experience, gained from within the financial services sector, ideally within general insurance
Good knowledge of visualisation tools such as PowerBI, Tableau, etc.
Strong project management, collaboration and communication skills
Ability to apply logic and reasoning to identify solutions to complex business problems and implement solutions
Business and financial acumen
Curiosity to learn and keep up with market trends and innovations
Flexibility to adapt in a complex changing environment
Ability to lead, manage and motivate a team, engage and influence stakeholders at all levels
Strong written and verbal communication skills

We are here to support you
We offer a range of benefits to help provide holistic support for your work life, whatever your circumstances. As an QBE employee you will have access to and benefit from:

‘Hybrid Working’ – a mix of working from home and in the office to enhance your work/life balance
Our ‘At My Best’ wellbeing program, including free holistic wellbeing coaching, nutritional, confidential counselling, financial and legal advice
12 weeks’ gender-equal flexible leave for all new parents, including paid super
The ability to maximise retirement savings through voluntary super contributions and company matching
Income protection insurance & reimbursed Death and Total Permanent Disability insurance premiums
Additional leave and support through QBE’s Family Domestic Violence First Responder Network
Discounts on insurance products, car hire, hotels, goods and services including benefits through our various sports and arts sponsorship partners

We value our employee’s experience with us and are proud to have been recognised for the following awards:

2021 LinkedIn Top Employer & HRD Employer of Choice
2020 Best Workplace Diversity & Inclusion and Excellence Award for Best Health & Wellbeing at the Australian HR Awards
Gold Employer status for 2019 & 2020 Australian Workplace Equality Index (AWEI) – the definitive national benchmark on LGBTI workplace inclusion!
Ranked 6th place in the AAGE Top Graduate Employers 2021 as voted by graduates
Top 20 Workplaces for Dads in 2019 and 2020 (HBF Direct Advice for Dads)

Join us

Name: CIB Chief Data Office Data Management Lead – Vice President
Description:
JPMorgan Chase & Co. (NYSE: JPM) is a leading global financial services firm with assets of $3 trillion and operations in more than 60 countries. The firm is a leader in investment banking, financial services for consumers, small business and commercial banking, financial transaction processing and asset management. 
The APAC CIB Chief Data Office (CDO) is a business centric team, part of the wider CIB Chief Data & Analytics Office (‘CDAO’) and is responsible for the execution of the data management strategy, ensuring data policies, governance and standards are applied consistently across LOB and countries. Reporting to the Australia & New Zealand Chief Data Office Lead, the successful candidate will assume responsibility for the delivery of the CIB data strategy agenda in Australia & New Zealand. 
Data is a key priority and focus of the CIB for 2022. This is an ideal, high profile and very high visibility opportunity for a suitable candidate to showcase talent and skillsets. 
Key Responsibilities
The APAC Chief Data Office is a new team and as such is looking for a candidate to support the build out of the function. The individual will be executing multiple data initiatives and programs across the CIB (although some may also be firm-wide), working both regionally and with the global team.  
Typical responsibilities include:

Partner with the Chief Data Office executives in defining and delivering a best in class global  data strategy considering country specific requirements
Perform all activities covered by the firmwide policy and standard
Present a holistic, aggregated view of all aspects of data risk and emerging control issues to senior management and governance committees
Develop reporting/ metrics to support governance meetings and managers with supervisory responsibilities e.g. Data Protection Officers
Partner with Compliance, Control Management and Cyber Tech Controls to advise on local implementation and ensure that local data management implementations in support of regulatory data-related requirements at country and legal entity level are consistent with CIB-wide data management practices and tools
Regulatory Change Implementation for all data related regulations and ensure processes and procedures are in place to meet the requirements; partner with Firmwide leads to ensure implementation is consistent across the location. 
Prepare/participate in regulatory inspections/audits/CCORR testing
Partner with Compliance, Government Relations and Office of Regulatory Affairs in the region to stay on top of data-related regulatory initiatives
Engage actively in regulatory advocacy ensuring that a message consistent with CIB’s global data advocacy strategy and Country level advocacy is on top of lawmakers’ and regulators’ mind across the region
Promote awareness of data culture across all CIB LOBs, conduct data governance training and communication strategy / campaign.
Drive Data Quality Strategy and implementation with overall goal to drive business value from better quality data
Help drive strategic vision of enabling data use while protecting data as an asset to the firm and help promote this culture with the business.
Partner closely with our AI/ML teams, AI Research, QR, Front Office, Business Managers, Operations and Technology teams
Act as a trusted senior partner to the business and provide advisory services as needed.

Qualifications  

BS/BA degree with at least 10 years of experience working in the financial services industry, Emerging Technology and Big Data experience a plus
The candidate must be a self-motivated leader with the ability to work in a fast-paced, results-driven environment.
Experience leading high profile programs and / or teams.
Demonstrated ability to interact and work effectively with senior management and other senior stakeholders, including influencing at this level of seniority to support the goals of the business.
Strong verbal, written, presentation and communication skills, including use of Excel and PowerPoint.
Knowledge of Tableau, Qlik or Alteryx is a bonus.
Demonstrated experience in emerging technology and big data in the financial services industry.
Strong data analysis, data management and problem-solving skills; project and program management skills are a plus.
Effective influencing and persuasion skills with groups outside of core team; ability to build consensus at a senior level.
Attention to detail and ability to work independently.
Ability to direct and lead others, directly and indirectly, locally, and globally.
Strong interpersonal and relationship building skills.
Ability to thrive in a changing work environment.
Ability to own tasks under aggressive targets and effectively adapt and reprioritise to changes in plan.

Name: Senior Systems Engineer (CI-CD)
Description:
Senior Systems Engineer – CI CD

You’ll enjoy solving analytical problems to help our team to reach highest potential and earn stakeholder trust
We nurture and support our people through career development and Flexibility
Together we can deliver the future of banking and customer satisfaction

Do work that matters
Technology (BU) is responsible for the world leading application of technology and operations across every aspect of CommBank, from innovative product platforms for our customers to essential tools within our business. We also use technology to drive efficient and timely processing, an essential component of great customer service.
Chief Data Office’s vision is to achieve better customer outcomes resulting in sustainable competitive advantage through analytically led decision making. We are also committed to providing high quality information to manage our business and meet regulatory obligations. We provide a range of services to our internal customers across all business units of the Group including strategy, architecture, data science, business intelligence, engineering and program delivery.
We are accountable for the Group’s key analytics capabilities including Big Data (Omnia, Teradata), BI/Analytics Applications (like SAS, Tableau, Alteryx, Oracle BI, Zeppelin, Jupyter, RStudio, H2O, Trifacta, Collibra, Alation) and Decisioning (Pega) platforms. We are focused on enhancing these to create world-leading capabilities for analytics, information management and decisioning.
See yourself in the team
A Senior Systems Engineer in the Decisioning team is responsible for designing, deploying and operating the team’s BI and analytics applications, in line with Agile and DevOps principles.
You will work with a range of different tools and technologies. And interact with a broad set of teams and customers across the bank. A knack for identifying and suggesting improvements to process inefficiencies is a must.
We believe in using the right tool for the job so an open mind and an ability to learn new tech stacks, languages and frameworks will go a long way.
We are interested in hearing from people who can:

Understand our customers' core business objectives and design end-to-end solutions to address them with primary focus on scalable architecture and design.
Use your analytical mindset to drive decisions based on data.
Participate in the full lifecycle of agile projects (ideation through implementation).
Be recognised as an SME for platform and application characteristics such as operational overhead, cost of change, appropriate use cases, and demonstrate an understanding of these characteristics in your
Approach to development, support and operations of the platform and applications.
Support strategic direction by understanding the business outcomes the squad is working towards solve, and how the work of the squad relates to customer outcomes.

We use a broad range of tools, languages, and frameworks. We don’t expect you to know them all but experience or exposure with some of these (or equivalents) will set you up for success in this team;

5 + of experience in system architecture and design
Experience in vendor and open source application deployment and management
Strong programming skills in Python and/or Nodejs
Strong scripting skills in at least one of the following scripting languages such as Bash/shell, PowerShell.
Strong background in Linux and experience in automation and configuration management tools such as Ansible, Puppet, Chef etc.
Experience in containerised application deployments e.g. Docker
Experience with Git for version control and Artifactory for artefacts management.
Implementing continuous integration and delivery pipelines using Teamcity and/or Jenkins.
Experience in Amazon Web Services (AWS) and/or Microsoft Azure
Experience of working with Kubernetes/ECS

Working with us:
Whether you’re passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career with CommBank is for you. 
Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive, and flexible workplace with flexible work locations. One where we’re driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.
Here, you’ll thrive. You’ll be supported when faced with challenges and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We’re hiring engineers from across all of Australia, you’ll be empowered to do your best work and be given the choice on when and where that work happens. We really love working here, and we think you will too.

If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.
We're aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.
Advertising End Date: 29/06/2022

Name: Range Analyst - Big W
Description:
What we're like

At BIG W everyday’s a big day. For you, this could be the start of something big. There are over 15,000 of us, in the biggest cities and the tiniest towns. And each of us has an important role to play to help make a real difference for families by providing real value, real solutions and real care. 

If you have a passion for designing and delivering great customer and team experiences, a desire to join a business that is rapidly evolving into a purpose led digital retailer enabled by a great store network, and you’re looking for a place that cares about your development and growth, you could be who we’re looking for.

The Role 

The Space & Range Team is made up of smart people with smart ideas, delivering the best planogram and ranging through data and insights across BIG W. We’re a team that is curious, resourceful and willing to experiment with everything that we do.

In your new role as Range Analyst you will bring BIG W Strategy to life by partnering with key stakeholders to deliver a differentiated offer for our customers, using customer data and analytics to drive decision making to increase Customer Advocacy, Sales, EBIT, and Stock Availability 
We partner across the ecosystem to analyse customer & market insights and data to come up with the best possible category plan and product planogram to deliver the best shopping experiences.  

Key responsibilities will include:

Utilising data, customer & market insights to provide recommendations & influence key stakeholders to build the best offer that our customers desire
Project manage & execute the Customer 1st Ranging process, from strategy development to roll out, including engagement with cross functional teams to deliver a great experience for our customers  
Work with stakeholders to deliver towards the range review Critical Path according to the set timelines Improve and evolve ranging process in line with the company’s strategic objectives  
Drive continuous improvement and evolve ranging process in line with the company’s strategic objectives  


About You

You will bring to the role an extensive background in commercial and data analytics. Your strategic thinking will support the co-creation of the ranging strategy and enhance the overall BIG W customer experience. 

You will bring the following knowledge, skills, experience & atrributes:  

Experience in retail/ FMCG preferred  
Business Transformation experience is preferred
Strong Analytical skills & Excel skills
Strong verbal and written communication skills


What's in it for you?

An attractive remuneration package including base, super and bonus
Opportunity to collaborate with some of the brightest and best minds in Australia both across BIG W and Woolworths Tech options - Woolworths is the largest employer of Google Apps in Australia, are early adopters of Agile and have BYOD options too
An exciting career - as our business grows, so do the opportunities for our people
Flexibility and work-life balance policies that will help you thrive  

Joining the Group
Woolworths Group has announced it will be requiring Australian team members to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 (subject to medical and religious exemptions).
 
As part of the wider Woolworths Group, we care deeply about creating a workplace where our team members feel valued, respected and empowered. We are committed to providing equal opportunity regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation or life stage. We are proud to be recognised as a Gold Tier Employer in the Australian Workplace Equality Index for LGBTQ+ inclusion and as an Employer of Choice for Gender Equality by the Workplace Gender Equality Agency.
 
As our Group continues to evolve, innovate and support our communities, we encourage our team members to do the same with their own careers, by providing ongoing opportunities to grow and make a real difference. 
 
If you meet a number of the requirements, but not all, we encourage you to submit your application. You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn #LI
 
Our Talent Acquisition Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. BIG W is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.
